id":"08fdead4-40c4-4e96-88bd-ec7f94b0bf30"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012aSeSfap4HAxy1nw11ogbJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Greybox ship interior: multi-room layout (24m×12m) with cockpit, machine room, corridor,\n     2→## vestibule, four module zones, and entry/exit transition system.\n     3→class_name ShipInterior\n     4→extends Node3D\n     5→\n     6→# ── Signals ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n     7→signal player_entered_ship\n     8→signal player_exited_ship\n     9→signal placement_zone_interacted(zone_index: int)\n    10→\n    11→# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n    12→## Room dimensions (per M7 wireframe TICKET-0123)\n    13→const CEILING_HEIGHT: float = 3.0\n    14→const CORRIDOR_WIDTH: float = 4.0\n    15→const CORRIDOR_DEPTH: float = 2.0\n    16→const VESTIBULE_WIDTH: float = 4.0\n    17→const VESTIBULE_DEPTH: float = 4.0\n    18→\n    19→## Zone layout — 4 zones in 2×2 grid within machine room\n    20→const ZONE_SIZE: float = 3.0\n    21→const ZONE_COUNT: int = 4\n    22→const ZONE_A_CENTER := Vector3(-2.5, 0.0, 4.5)\n    23→const ZONE_B_CENTER := Vector3(2.5, 0.0, 4.5)\n    24→const ZONE_C_CENTER := Vector3(-2.5, 0.0, -0.5)\n    25→const ZONE_D_CENTER := Vector3(2.5, 0.0, -0.5)\n    26→const ZONE_INTERACT_OFFSET: float = 0.5\n    27→const INTERACT_RANGE: float = 2.0\n    28→\n    29→## Greybox materials\n    30→const COLOR_FLOOR := Color(\"#4A4A4A\")\n    31→const COLOR_WALLS_MACHINE := Color(\"#333333\")\n    32→const COLOR_WALLS_COCKPIT := Color(\"#2A2A2A\")\n    33→const COLOR_CEILING := Color(\"#2A2A2A\")\n    34→const COLOR_CORRIDOR := Color(\"#555555\")\n    35→const COLOR_VESTIBULE := Color(\"#555555\")\n    36→const COLOR_ZONE_TEAL := Color(\"#00D4AA\", 0.3)\n    37→const COLOR_ZONE_TEAL_OCCUPIED := Color(\"#00D4AA\", 0.15)\n    38→const COLOR_VIEWPORT_FRAME := Color(\"#333333\")\n    39→const COLOR_LIGHT := Color(\"#E0E0E0\")\n    40→\n    41→## Fade transition\n    42→const FADE_DURATION: float = 0.3\n    43→\n    44→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    45→var _enter_marker: Marker3D = null\n    46→var _exterior_marker: Marker3D = null\n    47→var _zone_areas: Array[Area3D] = []\n    48→var _zone_floor_markers: Array[MeshInstance3D] = []\n    49→var _zone_occupied: Array[bool] = [false, false, false, false]\n    50→var _zone_module_nodes: Array[Node3D] = [null, null, null, null]\n    51→var _fade_rect: ColorRect = null\n    52→var _fade_layer: CanvasLayer = null\n    53→var _player_ref: CharacterBody3D = null\n    54→var _is_player_inside: bool = false\n    55→var _player_in_exit_zone: bool = false\n    56→var _exit_zone: ShipExitZone = null\n    57→var _terminal_area: Area3D = null\n    58→var _cockpit_console_area: Area3D = null\n    59→var _sub_viewport: SubViewport = null\n    60→var _viewport_camera: Camera3D = null\n    61→\n    62→# ── Built-in Virtual Methods ──────────────────────────────\n    63→\n    64→func _ready() -> void:\n    65→\t_build_geometry()\n    66→\t_build_module_zones()\n    67→\t_build_spawn_markers()\n    68→\t_build_cockpit_features()\n    69→\t_build_viewport_window()\n    70→\t_build_lighting()\n    71→\t_build_fade_overlay()\n    72→\t_build_terminal()\n    73→\t_build_cockpit_console_area()\n    74→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: initialized — 24m×12m multi-room layout\")\n    75→\n    76→# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n    77→\n    78→## Sets the player reference for interaction detection.\n    79→func setup(player: CharacterBody3D) -> void:\n    80→\t_player_ref = player\n    81→\n    82→## Returns true if the player is currently inside the ship.\n    83→func is_player_inside() -> bool:\n    84→\treturn _is_player_inside\n    85→\n    86→## Transitions the player into the ship interior with a fade.\n    87→func enter_ship(player: CharacterBody3D) -> void:\n    88→\tif _is_player_inside:\n    89→\t\treturn\n    90→\t_player_ref = player\n    91→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: player entering ship\")\n    92→\tawait _fade_out()\n    93→\tplayer.global_position = _enter_marker.global_position\n    94→\t_is_player_inside = true\n    95→\tplayer_entered_ship.emit()\n    96→\tawait _fade_in()\n    97→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: player entered ship\")\n    98→\n    99→## Transitions the player out of the ship with a fade.\n   100→func exit_ship() -> void:\n   101→\tif not _is_player_inside or not _player_ref:\n   102→\t\treturn\n   103→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: player exiting ship\")\n   104→\tawait _fade_out()\n   105→\t_player_ref.velocity = Vector3.ZERO\n   106→\t_player_ref.global_position = _exterior_marker.global_position\n   107→\t_is_player_inside = false\n   108→\tplayer_exited_ship.emit()\n   109→\tawait _fade_in()\n   110→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: player exited ship\")\n   111→\n   112→## Returns the exterior marker position for the test world to set.\n   113→func get_exterior_marker() -> Marker3D:\n   114→\treturn _exterior_marker\n   115→\n   116→## Sets the exterior exit position.\n   117→func set_exterior_position(pos: Vector3) -> void:\n   118→\t_exterior_marker.global_position = pos\n   119→\n   120→## Returns the enter marker for the interior.\n   121→func get_enter_marker() -> Marker3D:\n   122→\treturn _enter_marker\n   123→\n   124→## Returns true if the given zone index is occupied by a module.\n   125→func is_zone_occupied(zone_index: int) -> bool:\n   126→\tif zone_index < 0 or zone_index >= _zone_occupied.size():\n   127→\t\treturn false\n   128→\treturn _zone_occupied[zone_index]\n   129→\n   130→## Places a module mesh in the given zone. Returns the parent Node3D for the module.\n   131→func place_module_in_zone(zone_index: int, module_mesh: Node3D) -> void:\n   132→\tif zone_index < 0 or zone_index >= _zone_occupied.size():\n   133→\t\treturn\n   134→\t_zone_occupied[zone_index] = true\n   135→\tvar zone_centers: Array[Vector3] = [ZONE_A_CENTER, ZONE_B_CENTER, ZONE_C_CENTER, ZONE_D_CENTER]\n   136→\tmodule_mesh.position = zone_centers[zone_index]\n   137→\tadd_child(module_mesh)\n   138→\t_zone_module_nodes[zone_index] = module_mesh\n   139→\t_update_zone_visual(zone_index)\n   140→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: module placed in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n   141→\n   142→## Removes a module from the given zone.\n   143→func remove_module_from_zone(zone_index: int) -> void:\n   144→\tif zone_index < 0 or zone_index >= _zone_occupied.size():\n   145→\t\treturn\n   146→\tif _zone_module_nodes[zone_index]:\n   147→\t\t_zone_module_nodes[zone_index].queue_free()\n   148→\t\t_zone_module_nodes[zone_index] = null\n   149→\t_zone_occupied[zone_index] = false\n   150→\t_update_zone_visual(zone_index)\n   151→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: module removed from zone %d\" % zone_index)\n   152→\n   153→## Returns the module node at a given zone, or null.\n   154→func get_module_at_zone(zone_index: int) -> Node3D:\n   155→\tif zone_index < 0 or zone_index >= _zone_module_nodes.size():\n   156→\t\treturn null\n   157→\treturn _zone_module_nodes[zone_index]\n   158→\n   159→## Returns the number of placement zones.\n   160→func get_zone_count() -> int:\n   161→\treturn _zone_areas.size()\n   162→\n   163→## Returns the first empty zone index, or -1 if all occupied.\n   164→func get_first_empty_zone() -> int:\n   165→\tfor i: int in range(_zone_occupied.size()):\n   166→\t\tif not _zone_occupied[i]:\n   167→\t\t\treturn i\n   168→\treturn -1\n   169→\n   170→## Returns true if the player is standing in the exit zone.\n   171→func is_player_in_exit_zone() -> bool:\n   172→\treturn _player_in_exit_zone\n   173→\n   174→## Returns true if the player is near the tech tree terminal.\n   175→func is_player_near_terminal() -> bool:\n   176→\tif not _player_ref or not _terminal_area:\n   177→\t\treturn false\n   178→\treturn _terminal_area.get_overlapping_bodies().has(_player_ref)\n   179→\n   180→## Returns true if the player is near the cockpit navigation console.\n   181→func is_player_near_cockpit_console() -> bool:\n   182→\tif not _player_ref or not _cockpit_console_area:\n   183→\t\treturn false\n   184→\treturn _cockpit_console_area.get_overlapping_bodies().has(_player_ref)\n   185→\n   186→## Returns true if the player is near a placement zone. Returns the zone index or -1.\n   187→func get_nearby_zone_index() -> int:\n   188→\tif not _player_ref:\n   189→\t\treturn -1\n   190→\tfor i: int in range(_zone_areas.size()):\n   191→\t\tvar zone: Area3D = _zone_areas[i]\n   192→\t\tif zone.get_overlapping_bodies().has(_player_ref):\n   193→\t\t\treturn i\n   194→\treturn -1\n   195→\n   196→## Configures the viewport window to render the exterior world.\n   197→## camera_position is the world-space position for the exterior camera.\n   198→## Since the camera's parent (SubViewport) is non-spatial, local position equals world position.\n   199→func setup_viewport_world(world: World3D, camera_position: Vector3) -> void:\n   200→\tif _sub_viewport:\n   201→\t\t_sub_viewport.world_3d = world\n   202→\tif _viewport_camera:\n   203→\t\t_viewport_camera.position = camera_position\n   204→\t\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: viewport camera positioned at %s\" % str(camera_position))\n   205→\n   206→# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n   207→\n   208→func _build_geometry() -> void:\n   209→\t_build_floors()\n   210→\t_build_ceilings()\n   211→\t_build_machine_room_walls()\n   212→\t_build_cockpit_walls()\n   213→\t_build_corridor_walls()\n   214→\t_build_vestibule_walls()\n   215→\t_build_viewport_frame()\n   216→\n   217→func _build_floors() -> void:\n   218→\t# Machine room: 12m × 12m, center at Z=+2 (Z range: -4 to +8)\n   219→\t_create_static_surface(\"MachineRoomFloor\",\n   220→\t\tVector3(12.0, 0.1, 12.0), Vector3(0.0, -0.05, 2.0), COLOR_FLOOR, 0.8)\n   221→\t# Cockpit: 12m × 6m, center at Z=-9 (Z range: -12 to -6)\n   222→\t_create_static_surface(\"CockpitFloor\",\n   223→\t\tVector3(12.0, 0.1, 6.0), Vector3(0.0, -0.05, -9.0), COLOR_FLOOR, 0.8)\n   224→\t# Corridor: 4m × 2m, center at Z=-5 (Z range: -6 to -4)\n   225→\t_create_static_surface(\"CorridorFloor\",\n   226→\t\tVector3(4.0, 0.1, 2.0), Vector3(0.0, -0.05, -5.0), COLOR_CORRIDOR, 0.8)\n   227→\t# Vestibule: 4m × 4m, center at Z=+10 (Z range: +8 to +12)\n   228→\t_create_static_surface(\"VestibuleFloor\",\n   229→\t\tVector3(4.0, 0.1, 4.0), Vector3(0.0, -0.05, 10.0), COLOR_VESTIBULE, 0.8)\n   230→\n   231→func _build_ceilings() -> void:\n   232→\t_create_static_surface(\"MachineRoomCeiling\",\n   233→\t\tVector3(12.0, 0.1, 12.0), Vector3(0.0, 3.0, 2.0), COLOR_CEILING, 0.9)\n   234→\t_create_static_surface(\"CockpitCeiling\",\n   235→\t\tVector3(12.0, 0.1, 6.0), Vector3(0.0, 3.0, -9.0), COLOR_CEILING, 0.9)\n   236→\t_create_static_surface(\"CorridorCeiling\",\n   237→\t\tVector3(4.0, 0.1, 2.0), Vector3(0.0, 3.0, -5.0), COLOR_CEILING, 0.9)\n   238→\t_create_static_surface(\"VestibuleCeiling\",\n   239→\t\tVector3(4.0, 0.1, 4.0), Vector3(0.0, 3.0, 10.0), COLOR_CEILING, 0.9)\n   240→\n   241→func _build_machine_room_walls() -> void:\n   242→\tvar wall_y: float = CEILING_HEIGHT / 2.0\n   243→\t# West wall: X=-6, Z:-4 to +8\n   244→\t_create_static_surface(\"MachineRoomWallWest\",\n   245→\t\tVector3(0.2, 3.0, 12.0), Vector3(-6.0, wall_y, 2.0), COLOR_WALLS_MACHINE, 0.9)\n   246→\t# East wall: X=+6, Z:-4 to +8\n   247→\t_create_static_surface(\"MachineRoomWallEast\",\n   248→\t\tVector3(0.2, 3.0, 12.0), Vector3(6.0, wall_y, 2.0), COLOR_WALLS_MACHINE, 0.9)\n   249→\t# North wall left section: X:-6 to -2 at Z=-4 (corridor opening X:-2 to +2)\n   250→\t_create_static_surface(\"MachineRoomWallNorthLeft\",\n   251→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 0.2), Vector3(-4.0, wall_y, -4.0), COLOR_WALLS_MACHINE, 0.9)\n   252→\t# North wall right section: X:+2 to +6 at Z=-4\n   253→\t_create_static_surface(\"MachineRoomWallNorthRight\",\n   254→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 0.2), Vector3(4.0, wall_y, -4.0), COLOR_WALLS_MACHINE, 0.9)\n   255→\t# South wall left section: X:-6 to -2 at Z=+8 (vestibule opening X:-2 to +2)\n   256→\t_create_static_surface(\"MachineRoomWallSouthLeft\",\n   257→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 0.2), Vector3(-4.0, wall_y, 8.0), COLOR_WALLS_MACHINE, 0.9)\n   258→\t# South wall right section: X:+2 to +6 at Z=+8\n   259→\t_create_static_surface(\"MachineRoomWallSouthRight\",\n   260→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 0.2), Vector3(4.0, wall_y, 8.0), COLOR_WALLS_MACHINE, 0.9)\n   261→\n   262→func _build_cockpit_walls() -> void:\n   263→\tvar wall_y: float = CEILING_HEIGHT / 2.0\n   264→\t# West wall: X=-6, Z:-12 to -6\n   265→\t_create_static_surface(\"CockpitWallWest\",\n   266→\t\tVector3(0.2, 3.0, 6.0), Vector3(-6.0, wall_y, -9.0), COLOR_WALLS_COCKPIT, 0.9)\n   267→\t# East wall: X=+6, Z:-12 to -6\n   268→\t_create_static_surface(\"CockpitWallEast\",\n   269→\t\tVector3(0.2, 3.0, 6.0), Vector3(6.0, wall_y, -9.0), COLOR_WALLS_COCKPIT, 0.9)\n   270→\t# North wall left section: X:-6 to -2 at Z=-12 (viewport opening X:-2 to +2, Y:1.5 to 3.0)\n   271→\t_create_static_surface(\"CockpitWallNorthLeft\",\n   272→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 0.2), Vector3(-4.0, wall_y, -12.0), COLOR_WALLS_COCKPIT, 0.9)\n   273→\t# North wall right section: X:+2 to +6 at Z=-12\n   274→\t_create_static_surface(\"CockpitWallNorthRight\",\n   275→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 0.2), Vector3(4.0, wall_y, -12.0), COLOR_WALLS_COCKPIT, 0.9)\n   276→\t# North wall below viewport: X:-2 to +2, Y:0 to 1.5 at Z=-12\n   277→\t_create_static_surface(\"CockpitWallNorthBelow\",\n   278→\t\tVector3(4.0, 1.5, 0.2), Vector3(0.0, 0.75, -12.0), COLOR_WALLS_COCKPIT, 0.9)\n   279→\t# South wall left section: X:-6 to -2 at Z=-6 (corridor opening X:-2 to +2)\n   280→\t_create_static_surface(\"CockpitWallSouthLeft\",\n   281→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 0.2), Vector3(-4.0, wall_y, -6.0), COLOR_WALLS_COCKPIT, 0.9)\n   282→\t# South wall right section: X:+2 to +6 at Z=-6\n   283→\t_create_static_surface(\"CockpitWallSouthRight\",\n   284→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 0.2), Vector3(4.0, wall_y, -6.0), COLOR_WALLS_COCKPIT, 0.9)\n   285→\n   286→func _build_corridor_walls() -> void:\n   287→\tvar wall_y: float = CEILING_HEIGHT / 2.0\n   288→\t# West wall: X=-2, Z:-6 to -4\n   289→\t_create_static_surface(\"CorridorWallWest\",\n   290→\t\tVector3(0.2, 3.0, 2.0), Vector3(-2.0, wall_y, -5.0), COLOR_CORRIDOR, 0.9)\n   291→\t# East wall: X=+2, Z:-6 to -4\n   292→\t_create_static_surface(\"CorridorWallEast\",\n   293→\t\tVector3(0.2, 3.0, 2.0), Vector3(2.0, wall_y, -5.0), COLOR_CORRIDOR, 0.9)\n   294→\t# Solid fill walls flanking the corridor (seal gaps between machine room and cockpit)\n   295→\t# West fill: X:-6 to -2, Z:-6 to -4\n   296→\t_create_static_surface(\"CorridorFillWest\",\n   297→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 2.0), Vector3(-4.0, wall_y, -5.0), COLOR_WALLS_MACHINE, 0.9)\n   298→\t# East fill: X:+2 to +6, Z:-6 to -4\n   299→\t_create_static_surface(\"CorridorFillEast\",\n   300→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 2.0), Vector3(4.0, wall_y, -5.0), COLOR_WALLS_MACHINE, 0.9)\n   301→\n   302→func _build_vestibule_walls() -> void:\n   303→\tvar wall_y: float = CEILING_HEIGHT / 2.0\n   304→\t# West wall: X=-2, Z:+8 to +12\n   305→\t_create_static_surface(\"VestibuleWallWest\",\n   306→\t\tVector3(0.2, 3.0, 4.0), Vector3(-2.0, wall_y, 10.0), COLOR_VESTIBULE, 0.9)\n   307→\t# East wall: X=+2, Z:+8 to +12\n   308→\t_create_static_surface(\"VestibuleWallEast\",\n   309→\t\tVector3(0.2, 3.0, 4.0), Vector3(2.0, wall_y, 10.0), COLOR_VESTIBULE, 0.9)\n   310→\t# South wall (back): X:-2 to +2 at Z=+12\n   311→\t_create_static_surface(\"VestibuleWallSouth\",\n   312→\t\tVector3(4.0, 3.0, 0.2), Vector3(0.0, wall_y, 12.0), COLOR_VESTIBULE, 0.9)\n   313→\n   314→func _build_viewport_frame() -> void:\n   315→\t# Thin frame around cockpit viewport opening (X:-2 to +2, Y:1.5 to 3.0, Z=-12)\n   316→\tvar frame_mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   317→\tframe_mat.albedo_color = COLOR_VIEWPORT_FRAME\n   318→\tframe_mat.roughness = 0.9\n   319→\n   320→\t# Bottom edge\n   321→\tvar bottom_frame := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   322→\tbottom_frame.name = \"ViewportFrameBottom\"\n   323→\tvar bottom_mesh := BoxMesh.new()\n   324→\tbottom_mesh.size = Vector3(4.2, 0.1, 0.1)\n   325→\tbottom_frame.mesh = bottom_mesh\n   326→\tbottom_frame.material_override = frame_mat\n   327→\tbottom_frame.position = Vector3(0.0, 1.5, -11.95)\n   328→\tadd_child(bottom_frame)\n   329→\n   330→\t# Left edge\n   331→\tvar left_frame := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   332→\tleft_frame.name = \"ViewportFrameLeft\"\n   333→\tvar left_mesh := BoxMesh.new()\n   334→\tleft_mesh.size = Vector3(0.1, 1.5, 0.1)\n   335→\tleft_frame.mesh = left_mesh\n   336→\tleft_frame.material_override = frame_mat\n   337→\tleft_frame.position = Vector3(-2.0, 2.25, -11.95)\n   338→\tadd_child(left_frame)\n   339→\n   340→\t# Right edge\n   341→\tvar right_frame := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   342→\tright_frame.name = \"ViewportFrameRight\"\n   343→\tvar right_mesh := BoxMesh.new()\n   344→\tright_mesh.size = Vector3(0.1, 1.5, 0.1)\n   345→\tright_frame.mesh = right_mesh\n   346→\tright_frame.material_override = frame_mat\n   347→\tright_frame.position = Vector3(2.0, 2.25, -11.95)\n   348→\tadd_child(right_frame)\n   349→\n   350→\t# Top edge\n   351→\tvar top_frame := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   352→\ttop_frame.name = \"ViewportFrameTop\"\n   353→\tvar top_mesh := BoxMesh.new()\n   354→\ttop_mesh.size = Vector3(4.2, 0.1, 0.1)\n   355→\ttop_frame.mesh = top_mesh\n   356→\ttop_frame.material_override = frame_mat\n   357→\ttop_frame.position = Vector3(0.0, 3.0, -11.95)\n   358→\tadd_child(top_frame)\n   359→\n   360→func _build_module_zones() -> void:\n   361→\tvar zone_centers: Array[Vector3] = [ZONE_A_CENTER, ZONE_B_CENTER, ZONE_C_CENTER, ZONE_D_CENTER]\n   362→\tfor i: int in range(ZONE_COUNT):\n   363→\t\tvar center: Vector3 = zone_centers[i]\n   364→\n   365→\t\t# Floor marking (emissive teal overlay)\n   366→\t\tvar marker_mesh := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   367→\t\tmarker_mesh.name = \"ZoneMarker_%d\" % i\n   368→\t\tvar plane := PlaneMesh.new()\n   369→\t\tplane.size = Vector2(ZONE_SIZE, ZONE_SIZE)\n   370→\t\tmarker_mesh.mesh = plane\n   371→\t\tvar marker_mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   372→\t\tmarker_mat.albedo_color = COLOR_ZONE_TEAL\n   373→\t\tmarker_mat.emission_enabled = true\n   374→\t\tmarker_mat.emission = Color(\"#00D4AA\")\n   375→\t\tmarker_mat.emission_energy_multiplier = 0.3\n   376→\t\tmarker_mat.transparency = BaseMaterial3D.TRANSPARENCY_ALPHA\n   377→\t\tmarker_mesh.material_override = marker_mat\n   378→\t\tmarker_mesh.position = Vector3(center.x, 0.01, center.z)\n   379→\t\tadd_child(marker_mesh)\n   380→\t\t_zone_floor_markers.append(marker_mesh)\n   381→\n   382→\t\t# Interaction trigger area (slightly larger than zone for player detection)\n   383→\t\tvar zone_area := Area3D.new()\n   384→\t\tzone_area.name = \"PlacementZone_%d\" % i\n   385→\t\tzone_area.collision_layer = 0\n   386→\t\tzone_area.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n   387→\t\tvar zone_col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   388→\t\tzone_col.name = \"ZoneShape_%d\" % i\n   389→\t\tvar zone_shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   390→\t\tzone_shape.size = Vector3(ZONE_SIZE + 1.0, 2.0, ZONE_SIZE + 1.0)\n   391→\t\tzone_col.shape = zone_shape\n   392→\t\tzone_col.position = Vector3(center.x, 1.0, center.z + ZONE_INTERACT_OFFSET)\n   393→\t\tzone_area.add_child(zone_col)\n   394→\t\tadd_child(zone_area)\n   395→\t\t_zone_areas.append(zone_area)\n   396→\n   397→func _build_spawn_markers() -> void:\n   398→\t# Interior entry point — inside vestibule, facing north (per wireframe: X=0, Y=0, Z=+10)\n   399→\t_enter_marker = Marker3D.new()\n   400→\t_enter_marker.name = \"InteriorSpawn\"\n   401→\t_enter_marker.position = Vector3(0.0, 0.0, 10.0)\n   402→\tadd_child(_enter_marker)\n   403→\n   404→\t# Exit trigger area — near the back of the vestibule (Z ≈ +11.5)\n   405→\t_exit_zone = ShipExitZone.new()\n   406→\t_exit_zone.name = \"ExitTrigger\"\n   407→\t_exit_zone.collision_layer = 0\n   408→\t_exit_zone.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n   409→\tvar exit_col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   410→\tvar exit_shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   411→\texit_shape.size = Vector3(VESTIBULE_WIDTH, 2.0, 1.0)\n   412→\texit_col.shape = exit_shape\n   413→\texit_col.position = Vector3(0.0, 1.0, 11.5)\n   414→\t_exit_zone.add_child(exit_col)\n   415→\tadd_child(_exit_zone)\n   416→\t_exit_zone.body_entered.connect(_on_exit_zone_entered)\n   417→\t_exit_zone.body_exited.connect(_on_exit_zone_exited)\n   418→\t_exit_zone.add_to_group(\"interaction_prompt_source\")\n   419→\n   420→\t# Exterior marker — default position, set by test world after instancing\n   421→\t_exterior_marker = Marker3D.new()\n   422→\t_exterior_marker.name = \"ExteriorSpawn\"\n   423→\t_exterior_marker.position = Vector3(0.0, 0.0, 14.0)\n   424→\tadd_child(_exterior_marker)\n   425→\n   426→func _build_cockpit_features() -> void:\n   427→\t# Marker3D placeholder for TICKET-0127 (Status Display Area)\n   428→\tvar status_marker := Marker3D.new()\n   429→\tstatus_marker.name = \"StatusDisplayArea\"\n   430→\tstatus_marker.position = Vector3(0.0, 1.5, -9.0)\n   431→\tadd_child(status_marker)\n   432→\n   433→\t# Marker3D placeholder for TICKET-0128 (Viewport Area)\n   434→\tvar viewport_marker := Marker3D.new()\n   435→\tviewport_marker.name = \"ViewportArea\"\n   436→\tviewport_marker.position = Vector3(0.0, 2.25, -12.0)\n   437→\tadd_child(viewport_marker)\n   438→\n   439→func _build_viewport_window() -> void:\n   440→\t# SubViewport renders the exterior world through a secondary camera so the\n   441→\t# cockpit window shows the actual outside environment (sky + geometry).\n   442→\t# The interior is placed underground, so transparency alone cannot work.\n   443→\t_sub_viewport = SubViewport.new()\n   444→\t_sub_viewport.name = \"ExteriorViewport\"\n   445→\t_sub_viewport.size = Vector2i(512, 256)\n   446→\t_sub_viewport.render_target_update_mode = SubViewport.UPDATE_ALWAYS\n   447→\t_sub_viewport.transparent_bg = false\n   448→\tadd_child(_sub_viewport)\n   449→\n   450→\t# Camera will be positioned at the ship exterior by setup_viewport_world()\n   451→\t_viewport_camera = Camera3D.new()\n   452→\t_viewport_camera.name = \"ExteriorCamera\"\n   453→\t_viewport_camera.fov = 70.0\n   454→\t_sub_viewport.add_child(_viewport_camera)\n   455→\n   456→\t# Window surface — QuadMesh filling the viewport frame opening (4m × 1.5m)\n   457→\tvar window_mesh := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   458→\twindow_mesh.name = \"ViewportWindow\"\n   459→\tvar quad := QuadMesh.new()\n   460→\tquad.size = Vector2(4.0, 1.5)\n   461→\twindow_mesh.mesh = quad\n   462→\n   463→\t# Unshaded material so interior lighting does not affect the exterior view\n   464→\tvar mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   465→\tmat.shading_mode = BaseMaterial3D.SHADING_MODE_UNSHADED\n   466→\tmat.albedo_texture = _sub_viewport.get_texture()\n   467→\twindow_mesh.material_override = mat\n   468→\twindow_mesh.position = Vector3(0.0, 2.25, -11.97)\n   469→\tadd_child(window_mesh)\n   470→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: viewport window built (SubViewport exterior camera)\")\n   471→\n   472→func _build_lighting() -> void:\n   473→\t# Machine room light — centered overhead at Y=2.8\n   474→\tvar machine_light := OmniLight3D.new()\n   475→\tmachine_light.name = \"MachineRoomLight\"\n   476→\tmachine_light.light_color = COLOR_LIGHT\n   477→\tmachine_light.light_energy = 2.0\n   478→\tmachine_light.omni_range = 15.0\n   479→\tmachine_light.omni_attenuation = 0.5\n   480→\tmachine_light.shadow_enabled = false\n   481→\tmachine_light.position = Vector3(0.0, 2.8, 2.0)\n   482→\tadd_child(machine_light)\n   483→\n   484→\t# Cockpit light — centered overhead\n   485→\tvar cockpit_light := OmniLight3D.new()\n   486→\tcockpit_light.name = \"CockpitLight\"\n   487→\tcockpit_light.light_color = COLOR_LIGHT\n   488→\tcockpit_light.light_energy = 2.0\n   489→\tcockpit_light.omni_range = 12.0\n   490→\tcockpit_light.omni_attenuation = 0.5\n   491→\tcockpit_light.shadow_enabled = false\n   492→\tcockpit_light.position = Vector3(0.0, 2.8, -9.0)\n   493→\tadd_child(cockpit_light)\n   494→\n   495→func _build_fade_overlay() -> void:\n   496→\t_fade_layer = CanvasLayer.new()\n   497→\t_fade_layer.name = \"FadeLayer\"\n   498→\t_fade_layer.layer = 10\n   499→\tadd_child(_fade_layer)\n   500→\n   501→\t_fade_rect = ColorRect.new()\n   502→\t_fade_rect.color = Color.BLACK\n   503→\t_fade_rect.set_anchors_preset(Control.PRESET_FULL_RECT)\n   504→\t_fade_rect.modulate.a = 0.0\n   505→\t_fade_rect.mouse_filter = Control.MOUSE_FILTER_IGNORE\n   506→\t_fade_layer.add_child(_fade_rect)\n   507→\n   508→func _build_terminal() -> void:\n   509→\t# Tech tree terminal on machine room north wall (left of corridor opening)\n   510→\tvar terminal_mesh := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   511→\tterminal_mesh.name = \"TerminalMesh\"\n   512→\tvar box := BoxMesh.new()\n   513→\tbox.size = Vector3(1.0, 1.5, 0.3)\n   514→\tterminal_mesh.mesh = box\n   515→\tvar mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   516→\tmat.albedo_color = Color(\"#2A4A4A\")\n   517→\tmat.emission_enabled = true\n   518→\tmat.emission = Color(\"#00D4AA\")\n   519→\tmat.emission_energy_multiplier = 0.4\n   520→\tterminal_mesh.material_override = mat\n   521→\tterminal_mesh.position = Vector3(-4.0, 0.75, -3.8)\n   522→\tadd_child(terminal_mesh)\n   523→\n   524→\t# Interaction area for terminal\n   525→\t_terminal_area = Area3D.new()\n   526→\t_terminal_area.name = \"TerminalArea\"\n   527→\t_terminal_area.collision_layer = 0\n   528→\t_terminal_area.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n   529→\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   530→\tcol.name = \"TerminalShape\"\n   531→\tvar shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   532→\tshape.size = Vector3(2.0, 2.0, 1.5)\n   533→\tcol.shape = shape\n   534→\tcol.position = Vector3(-4.0, 1.0, -3.0)\n   535→\t_terminal_area.add_child(col)\n   536→\tadd_child(_terminal_area)\n   537→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: tech tree terminal built\")\n   538→\n   539→func _build_cockpit_console_area() -> void:\n   540→\t# Interaction area around the cockpit navigation console (instanced at Z=-11.5 in scene)\n   541→\t# Uses CockpitConsolePromptArea so the HUD prompt is area-gated, not raycast-gated (TICKET-0245)\n   542→\t_cockpit_console_area = CockpitConsolePromptArea.new()\n   543→\t_cockpit_console_area.name = \"CockpitConsoleArea\"\n   544→\t_cockpit_console_area.collision_layer = 0\n   545→\t_cockpit_console_area.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n   546→\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   547→\tcol.name = \"CockpitConsoleShape\"\n   548→\tvar shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   549→\tshape.size = Vector3(3.0, 2.0, 2.0)\n   550→\tcol.shape = shape\n   551→\tcol.position = Vector3(0.0, 1.0, -11.5)\n   552→\t_cockpit_console_area.add_child(col)\n   553→\t_cockpit_console_area.add_to_group(\"interaction_prompt_source\")\n   554→\tadd_child(_cockpit_console_area)\n   555→\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: cockpit console interaction area built\")\n   556→\n   557→func _create_static_surface(surface_name: String, size: Vector3, pos: Vector3, color: Color, roughness: float) -> void:\n   558→\tvar body := StaticBody3D.new()\n   559→\tbody.name = surface_name\n   560→\tbody.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT\n   561→\tbody.collision_mask = 0\n   562→\tbody.position = pos\n   563→\n   564→\tvar mesh_inst := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   565→\tvar box_mesh := BoxMesh.new()\n   566→\tbox_mesh.size = size\n   567→\tmesh_inst.mesh = box_mesh\n   568→\tvar mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   569→\tmat.albedo_color = color\n   570→\tmat.roughness = roughness\n   571→\tmesh_inst.material_override = mat\n   572→\tbody.add_child(mesh_inst)\n   573→\n   574→\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   575→\tvar col_shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   576→\tcol_shape.size = size\n   577→\tcol.shape = col_shape\n   578→\tbody.add_child(col)\n   579→\n   580→\tadd_child(body)\n   581→\n   582→func _update_zone_visual(zone_index: int) -> void:\n   583→\tif zone_index < 0 or zone_index >= _zone_floor_markers.size():\n   584→\t\treturn\n   585→\tvar marker: MeshInstance3D = _zone_floor_markers[zone_index]\n   586→\tvar mat: StandardMaterial3D = marker.material_override as StandardMaterial3D\n   587→\tif _zone_occupied[zone_index]:\n   588→\t\tmat.albedo_color = COLOR_ZONE_TEAL_OCCUPIED\n   589→\t\tmat.emission_energy_multiplier = 0.15\n   590→\telse:\n   591→\t\tmat.albedo_color = COLOR_ZONE_TEAL\n   592→\t\tmat.emission_energy_multiplier = 0.3\n   593→\n   594→func _fade_out() -> Signal:\n   595→\tvar tween: Tween = create_tween()\n   596→\ttween.tween_property(_fade_rect, \"modulate:a\", 1.0, FADE_DURATION)\n   597→\treturn tween.finished\n   598→\n   599→func _fade_in() -> Signal:\n   600→\tvar tween: Tween = create_tween()\n   601→\ttween.tween_property(_fade_rect, \"modulate:a\", 0.0, FADE_DURATION)\n   602→\treturn tween.finished\n   603→\n   604→func _on_exit_zone_entered(body: Node3D) -> void:\n   605→\tif body == _player_ref:\n   606→\t\t_player_in_exit_zone = true\n   607→\t\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: player in exit zone\")\n   608→\n   609→func _on_exit_zone_exited(body: Node3D) -> void:\n   610→\tif body == _player_ref:\n   611→\t\t_player_in_exit_zone = false\n   612→\t\tGlobal.log(\"ShipInterior: player left exit zone\")\n   613→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1VSpKin6KMeV4ndj6QFJh","session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"022b3cf2-7736-40a4-b2dc-c00f57a92157"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01ABN9YuPDzAuqfbzxJdJBc2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015n44T3dXBSeKMJYqTgbLid","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\levels\\test_world.gd"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11399,"cache_read_input_tokens":54046,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":11399},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1VSpKin6KMeV4ndj6QFJh","session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"418dfb1c-85de-4ebb-b628-337ebe57f26f"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015n44T3dXBSeKMJYqTgbLid","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## M4 greybox test world: bounded play area with ship interior, deposits, and all gameplay systems.\n     2→class_name TestWorld\n     3→extends Node3D\n     4→\n     5→# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n     6→const WORLD_SIZE: float = 100.0\n     7→const WALL_HEIGHT: float = 8.0\n     8→const DEPOSIT_SPREAD: float = 60.0\n     9→const DEPOSIT_VISUAL_SCALE := Vector3(3.2, 3.2, 3.2)\n    10→const DEPOSIT_COLLISION_RADIUS: float = 1.5\n    11→\n    12→## Ship interior is placed underground to isolate it from the exterior world.\n    13→const INTERIOR_Y_OFFSET: float = -50.0\n    14→\n    15→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    16→var _player: Node3D = null\n    17→var _first_person: CharacterBody3D = null\n    18→var _camera: Camera3D = null\n    19→var _scanner: Scanner = null\n    20→var _mining: Mining = null\n    21→var _hud: GameHUD = null\n    22→var _inventory_screen: InventoryScreen = null\n    23→var _ship_exterior: ShipExterior = null\n    24→var _deposit_container: Node3D = null\n    25→var _ship_interior: Node3D = null\n    26→var _ship_enter_zone: ShipEnterZone = null\n    27→var _player_near_ship_entrance: bool = false\n    28→var _transitioning: bool = false\n    29→var _module_placement_ui: ModulePlacementUI = null\n    30→var _recycler_panel: RecyclerPanel = null\n    31→var _tech_tree_panel: TechTreePanel = null\n    32→var _fabricator_panel: FabricatorPanel = null\n    33→var _automation_hub_panel: AutomationHubPanel = null\n    34→var _navigation_console: NavigationConsole = null\n    35→var _head_lamp_light: SpotLight3D = null\n    36→var _third_person: PlayerThirdPerson = null\n    37→var _player_manager: PlayerManager = null\n    38→var _drone_manager: DroneManager = null\n    39→var _zone_module_ids: Dictionary = {}\n    40→var _biome_content: Node3D = null\n    41→var _travel_manager: TravelSequenceManager = null\n    42→\n    43→# ── Built-in Virtual Methods ──────────────────────────────\n    44→\n    45→func _ready() -> void:\n    46→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: initializing\")\n    47→\t_build_environment()\n    48→\t_build_biome_content()\n    49→\t_build_ship()\n    50→\t_spawn_player()\n    51→\t_setup_gameplay_systems()\n    52→\t_setup_ship_interior()\n    53→\t_setup_hud()\n    54→\t_setup_ship_ui()\n    55→\t_setup_head_lamp()\n    56→\t_setup_drone_manager()\n    57→\t_setup_travel_sequence()\n    58→\tInput.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED)\n    59→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: initialization complete\")\n    60→\n    61→func _process(_delta: float) -> void:\n    62→\t_update_ship_interact()\n    63→\t_update_use_item()\n    64→\t_update_head_lamp_toggle()\n    65→\n    66→func _input(event: InputEvent) -> void:\n    67→\t# Toggle mouse capture with Escape\n    68→\tif event.is_action_pressed(\"pause\"):\n    69→\t\tif Input.get_mouse_mode() == Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED:\n    70→\t\t\tInput.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_VISIBLE)\n    71→\t\telse:\n    72→\t\t\tInput.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED)\n    73→\n    74→# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n    75→\n    76→func _build_environment() -> void:\n    77→\t# Sky and ambient lighting\n    78→\tvar env := WorldEnvironment.new()\n    79→\tvar environment := Environment.new()\n    80→\tenvironment.background_mode = Environment.BG_COLOR\n    81→\tenvironment.background_color = Color(\"#1a1a2e\")\n    82→\tenvironment.ambient_light_source = Environment.AMBIENT_SOURCE_COLOR\n    83→\tenvironment.ambient_light_color = Color(\"#404060\")\n    84→\tenvironment.ambient_light_energy = 0.4\n    85→\tenvironment.tonemap_mode = Environment.TONE_MAPPER_ACES\n    86→\tenv.environment = environment\n    87→\tadd_child(env)\n    88→\n    89→\t# Directional light (sun)\n    90→\tvar sun := DirectionalLight3D.new()\n    91→\tsun.rotation_degrees = Vector3(-45, 30, 0)\n    92→\tsun.light_color = Color(\"#ffe0c0\")\n    93→\tsun.light_energy = 1.2\n    94→\tsun.shadow_enabled = true\n    95→\tadd_child(sun)\n    96→\n    97→func _build_biome_content() -> void:\n    98→\t# Container for biome-specific content (ground, boundaries, deposits).\n    99→\t# TravelSequenceManager swaps this container's children on biome travel.\n   100→\t_biome_content = Node3D.new()\n   101→\t_biome_content.name = \"BiomeContent\"\n   102→\tadd_child(_biome_content)\n   103→\t_build_ground()\n   104→\t_build_boundaries()\n   105→\t_generate_deposits()\n   106→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: biome content built (starter biome)\")\n   107→\n   108→func _build_ground() -> void:\n   109→\tvar ground := StaticBody3D.new()\n   110→\tground.name = \"Ground\"\n   111→\tground.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT\n   112→\tground.collision_mask = 0\n   113→\n   114→\t# Visual mesh\n   115→\tvar mesh_inst := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   116→\tvar plane_mesh := PlaneMesh.new()\n   117→\tplane_mesh.size = Vector2(WORLD_SIZE * 2, WORLD_SIZE * 2)\n   118→\tmesh_inst.mesh = plane_mesh\n   119→\tvar material := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   120→\tmaterial.albedo_color = Color(\"#3a3a4a\")\n   121→\tmaterial.roughness = 0.9\n   122→\tmesh_inst.material_override = material\n   123→\tground.add_child(mesh_inst)\n   124→\n   125→\t# Collision\n   126→\tvar col_shape := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   127→\tvar box_shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   128→\tbox_shape.size = Vector3(WORLD_SIZE * 2, 0.1, WORLD_SIZE * 2)\n   129→\tcol_shape.shape = box_shape\n   130→\tcol_shape.position.y = -0.05\n   131→\tground.add_child(col_shape)\n   132→\n   133→\t_biome_content.add_child(ground)\n   134→\n   135→func _build_boundaries() -> void:\n   136→\tvar boundaries := Node3D.new()\n   137→\tboundaries.name = \"Boundaries\"\n   138→\t_biome_content.add_child(boundaries)\n   139→\n   140→\t# Four invisible walls\n   141→\tvar offsets: Array[Vector3] = [\n   142→\t\tVector3(WORLD_SIZE, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, 0),\n   143→\t\tVector3(-WORLD_SIZE, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, 0),\n   144→\t\tVector3(0, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, WORLD_SIZE),\n   145→\t\tVector3(0, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, -WORLD_SIZE),\n   146→\t]\n   147→\tvar sizes: Array[Vector3] = [\n   148→\t\tVector3(0.5, WALL_HEIGHT, WORLD_SIZE * 2),\n   149→\t\tVector3(0.5, WALL_HEIGHT, WORLD_SIZE * 2),\n   150→\t\tVector3(WORLD_SIZE * 2, WALL_HEIGHT, 0.5),\n   151→\t\tVector3(WORLD_SIZE * 2, WALL_HEIGHT, 0.5),\n   152→\t]\n   153→\n   154→\tfor i: int in range(4):\n   155→\t\tvar wall := StaticBody3D.new()\n   156→\t\twall.name = \"Wall_%d\" % i\n   157→\t\twall.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT\n   158→\t\twall.collision_mask = 0\n   159→\t\twall.position = offsets[i]\n   160→\n   161→\t\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   162→\t\tvar shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   163→\t\tshape.size = sizes[i]\n   164→\t\tcol.shape = shape\n   165→\t\twall.add_child(col)\n   166→\n   167→\t\tboundaries.add_child(wall)\n   168→\n   169→func _build_ship() -> void:\n   170→\tvar ship_scene: PackedScene = load(\"res://scenes/objects/ship_exterior.tscn\") as PackedScene\n   171→\tif not ship_scene:\n   172→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Could not load ship exterior scene!\")\n   173→\t\treturn\n   174→\t_ship_exterior = ship_scene.instantiate() as ShipExterior\n   175→\t_ship_exterior.name = \"Ship\"\n   176→\t_ship_exterior.position = Vector3.ZERO\n   177→\tadd_child(_ship_exterior)\n   178→\n   179→func _spawn_player() -> void:\n   180→\tvar player_scene: PackedScene = load(\"res://player/player.tscn\") as PackedScene\n   181→\tif not player_scene:\n   182→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Could not load player scene!\")\n   183→\t\treturn\n   184→\t_player = player_scene.instantiate()\n   185→\t_player.name = \"Player\"\n   186→\t_player.position = Vector3(0, 0.0, 24)  # Spawn near ship entrance (3× hull), capsule bottom at local Y=0\n   187→\tadd_child(_player)\n   188→\n   189→\t# Get controllers and camera\n   190→\t_first_person = _player.get_node(\"FirstPersonController\") as CharacterBody3D\n   191→\t_third_person = _player.get_node(\"ThirdPersonController\") as PlayerThirdPerson\n   192→\tif _first_person and _first_person.has_method(\"get_camera\"):\n   193→\t\t_camera = _first_person.get_camera()\n   194→\n   195→\t# Connect view mode switching\n   196→\t_player_manager = _player as PlayerManager\n   197→\tif _player_manager:\n   198→\t\t_player_manager.view_mode_changed.connect(_on_view_mode_changed)\n   199→\n   200→\t# Set player collision layer\n   201→\tif _first_person:\n   202→\t\t_first_person.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n   203→\t\t_first_person.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT | PhysicsLayers.INTERACTABLE\n   204→\n   205→func _generate_deposits() -> void:\n   206→\t_deposit_container = Node3D.new()\n   207→\t_deposit_container.name = \"Deposits\"\n   208→\t_biome_content.add_child(_deposit_container)\n   209→\n   210→\tvar deposits: Array[Deposit] = DepositRegistry.generate_m3_deposits(Vector3.ZERO, DEPOSIT_SPREAD)\n   211→\tvar scrap_mesh_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/props/mesh_resource_node_scrap.glb\")\n   212→\n   213→\tfor deposit: Deposit in deposits:\n   214→\t\t# Ensure deposit is on the ground\n   215→\t\tdeposit.position.y = 0.0\n   216→\t\t_deposit_container.add_child(deposit)\n   217→\t\tdeposit.depleted.connect(func() -> void:\n   218→\t\t\tDepositRegistry.unregister(deposit)\n   219→\t\t\tdeposit.queue_free()\n   220→\t\t)\n   221→\n   222→\t\t# Add visual mesh\n   223→\t\tif scrap_mesh_scene and scrap_mesh_scene is PackedScene:\n   224→\t\t\tvar mesh_instance: Node3D = (scrap_mesh_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n   225→\t\t\tmesh_instance.name = \"Mesh\"\n   226→\t\t\tmesh_instance.scale = DEPOSIT_VISUAL_SCALE\n   227→\t\t\tmesh_instance.position.y = 0.9\n   228→\t\t\tdeposit.add_child(mesh_instance)\n   229→\t\telse:\n   230→\t\t\t# Fallback: colored box\n   231→\t\t\tvar fallback := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   232→\t\t\tvar box := BoxMesh.new()\n   233→\t\t\tbox.size = Vector3(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)\n   234→\t\t\tfallback.mesh = box\n   235→\t\t\tvar mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   236→\t\t\tmat.albedo_color = Color(\"#D4AA00\")\n   237→\t\t\tfallback.material_override = mat\n   238→\t\t\tdeposit.add_child(fallback)\n   239→\n   240→\t\t# Add collision body for raycast detection\n   241→\t\tvar body := StaticBody3D.new()\n   242→\t\tbody.name = \"InteractBody\"\n   243→\t\tbody.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.INTERACTABLE\n   244→\t\tbody.collision_mask = 0\n   245→\t\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   246→\t\tvar sphere := SphereShape3D.new()\n   247→\t\tsphere.radius = DEPOSIT_COLLISION_RADIUS\n   248→\t\tcol.shape = sphere\n   249→\t\tcol.position.y = 0.9\n   250→\t\tbody.add_child(col)\n   251→\t\tdeposit.add_child(body)\n   252→\n   253→func _setup_gameplay_systems() -> void:\n   254→\tif not _camera or not _first_person:\n   255→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Camera or player not available for gameplay systems!\")\n   256→\t\treturn\n   257→\n   258→\t# Scanner\n   259→\t_scanner = Scanner.new()\n   260→\t_scanner.name = \"Scanner\"\n   261→\t_scanner.setup(_camera, _first_person)\n   262→\tadd_child(_scanner)\n   263→\n   264→\t# Mining\n   265→\t_mining = Mining.new()\n   266→\t_mining.name = \"Mining\"\n   267→\t_mining.setup(_camera, _first_person, _scanner)\n   268→\tadd_child(_mining)\n   269→\n   270→func _setup_hud() -> void:\n   271→\t# Main HUD (includes all UI panels and HUD elements as instanced subscenes)\n   272→\tvar hud_scene: PackedScene = preload(\"res://scenes/ui/game_hud.tscn\")\n   273→\t_hud = hud_scene.instantiate() as GameHUD\n   274→\t_hud.name = \"HUD\"\n   275→\tadd_child(_hud)\n   276→\tif _camera and _first_person and _scanner and _mining:\n   277→\t\t_hud.setup(_camera, _first_person, _scanner, _mining)\n   278→\n   279→\t# Wire the ship marker on the compass bar so the player can always see the ship bearing\n   280→\tif _ship_exterior:\n   281→\t\t_hud.set_ship_target(_ship_exterior)\n   282→\n   283→\t# Get panel references from the HUD\n   284→\t_inventory_screen = _hud.get_inventory_screen()\n   285→\t_module_placement_ui = _hud.get_module_placement_ui()\n   286→\t_recycler_panel = _hud.get_recycler_panel()\n   287→\t_tech_tree_panel = _hud.get_tech_tree_panel()\n   288→\t_fabricator_panel = _hud.get_fabricator_panel()\n   289→\t_automation_hub_panel = _hud.get_automation_hub_panel()\n   290→\t_navigation_console = _hud.get_navigation_console()\n   291→\n   292→func _setup_ship_interior() -> void:\n   293→\tif not _ship_exterior:\n   294→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: _ship_exterior is null — cannot setup ship interior!\")\n   295→\t\treturn\n   296→\t# Load and instance ship interior scene underground\n   297→\tvar interior_scene: PackedScene = load(\"res://scenes/gameplay/ship_interior.tscn\") as PackedScene\n   298→\tif not interior_scene:\n   299→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Could not load ship interior scene!\")\n   300→\t\treturn\n   301→\t_ship_interior = interior_scene.instantiate()\n   302→\t_ship_interior.name = \"ShipInterior\"\n   303→\t_ship_interior.position = Vector3(0, INTERIOR_Y_OFFSET, 0)\n   304→\tadd_child(_ship_interior)\n   305→\n   306→\t# Position the cockpit viewport camera at the ship exterior front, looking forward\n   307→\tvar viewport_camera_pos := Vector3(0.0, 8.0, -23.0)\n   308→\t_ship_interior.setup_viewport_world(get_viewport().world_3d, viewport_camera_pos)\n   309→\n   310→\tif _first_person:\n   311→\t\t_ship_interior.setup(_first_person)\n   312→\n   313→\t# Set the exterior exit position outside the ship hull (3× hull Z-edge = 21, exit beyond it)\n   314→\t_ship_interior.set_exterior_position(Vector3(0, 0.0, 24))\n   315→\n   316→\t# Connect ship interior signals\n   317→\t_ship_interior.player_entered_ship.connect(_on_player_entered_ship)\n   318→\t_ship_interior.player_exited_ship.connect(_on_player_exited_ship)\n   319→\n   320→\t# Create a boarding zone that wraps the full ship hull so the player can board from any side.\n   321→\t# BoxShape3D is sized slightly larger than the ship's bounding box (~1–2 m clearance all around):\n   322→\t#   ship hull ≈ 26 m wide × 46 m long × 11 m tall (24× scaled mesh, center at Y=6.5).\n   323→\t#   boarding box: 28 m wide × 50 m long × 14 m tall, centered at local (0, 4.5, 0).\n   324→\t# Replaces the former single-point entrance trigger (TICKET-0206).\n   325→\t_ship_enter_zone = ShipEnterZone.new()\n   326→\t_ship_enter_zone.name = \"ShipEnterZone\"\n   327→\t_ship_enter_zone.collision_layer = 0\n   328→\t_ship_enter_zone.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n   329→\tvar enter_col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   330→\tvar enter_shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   331→\tenter_shape.size = Vector3(28.0, 14.0, 50.0)\n   332→\tenter_col.shape = enter_shape\n   333→\tenter_col.position = Vector3(0.0, 4.5, 0.0)\n   334→\t_ship_enter_zone.add_child(enter_col)\n   335→\t# Parent to ship exterior so the zone follows the ship on biome travel automatically.\n   336→\t# enter_col.position is a local offset from the ship center (TICKET-0207).\n   337→\t_ship_exterior.add_child(_ship_enter_zone)\n   338→\n   339→\t_ship_enter_zone.body_entered.connect(_on_ship_enter_zone_entered)\n   340→\t_ship_enter_zone.body_exited.connect(_on_ship_enter_zone_exited)\n   341→\t_ship_enter_zone.add_to_group(\"interaction_prompt_source\")\n   342→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: ship interior ready\")\n   343→\n   344→func _update_ship_interact() -> void:\n   345→\tif _transitioning or not _ship_interior:\n   346→\t\treturn\n   347→\tif _travel_manager and _travel_manager.is_transitioning():\n   348→\t\treturn\n   349→\n   350→\t# Don't process interact while a UI panel is open\n   351→\tif _module_placement_ui and _module_placement_ui.is_open():\n   352→\t\treturn\n   353→\tif _recycler_panel and _recycler_panel.is_open():\n   354→\t\treturn\n   355→\tif _tech_tree_panel and _tech_tree_panel.is_open():\n   356→\t\treturn\n   357→\tif _fabricator_panel and _fabricator_panel.is_open():\n   358→\t\treturn\n   359→\tif _automation_hub_panel and _automation_hub_panel.is_open():\n   360→\t\treturn\n   361→\tif _navigation_console and _navigation_console.is_open():\n   362→\t\treturn\n   363→\tif _inventory_screen and _inventory_screen.is_open():\n   364→\t\treturn\n   365→\n   366→\t# Enter ship from exterior\n   367→\tif _player_near_ship_entrance and not _ship_interior.is_player_inside():\n   368→\t\tif InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"interact\"):\n   369→\t\t\t_begin_enter_ship()\n   370→\t\t\treturn\n   371→\n   372→\t# Exit ship from interior exit zone\n   373→\tif _ship_interior.is_player_inside() and _ship_interior.is_player_in_exit_zone():\n   374→\t\tif InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"interact\"):\n   375→\t\t\t_begin_exit_ship()\n   376→\t\t\treturn\n   377→\n   378→\t# Interact with ship interior objects when inside\n   379→\tif _ship_interior.is_player_inside():\n   380→\t\tif InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"interact\"):\n   381→\t\t\t# Check cockpit navigation console\n   382→\t\t\tif _ship_interior.is_player_near_cockpit_console():\n   383→\t\t\t\tif _navigation_console:\n   384→\t\t\t\t\t_navigation_console.open_panel()\n   385→\t\t\t\treturn\n   386→\t\t\t# Check terminal\n   387→\t\t\tif _ship_interior.is_player_near_terminal():\n   388→\t\t\t\t_tech_tree_panel.open()\n   389→\t\t\t\treturn\n   390→\t\t\t# Check placement zones\n   391→\t\t\tvar zone_index: int = _ship_interior.get_nearby_zone_index()\n   392→\t\t\tif zone_index >= 0:\n   393→\t\t\t\tif _ship_interior.is_zone_occupied(zone_index):\n   394→\t\t\t\t\t_open_module_panel(zone_index)\n   395→\t\t\t\telse:\n   396→\t\t\t\t\t_module_placement_ui.open(zone_index)\n   397→\n   398→func _begin_enter_ship() -> void:\n   399→\t_transitioning = true\n   400→\tawait _ship_interior.enter_ship(_first_person)\n   401→\t_transitioning = false\n   402→\n   403→func _begin_exit_ship() -> void:\n   404→\t_transitioning = true\n   405→\tawait _ship_interior.exit_ship()\n   406→\t_transitioning = false\n   407→\n   408→func _update_use_item() -> void:\n   409→\tif not InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"use_item\"):\n   410→\t\treturn\n   411→\t# Spare Battery cannot be used inside the ship (suit auto-recharges there)\n   412→\tif _ship_interior and _ship_interior.is_player_inside():\n   413→\t\treturn\n   414→\t# Don't use while transitioning\n   415→\tif _transitioning:\n   416→\t\treturn\n   417→\t# Check if suit battery is already full\n   418→\tif SuitBattery.get_charge_percent() >= 1.0:\n   419→\t\tif _hud:\n   420→\t\t\t_hud.show_notification(\"Battery already full\", Color(\"#94A3B8\"))\n   421→\t\treturn\n   422→\t# Attempt to use a Spare Battery from inventory\n   423→\tvar success: bool = SpareBattery.use()\n   424→\tif success:\n   425→\t\tif _hud:\n   426→\t\t\t_hud.show_notification(\"Battery Recharged!\", Color(\"#00D4AA\"))\n   427→\telse:\n   428→\t\tif _hud:\n   429→\t\t\t_hud.show_notification(\"No Spare Batteries\", Color(\"#FF6B5A\"))\n   430→\n   431→func _setup_head_lamp() -> void:\n   432→\tif not _camera:\n   433→\t\treturn\n   434→\t# Create a SpotLight3D parented to the camera for head-lamp illumination\n   435→\t_head_lamp_light = SpotLight3D.new()\n   436→\t_head_lamp_light.name = \"HeadLampLight\"\n   437→\t_head_lamp_light.light_color = Color(\"#FFFBE6\")\n   438→\t_head_lamp_light.light_energy = 3.0\n   439→\t_head_lamp_light.spot_range = 30.0\n   440→\t_head_lamp_light.spot_angle = 35.0\n   441→\t_head_lamp_light.spot_attenuation = 0.8\n   442→\t_head_lamp_light.shadow_enabled = true\n   443→\t_head_lamp_light.visible = false\n   444→\t_camera.add_child(_head_lamp_light)\n   445→\t# Connect to HeadLamp signals\n   446→\tHeadLamp.head_lamp_toggled.connect(_on_head_lamp_toggled)\n   447→\t# Restore visual state if lamp was already equipped and active\n   448→\tif HeadLamp.is_equipped() and HeadLamp.is_active():\n   449→\t\t_head_lamp_light.visible = true\n   450→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: head lamp visual ready\")\n   451→\n   452→func _update_head_lamp_toggle() -> void:\n   453→\tif not InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"toggle_head_lamp\"):\n   454→\t\treturn\n   455→\tHeadLamp.toggle()\n   456→\n   457→func _on_head_lamp_toggled(active: bool) -> void:\n   458→\tif _head_lamp_light:\n   459→\t\t_head_lamp_light.visible = active\n   460→\n   461→func _setup_ship_ui() -> void:\n   462→\t# Panels are instanced in game_hud.tscn; connect signals and configure\n   463→\t_module_placement_ui.module_installed.connect(_on_module_installed)\n   464→\n   465→\t_automation_hub_panel.setup(Vector3.ZERO)  # Ship position for deposit distance calculations\n   466→\t_automation_hub_panel.drone_deployed.connect(_on_drone_deployed)\n   467→\t_automation_hub_panel.drones_recalled.connect(_on_drones_recalled)\n   468→\n   469→\t# Restore any modules already installed (e.g., from autoload state after scene reload)\n   470→\t_restore_installed_modules()\n   471→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: ship UI ready\")\n   472→\n   473→func _restore_installed_modules() -> void:\n   474→\tvar installed_ids: Array[String] = ModuleManager.get_installed_module_ids()\n   475→\tfor module_id: String in installed_ids:\n   476→\t\tvar zone_index: int = _ship_interior.get_first_empty_zone()\n   477→\t\tif zone_index >= 0:\n   478→\t\t\t_zone_module_ids[zone_index] = module_id\n   479→\t\t\t_place_module_visual(module_id, zone_index)\n   480→\n   481→func _on_module_installed(module_id: String, zone_index: int) -> void:\n   482→\t_zone_module_ids[zone_index] = module_id\n   483→\t_place_module_visual(module_id, zone_index)\n   484→\n   485→func _place_module_visual(module_id: String, zone_index: int) -> void:\n   486→\tif module_id == \"recycler\":\n   487→\t\tvar recycler_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/machines/mesh_recycler_module.glb\")\n   488→\t\tif recycler_scene and recycler_scene is PackedScene:\n   489→\t\t\tvar mesh_node: Node3D = (recycler_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n   490→\t\t\tmesh_node.name = \"RecyclerModule\"\n   491→\t\t\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, mesh_node)\n   492→\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed recycler mesh in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n   493→\t\telse:\n   494→\t\t\t_place_module_fallback(\"RecyclerModule\", Vector3(1.8, 1.4, 1.2), zone_index)\n   495→\telif module_id == \"fabricator\":\n   496→\t\tvar fabricator_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/machines/mesh_fabricator_module.glb\")\n   497→\t\tif fabricator_scene and fabricator_scene is PackedScene:\n   498→\t\t\tvar mesh_node: Node3D = (fabricator_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n   499→\t\t\tmesh_node.name = \"FabricatorModule\"\n   500→\t\t\t_add_interaction_area(mesh_node, Vector3(2.0, 1.2, 1.2))\n   501→\t\t\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, mesh_node)\n   502→\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed fabricator mesh in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n   503→\t\telse:\n   504→\t\t\t_place_module_fallback(\"FabricatorModule\", Vector3(2.0, 1.2, 1.2), zone_index)\n   505→\telif module_id == \"automation_hub\":\n   506→\t\tvar hub_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/machines/mesh_automation_hub_module.glb\")\n   507→\t\tif hub_scene and hub_scene is PackedScene:\n   508→\t\t\tvar mesh_node: Node3D = (hub_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n   509→\t\t\tmesh_node.name = \"AutomationHubModule\"\n   510→\t\t\t_add_interaction_area(mesh_node, Vector3(2.2, 1.4, 1.2))\n   511→\t\t\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, mesh_node)\n   512→\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed automation hub mesh in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n   513→\t\telse:\n   514→\t\t\t_place_module_fallback(\"AutomationHubModule\", Vector3(2.2, 1.4, 1.2), zone_index)\n   515→\n   516→func _place_module_fallback(module_name: String, size: Vector3, zone_index: int) -> void:\n   517→\tvar fallback := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   518→\tvar box := BoxMesh.new()\n   519→\tbox.size = size\n   520→\tfallback.mesh = box\n   521→\tvar mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   522→\tmat.albedo_color = Color(\"#666666\")\n   523→\tfallback.material_override = mat\n   524→\tfallback.name = module_name\n   525→\tfallback.position.y = size.y / 2.0\n   526→\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, fallback)\n   527→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed %s fallback mesh in zone %d\" % [module_name, zone_index])\n   528→\n   529→func _open_module_panel(zone_index: int) -> void:\n   530→\tvar module_id: String = _zone_module_ids.get(zone_index, \"\") as String\n   531→\tmatch module_id:\n   532→\t\t\"recycler\":\n   533→\t\t\t_recycler_panel.open()\n   534→\t\t\"fabricator\":\n   535→\t\t\t_fabricator_panel.open()\n   536→\t\t\"automation_hub\":\n   537→\t\t\t_automation_hub_panel.open()\n   538→\t\t_:\n   539→\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: no panel for module '%s' at zone %d\" % [module_id, zone_index])\n   540→\n   541→func _setup_drone_manager() -> void:\n   542→\t_drone_manager = DroneManager.new()\n   543→\t_drone_manager.name = \"DroneManager\"\n   544→\tadd_child(_drone_manager)\n   545→\t_drone_manager.setup(Vector3.ZERO)\n   546→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: drone manager ready\")\n   547→\n   548→func _setup_travel_sequence() -> void:\n   549→\t_travel_manager = TravelSequenceManager.new()\n   550→\t_travel_manager.name = \"TravelSequenceManager\"\n   551→\tadd_child(_travel_manager)\n   552→\t_travel_manager.setup(_player, _ship_exterior, _biome_content)\n   553→\t_travel_manager.travel_sequence_started.connect(_on_travel_sequence_started)\n   554→\t_travel_manager.travel_sequence_completed.connect(_on_travel_sequence_completed)\n   555→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence manager ready\")\n   556→\n   557→func _on_travel_sequence_started(destination_id: String) -> void:\n   558→\t_transitioning = true\n   559→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence started → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n   560→\n   561→func _on_travel_sequence_completed(destination_id: String) -> void:\n   562→\t_transitioning = false\n   563→\t# ShipEnterZone is a child of _ship_exterior, so it follows the ship automatically (TICKET-0207).\n   564→\t# No manual repositioning needed here.\n   565→\t# Update ship interior exterior marker to match new ship position\n   566→\tif _ship_interior and _ship_exterior:\n   567→\t\tvar exit_offset: Vector3 = Vector3(0.0, 0.0, 24.0)\n   568→\t\t_ship_interior.set_exterior_position(_ship_exterior.position + exit_offset)\n   569→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence completed → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n   570→\n   571→func _on_drone_deployed(drone_id: int, program: DroneProgram) -> void:\n   572→\tif _drone_manager:\n   573→\t\t_drone_manager.spawn_drone(drone_id, program)\n   574→\n   575→func _on_drones_recalled() -> void:\n   576→\tif _drone_manager:\n   577→\t\t_drone_manager.recall_all_drones()\n   578→\n   579→func _add_interaction_area(parent: Node3D, size: Vector3) -> void:\n   580→\tvar area := Area3D.new()\n   581→\tarea.name = \"InteractionArea\"\n   582→\tarea.collision_layer = 1 << 3\n   583→\tarea.collision_mask = 1 << 0\n   584→\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   585→\tcol.name = \"InteractionShape\"\n   586→\tvar shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   587→\tshape.size = size + Vector3(0.5, 0.5, 0.5)\n   588→\tcol.shape = shape\n   589→\tcol.position = Vector3(0, size.y / 2.0, 0)\n   590→\tarea.add_child(col)\n   591→\tparent.add_child(area)\n   592→\n   593→func _on_ship_enter_zone_entered(body: Node3D) -> void:\n   594→\tif body == _first_person:\n   595→\t\t_player_near_ship_entrance = true\n   596→\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: player near ship entrance\")\n   597→\n   598→func _on_ship_enter_zone_exited(body: Node3D) -> void:\n   599→\tif body == _first_person:\n   600→\t\t_player_near_ship_entrance = false\n   601→\n   602→func _on_player_entered_ship() -> void:\n   603→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: player entered ship — activating ship HUD\")\n   604→\tif _hud:\n   605→\t\t_hud.show_ship_globals(true)\n   606→\tif _ship_enter_zone:\n   607→\t\t_ship_enter_zone.set_prompt_enabled(false)\n   608→\n   609→func _on_player_exited_ship() -> void:\n   610→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: player exited ship — deactivating ship HUD\")\n   611→\tif _ship_enter_zone:\n   612→\t\t_ship_enter_zone.set_prompt_enabled(true)\n   613→\tif _hud:\n   614→\t\t_hud.show_ship_globals(false)\n   615→\t# Close any open ship UI panels\n   616→\tif _recycler_panel and _recycler_panel.is_open():\n   617→\t\t_recycler_panel.close()\n   618→\tif _module_placement_ui and _module_placement_ui.is_open():\n   619→\t\t_module_placement_ui.close()\n   620→\tif _tech_tree_panel and _tech_tree_panel.is_open():\n   621→\t\t_tech_tree_panel.close()\n   622→\tif _fabricator_panel and _fabricator_panel.is_open():\n   623→\t\t_fabricator_panel.close()\n   624→\tif _automation_hub_panel and _automation_hub_panel.is_open():\n   625→\t\t_automation_hub_panel.close()\n   626→\tif _navigation_console and _navigation_console.is_open():\n   627→\t\t_navigation_console.close_panel()\n   628→\n   629→func _on_view_mode_changed(mode: String) -> void:\n   630→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: view mode changed to %s\" % mode)\n   631→\tvar new_camera: Camera3D = null\n   632→\tif mode == \"third_person\" and _third_person:\n   633→\t\tnew_camera = _third_person.get_camera()\n   634→\telif _first_person and _first_person.has_method(\"get_camera\"):\n   635→\t\tnew_camera = _first_person.get_camera()\n   636→\tif new_camera:\n   637→\t\t_camera = new_camera\n   638→\t\tif _scanner:\n   639→\t\t\t_scanner.set_camera(new_camera)\n   640→\t\t\t_scanner.set_view_mode(mode)\n   641→\t\tif _mining:\n   642→\t\t\t_mining.set_camera(new_camera)\n   643→\t\tif _hud:\n   644→\t\t\tvar prompt_hud: InteractionPromptHUD = _hud.get_interaction_prompt_hud()\n   645→\t\t\tif prompt_hud:\n   646→\t\t\t\tprompt_hud.set_camera(new_camera)\n   647→\tif _hud:\n   648→\t\t_hud.set_crosshair_visible(mode == \"first_person\")\n   649→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1VSpKin6KMeV4ndj6QFJh","session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"f643d254-a89d-41bc-b117-2f052e552123"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01LvrggVe9veugQqutfC6W7S","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012RLdykDTYDdkoAVN4VpC8c","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio && grep -r \"travel_confirmed\" game/scripts --include=\"*.gd\" -n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10577,"cache_read_input_tokens":65445,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10577},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1VSpKin6KMeV4ndj6QFJh","session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"343dc6b2-78de-4a5c-9fbf-fc6f7a9ccbbe"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012RLdykDTYDdkoAVN4VpC8c","type":"tool_result","content":"game/scripts/ui/navigation_console.gd:10:signal travel_confirmed(destination_biome_id: String)\ngame/scripts/ui/navigation_console.gd:697:\ttravel_confirmed.emit(_selected_biome_id)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1VSpKin6KMeV4ndj6QFJh","session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"19ed964f-38a2-4245-bb5c-3f7ffd101031"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1VSpKin6KMeV4ndj6QFJh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary report:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the codebase for files related to biome transition, travel confirmation, and navigation system. Here are the key findings:\n\n### 1. **NavigationSystem** (Core Travel State Machine)\n**File:** `/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247/game/scripts/systems/navigation_system.gd`\n\n- Autoload-level system managing inter-biome jumps\n- **Signals:**\n  - `travel_completed(destination_id: String)` - Fired when arrival is complete\n  - `travel_blocked(destination_id: String)` - Fired when fuel is insufficient\n  - `biome_changed(new_biome_id: String)` - Integration point for resource respawn and travel sequence visuals\n- **Key Methods:**\n  - `initiate_travel(destination_id)` - Starts the travel state machine (IDLE → PREPARING → IN_TRANSIT → ARRIVING → IDLE)\n  - `can_travel_to(destination_id)` - Checks fuel availability\n  - `get_travel_cost(destination_id)` - Calculates fuel cost\n- **Current Biome:** Tracks `current_biome` (default: \"shattered_flats\")\n\n### 2. **TravelSequenceManager** (Transition Orchestration)\n**File:** `/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247/game/scripts/gameplay/travel_sequence_manager.gd`\n\n- Listens to `NavigationSystem.travel_completed` signal\n- **Signals:**\n  - `travel_sequence_started(destination_id)`\n  - `travel_sequence_completed(destination_id)`\n- **Transition Sequence:** Fade to black → Disable input → Swap biome content → Reposition player/ship → Fade in → Re-enable input\n- **Key Methods:**\n  - `execute_biome_swap(destination_id)` - Synchronously unloads old biome, creates new biome node, repositions player and ship at spawn points\n  - `create_biome_node(biome_id)` - Factory for creating biome instances (ShatteredFlatsBiome, RockWarrensBiome, DebrisFieldBiome)\n\n### 3. **NavigationConsole** (UI Modal Panel)\n**File:** `/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247/game/scripts/ui/navigation_console.gd`\n\n- Modal dialog displayed when player interacts with cockpit console\n- **Signal:** `travel_confirmed(destination_biome_id: String)` (line 10)\n- **Open Method:** `open_panel()` (line 136)\n- **Close Method:** `close_panel()` (line 158)\n- **Confirm Button Handler:** `_on_confirm_pressed()` (line 692) - **THIS IS THE CRITICAL METHOD**\n\n### 4. **CockpitConsolePromptArea** (Interaction Trigger)\n**File:** `/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247/game/scripts/gameplay/cockpit_console_prompt_area.gd`\n\n- Area3D-based interaction detection in ship interior\n- Provides contextual HUD prompt when player is near cockpit console\n- **Key Method:** `get_interaction_prompt()` - Returns prompt dictionary with key, label, and hold flag\n\n### 5. **CockpitConsole** (Physical Object)\n**File:** `/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247/game/scripts/objects/cockpit_console.gd`\n\n- Simple StaticBody3D placeholder for the physical console (TICKET-0167)\n- Interaction prompt provided by CockpitConsolePromptArea, not raycast detection\n\n### 6. **ShipInterior** (Ship Layout & Interaction Detection)\n**File:** `/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247/game/scripts/gameplay/ship_interior.gd`\n\n- **Method:** `is_player_near_cockpit_console()` (line 181) - Checks if player overlaps cockpit console area\n- **Built-in Cockpit Console Area:** `_build_cockpit_console_area()` (line 539) - Creates CockpitConsolePromptArea instance\n\n### 7. **TestWorld** (Game Scene Manager)\n**File:** `/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247/game/scripts/levels/test_world.gd`\n\n- **Interaction Handler:** `_update_ship_interact()` (line 344) - Checks if player is near cockpit console and opens NavigationConsole\n- **Line 384:** Calls `_navigation_console.open_panel()` when player presses interact near console\n- **Travel Setup:** `_setup_travel_sequence()` (line 548) - Creates TravelSequenceManager and connects signals\n- **NavigationConsole Reference:** Retrieved from HUD via `_hud.get_navigation_console()` (line 290)\n\n### 8. **BiomeRegistry** (Biome Definitions)\n**File:** `/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247/game/scripts/data/biome_registry.gd`\n\n- **Registered Biomes:** \"shattered_flats\", \"rock_warrens\", \"debris_field\"\n- **Distance Matrix:** Symmetric inter-biome distances (used for fuel cost calculation)\n- **Key Methods:**\n  - `get_biome(id)` - Returns BiomeData\n  - `get_distance(from_id, to_id)` - Returns travel distance\n  - `is_valid_biome(id)` - Validates biome ID\n\n### 9. **BiomeData** (Biome Information Container)\n**File:** `/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247/game/scripts/data/biome_data.gd`\n\n- Immutable container with biome metadata (id, display_name, description, terrain_seed, resource_profile)\n\n### Key Integration Flow\n\n1. Player presses \"interact\" near cockpit console in ship interior\n2. TestWorld._update_ship_interact() detects proximity (via ShipInterior.is_player_near_cockpit_console())\n3. NavigationConsole.open_panel() is called\n4. Player selects destination and presses \"CONFIRM TRAVEL\" button\n5. NavigationConsole._on_confirm_pressed() (line 692):\n   - Emits `travel_confirmed` signal with destination\n   - Calls `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel(destination_biome_id)`\n   - Closes the panel\n6. NavigationSystem runs state machine → emits `travel_completed`\n7. TravelSequenceManager listens to `travel_completed` → executes biome swap with fade transitions\n8. TravelSequenceManager emits `travel_sequence_completed`\n\nAll file paths are absolute and ready for analysis."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5b44b49e476ef710 (