esource_profile)\n\n### Key Integration Flow\n\n1. Player presses \"interact\" near cockpit console in ship interior\n2. TestWorld._update_ship_interact() detects proximity (via ShipInterior.is_player_near_cockpit_console())\n3. NavigationConsole.open_panel() is called\n4. Player selects destination and presses \"CONFIRM TRAVEL\" button\n5. NavigationConsole._on_confirm_pressed() (line 692):\n   - Emits `travel_confirmed` signal with destination\n   - Calls `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel(destination_biome_id)`\n   - Closes the panel\n6. NavigationSystem runs state machine → emits `travel_completed`\n7. TravelSequenceManager listens to `travel_completed` → executes biome swap with fade transitions\n8. TravelSequenceManager emits `travel_sequence_completed`\n\nAll file paths are absolute and ready for analysis."}],"totalDurationMs":55202,"totalTokens":78049,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":221,"cache_read_input_tokens":76022,"output_tokens":1806,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":221,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01B22n5YrYmVHGuWfoELGn8T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full flow. Let me look at the critical code paths:\n\n1. `NavigationConsole._on_confirm_pressed()` (line 692-700) - emits `travel_confirmed`, calls `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()`, closes panel\n2. `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()` - runs the travel state machine\n3. `TravelSequenceManager` - listens to `NavigationSystem.travel_completed` and executes biome swap\n\nThe issue is \"pressing CONFIRM TRAVEL does nothing\". Let me trace through:\n\n- The `_on_confirm_pressed` method at line 692 looks correct - it emits the signal, calls `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel(_selected_biome_id)`, and closes the panel.\n\n\n- Now I need to verify that `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()` is actually executing, check if `TravelSequenceManager` is properly connected to the signals, and confirm that the button press is triggering the callback in the first place. Let me examine the NavigationSystem and TravelSequenceManager implementations along with how TestWorld wires everything together.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16236,"cache_read_input_tokens":34782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16236},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"6e916f8c-c6c7-45b6-b8c9-e6506682b383"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01B22n5YrYmVHGuWfoELGn8T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. I can see `_on_confirm_pressed()` calls `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()` and the `TravelSequenceManager` listens for `travel_completed`. Let me now read the NavigationSystem and TravelSequenceManager to trace the issue."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16236,"cache_read_input_tokens":34782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16236},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"440ca956-84a4-460e-9def-055c634b27c3"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01B22n5YrYmVHGuWfoELGn8T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Rw3DxQZaydwvqE83jwKkBs","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\navigation_system.gd"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16236,"cache_read_input_tokens":34782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16236},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"548f6cca-3922-4979-b62f-3b5c0663e2a0"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Rw3DxQZaydwvqE83jwKkBs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Ship navigation system autoload: manages the biome registry, travel state\n     2→## machine, and fuel cost calculation for inter-biome jumps. Emits\n     3→## travel_completed and biome_changed on arrival, and travel_blocked if the\n     4→## ship lacks the fuel required for the requested jump.\n     5→## Ticket: TICKET-0159\n     6→class_name NavigationSystemType\n     7→extends Node\n     8→\n     9→# ── Signals ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n    10→\n    11→## Emitted when the ship successfully arrives at a new biome.\n    12→## Passes the destination biome ID.\n    13→signal travel_completed(destination_id: String)\n    14→\n    15→## Emitted when travel is attempted but the ship lacks sufficient fuel.\n    16→## Passes the destination biome ID that was requested.\n    17→signal travel_blocked(destination_id: String)\n    18→\n    19→## Emitted on arrival at a new biome. Sole integration point for the resource\n    20→## respawn system (TICKET-0161) and travel sequence visuals (TICKET-0168).\n    21→signal biome_changed(new_biome_id: String)\n    22→\n    23→# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n    24→\n    25→## Travel state machine states for inter-biome jump sequences.\n    26→enum TravelState {\n    27→\tIDLE,       ## No travel in progress. Default/resting state.\n    28→\tPREPARING,  ## Jump initiated: fuel cost computed, pre-flight checks run.\n    29→\tIN_TRANSIT, ## Fuel consumed, ship is in mid-jump.\n    30→\tARRIVING,   ## Ship is decelerating into destination biome.\n    31→}\n    32→\n    33→# ── Public Variables ──────────────────────────────────────\n    34→\n    35→## ID of the biome where the ship currently resides.\n    36→## Read externally; mutated only by initiate_travel() on successful arrival.\n    37→var current_biome: String = \"shattered_flats\"\n    38→\n    39→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    40→\n    41→## Current state of the travel state machine.\n    42→var _state: TravelState = TravelState.IDLE\n    43→\n    44→# ── Built-in Virtual Methods ──────────────────────────────\n    45→\n    46→func _ready() -> void:\n    47→\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: initialized (current_biome=%s)\" % current_biome)\n    48→\n    49→# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n    50→\n    51→## Returns the current travel state machine state.\n    52→func get_state() -> TravelState:\n    53→\treturn _state\n    54→\n    55→\n    56→## Returns the fuel cost (in fuel units) to travel from the current biome to\n    57→## destination_id, using the FuelSystem formula with the current ship weight.\n    58→## Returns 0.0 if the destination is unknown or is the current biome.\n    59→func get_travel_cost(destination_id: String) -> float:\n    60→\tvar distance: float = BiomeRegistry.get_distance(current_biome, destination_id)\n    61→\tif distance < 0.0:\n    62→\t\treturn 0.0\n    63→\tvar ship_weight: float = FuelSystem.calculate_ship_weight()\n    64→\treturn FuelSystem.calculate_cost(distance, ship_weight)\n    65→\n    66→\n    67→## Returns true if the ship currently holds enough fuel to reach destination_id.\n    68→## Returns false for unknown destinations or if already at destination_id.\n    69→func can_travel_to(destination_id: String) -> bool:\n    70→\tvar distance: float = BiomeRegistry.get_distance(current_biome, destination_id)\n    71→\tif distance < 0.0:\n    72→\t\treturn false\n    73→\tvar ship_weight: float = FuelSystem.calculate_ship_weight()\n    74→\treturn FuelSystem.can_travel(distance, ship_weight)\n    75→\n    76→\n    77→## Initiates travel to destination_id and runs the full state machine sequence:\n    78→##   IDLE → PREPARING → IN_TRANSIT → ARRIVING → IDLE\n    79→## Consumes fuel via FuelSystem on departure.\n    80→## Emits travel_blocked and returns early if fuel is insufficient.\n    81→## Emits travel_completed and biome_changed on successful arrival.\n    82→## No-ops silently if already in-transit or destination is invalid/current.\n    83→func initiate_travel(destination_id: String) -> void:\n    84→\tif _state != TravelState.IDLE:\n    85→\t\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: initiate_travel ignored — state is %s\" % \\\n    86→\t\t\tTravelState.keys()[_state])\n    87→\t\treturn\n    88→\tif not BiomeRegistry.is_valid_biome(destination_id):\n    89→\t\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: unknown destination '%s'\" % destination_id)\n    90→\t\treturn\n    91→\tif destination_id == current_biome:\n    92→\t\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: already at '%s' — no travel needed\" % destination_id)\n    93→\t\treturn\n    94→\tif not can_travel_to(destination_id):\n    95→\t\ttravel_blocked.emit(destination_id)\n    96→\t\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: travel to '%s' blocked — insufficient fuel\" % \\\n    97→\t\t\tdestination_id)\n    98→\t\treturn\n    99→\n   100→\t# PREPARING: validate and compute cost\n   101→\t_set_state(TravelState.PREPARING)\n   102→\tvar cost: float = get_travel_cost(destination_id)\n   103→\n   104→\t# IN_TRANSIT: consume fuel and mark ship as travelling\n   105→\tFuelSystem.consume_fuel(cost)\n   106→\t_set_state(TravelState.IN_TRANSIT)\n   107→\n   108→\t# ARRIVING: update current biome, return to IDLE, then fire arrival signals\n   109→\t_set_state(TravelState.ARRIVING)\n   110→\tvar previous_biome: String = current_biome\n   111→\tcurrent_biome = destination_id\n   112→\t_set_state(TravelState.IDLE)\n   113→\n   114→\ttravel_completed.emit(destination_id)\n   115→\tbiome_changed.emit(destination_id)\n   116→\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: arrived at '%s' (from '%s', fuel_cost=%.1f)\" % [\n   117→\t\tdestination_id, previous_biome, cost])\n   118→\n   119→\n   120→## Resets the navigation system to the starting biome (shattered_flats) and\n   121→## the IDLE state. Used for new-game initialization and test teardown.\n   122→func reset() -> void:\n   123→\tcurrent_biome = \"shattered_flats\"\n   124→\t_state = TravelState.IDLE\n   125→\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: reset to shattered_flats (IDLE)\")\n   126→\n   127→# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n   128→\n   129→## Transitions to new_state and logs the change.\n   130→func _set_state(new_state: TravelState) -> void:\n   131→\t_state = new_state\n   132→\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: state → %s\" % TravelState.keys()[new_state])\n   133→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"a0b31c38-fd7f-4e94-8162-c1c11869868f","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\navigation_system.gd","content":"## Ship navigation system autoload: manages the biome registry, travel state\n## machine, and fuel cost calculation for inter-biome jumps. Emits\n## travel_completed and biome_changed on arrival, and travel_blocked if the\n## ship lacks the fuel required for the requested jump.\n## Ticket: TICKET-0159\nclass_name NavigationSystemType\nextends Node\n\n# ── Signals ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Emitted when the ship successfully arrives at a new biome.\n## Passes the destination biome ID.\nsignal travel_completed(destination_id: String)\n\n## Emitted when travel is attempted but the ship lacks sufficient fuel.\n## Passes the destination biome ID that was requested.\nsignal travel_blocked(destination_id: String)\n\n## Emitted on arrival at a new biome. Sole integration point for the resource\n## respawn system (TICKET-0161) and travel sequence visuals (TICKET-0168).\nsignal biome_changed(new_biome_id: String)\n\n# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Travel state machine states for inter-biome jump sequences.\nenum TravelState {\n\tIDLE,       ## No travel in progress. Default/resting state.\n\tPREPARING,  ## Jump initiated: fuel cost computed, pre-flight checks run.\n\tIN_TRANSIT, ## Fuel consumed, ship is in mid-jump.\n\tARRIVING,   ## Ship is decelerating into destination biome.\n}\n\n# ── Public Variables ──────────────────────────────────────\n\n## ID of the biome where the ship currently resides.\n## Read externally; mutated only by initiate_travel() on successful arrival.\nvar current_biome: String = \"shattered_flats\"\n\n# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Current state of the travel state machine.\nvar _state: TravelState = TravelState.IDLE\n\n# ── Built-in Virtual Methods ──────────────────────────────\n\nfunc _ready() -> void:\n\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: initialized (current_biome=%s)\" % current_biome)\n\n# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Returns the current travel state machine state.\nfunc get_state() -> TravelState:\n\treturn _state\n\n\n## Returns the fuel cost (in fuel units) to travel from the current biome to\n## destination_id, using the FuelSystem formula with the current ship weight.\n## Returns 0.0 if the destination is unknown or is the current biome.\nfunc get_travel_cost(destination_id: String) -> float:\n\tvar distance: float = BiomeRegistry.get_distance(current_biome, destination_id)\n\tif distance < 0.0:\n\t\treturn 0.0\n\tvar ship_weight: float = FuelSystem.calculate_ship_weight()\n\treturn FuelSystem.calculate_cost(distance, ship_weight)\n\n\n## Returns true if the ship currently holds enough fuel to reach destination_id.\n## Returns false for unknown destinations or if already at destination_id.\nfunc can_travel_to(destination_id: String) -> bool:\n\tvar distance: float = BiomeRegistry.get_distance(current_biome, destination_id)\n\tif distance < 0.0:\n\t\treturn false\n\tvar ship_weight: float = FuelSystem.calculate_ship_weight()\n\treturn FuelSystem.can_travel(distance, ship_weight)\n\n\n## Initiates travel to destination_id and runs the full state machine sequence:\n##   IDLE → PREPARING → IN_TRANSIT → ARRIVING → IDLE\n## Consumes fuel via FuelSystem on departure.\n## Emits travel_blocked and returns early if fuel is insufficient.\n## Emits travel_completed and biome_changed on successful arrival.\n## No-ops silently if already in-transit or destination is invalid/current.\nfunc initiate_travel(destination_id: String) -> void:\n\tif _state != TravelState.IDLE:\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: initiate_travel ignored — state is %s\" % \\\n\t\t\tTravelState.keys()[_state])\n\t\treturn\n\tif not BiomeRegistry.is_valid_biome(destination_id):\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: unknown destination '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\t\treturn\n\tif destination_id == current_biome:\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: already at '%s' — no travel needed\" % destination_id)\n\t\treturn\n\tif not can_travel_to(destination_id):\n\t\ttravel_blocked.emit(destination_id)\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: travel to '%s' blocked — insufficient fuel\" % \\\n\t\t\tdestination_id)\n\t\treturn\n\n\t# PREPARING: validate and compute cost\n\t_set_state(TravelState.PREPARING)\n\tvar cost: float = get_travel_cost(destination_id)\n\n\t# IN_TRANSIT: consume fuel and mark ship as travelling\n\tFuelSystem.consume_fuel(cost)\n\t_set_state(TravelState.IN_TRANSIT)\n\n\t# ARRIVING: update current biome, return to IDLE, then fire arrival signals\n\t_set_state(TravelState.ARRIVING)\n\tvar previous_biome: String = current_biome\n\tcurrent_biome = destination_id\n\t_set_state(TravelState.IDLE)\n\n\ttravel_completed.emit(destination_id)\n\tbiome_changed.emit(destination_id)\n\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: arrived at '%s' (from '%s', fuel_cost=%.1f)\" % [\n\t\tdestination_id, previous_biome, cost])\n\n\n## Resets the navigation system to the starting biome (shattered_flats) and\n## the IDLE state. Used for new-game initialization and test teardown.\nfunc reset() -> void:\n\tcurrent_biome = \"shattered_flats\"\n\t_state = TravelState.IDLE\n\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: reset to shattered_flats (IDLE)\")\n\n# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Transitions to new_state and logs the change.\nfunc _set_state(new_state: TravelState) -> void:\n\t_state = new_state\n\tGlobal.log(\"NavigationSystem: state → %s\" % TravelState.keys()[new_state])\n","numLines":133,"startLine":1,"totalLines":133}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01B22n5YrYmVHGuWfoELGn8T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RxUiypDgFhHazcKF6kY4T7","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\gameplay\\travel_sequence_manager.gd"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16236,"cache_read_input_tokens":34782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16236},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"93ff697a-fefa-4321-9827-2797817ae0bf"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RxUiypDgFhHazcKF6kY4T7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## TravelSequenceManager - Orchestrates inter-biome travel transitions: fade to black,\n     2→## disable input, unload old biome, load destination biome, reposition player and ship\n     3→## at spawn points, fade back in, re-enable input. Listens to NavigationSystem.travel_completed.\n     4→## Owner: gameplay-programmer\n     5→class_name TravelSequenceManager\n     6→extends Node\n     7→\n     8→\n     9→# ── Signals ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n    10→\n    11→## Emitted when the travel transition sequence begins (fade-out starting).\n    12→signal travel_sequence_started(destination_id: String)\n    13→\n    14→## Emitted when the travel transition sequence finishes (fade-in complete, input restored).\n    15→signal travel_sequence_completed(destination_id: String)\n    16→\n    17→\n    18→# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n    19→\n    20→## Duration of the fade-to-black and fade-from-black transitions in seconds.\n    21→const FADE_DURATION: float = 0.5\n    22→\n    23→\n    24→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    25→\n    26→## Whether a travel transition is currently in progress.\n    27→var _is_transitioning: bool = false\n    28→\n    29→## Reference to the player root node for repositioning on arrival.\n    30→var _player: Node3D = null\n    31→\n    32→## Reference to the ship exterior for repositioning on arrival.\n    33→var _ship_exterior: ShipExterior = null\n    34→\n    35→## Container node whose children are replaced on biome swap.\n    36→var _biome_container: Node3D = null\n    37→\n    38→## The currently active biome scene node inside _biome_container.\n    39→var _current_biome_node: Node3D = null\n    40→\n    41→## CanvasLayer for the full-screen fade overlay.\n    42→var _fade_layer: CanvasLayer = null\n    43→\n    44→## ColorRect used as the fade-to-black overlay.\n    45→var _fade_rect: ColorRect = null\n    46→\n    47→\n    48→# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n    49→\n    50→## Initialises the travel sequence manager with references to the player,\n    51→## ship exterior, and biome container. Connects to NavigationSystem signals.\n    52→func setup(player: Node3D, ship_exterior: ShipExterior, biome_container: Node3D) -> void:\n    53→\t_player = player\n    54→\t_ship_exterior = ship_exterior\n    55→\t_biome_container = biome_container\n    56→\tNavigationSystem.travel_completed.connect(_on_travel_completed)\n    57→\t_build_fade_overlay()\n    58→\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: setup complete\")\n    59→\n    60→\n    61→## Disconnects from NavigationSystem. Call before freeing this node.\n    62→func teardown() -> void:\n    63→\tif NavigationSystem.travel_completed.is_connected(_on_travel_completed):\n    64→\t\tNavigationSystem.travel_completed.disconnect(_on_travel_completed)\n    65→\n    66→\n    67→## Returns true if a travel transition is currently in progress.\n    68→func is_transitioning() -> bool:\n    69→\treturn _is_transitioning\n    70→\n    71→\n    72→## Returns the currently loaded biome scene node, or null if none loaded.\n    73→func get_current_biome_node() -> Node3D:\n    74→\treturn _current_biome_node\n    75→\n    76→\n    77→## Executes the biome swap synchronously: clears the biome container, creates\n    78→## the destination biome node, adds it to the container, and repositions the\n    79→## player and ship at the new biome spawn points. Returns true on success.\n    80→func execute_biome_swap(destination_id: String) -> bool:\n    81→\tvar new_biome: Node3D = create_biome_node(destination_id)\n    82→\tif new_biome == null:\n    83→\t\tpush_error(\"TravelSequenceManager: unknown biome '%s' — swap aborted\" % destination_id)\n    84→\t\treturn false\n    85→\n    86→\t# Clear existing biome content\n    87→\t_clear_biome_container()\n    88→\n    89→\t# Add the new biome to the container\n    90→\tnew_biome.name = \"Biome_%s\" % destination_id\n    91→\t_biome_container.add_child(new_biome)\n    92→\n    93→\t# Some biomes auto-generate in _ready(), others need explicit calls\n    94→\tif new_biome.get_child_count() == 0:\n    95→\t\tif new_biome.has_method(\"generate\"):\n    96→\t\t\tnew_biome.generate()\n    97→\t\telif new_biome.has_method(\"build_scene\"):\n    98→\t\t\tnew_biome.build_scene()\n    99→\n   100→\t_current_biome_node = new_biome\n   101→\n   102→\t# Reposition player and ship at the new biome spawn points\n   103→\t_reposition_at_spawn(new_biome)\n   104→\n   105→\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome swap to '%s' complete\" % destination_id)\n   106→\treturn true\n   107→\n   108→\n   109→## Creates a biome scene node for the given biome ID. Returns null for invalid IDs.\n   110→static func create_biome_node(biome_id: String) -> Node3D:\n   111→\tmatch biome_id:\n   112→\t\t\"shattered_flats\":\n   113→\t\t\treturn ShatteredFlatsBiome.new()\n   114→\t\t\"rock_warrens\":\n   115→\t\t\treturn RockWarrensBiome.new()\n   116→\t\t\"debris_field\":\n   117→\t\t\treturn DebrisFieldBiome.new()\n   118→\treturn null\n   119→\n   120→\n   121→## Returns the player spawn position from a biome node using duck typing.\n   122→## Checks for get_player_spawn_position() and get_player_spawn_point().\n   123→static func get_biome_player_spawn(biome_node: Node3D) -> Vector3:\n   124→\tif biome_node.has_method(\"get_player_spawn_position\"):\n   125→\t\treturn biome_node.call(\"get_player_spawn_position\")\n   126→\tif biome_node.has_method(\"get_player_spawn_point\"):\n   127→\t\treturn biome_node.call(\"get_player_spawn_point\")\n   128→\tpush_warning(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome node has no player spawn method\")\n   129→\treturn Vector3.ZERO\n   130→\n   131→\n   132→## Returns the ship spawn position from a biome node using duck typing.\n   133→## Checks for get_ship_spawn_position() and get_ship_spawn_point().\n   134→static func get_biome_ship_spawn(biome_node: Node3D) -> Vector3:\n   135→\tif biome_node.has_method(\"get_ship_spawn_position\"):\n   136→\t\treturn biome_node.call(\"get_ship_spawn_position\")\n   137→\tif biome_node.has_method(\"get_ship_spawn_point\"):\n   138→\t\treturn biome_node.call(\"get_ship_spawn_point\")\n   139→\tpush_warning(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome node has no ship spawn method\")\n   140→\treturn Vector3.ZERO\n   141→\n   142→\n   143→# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n   144→\n   145→## Handles NavigationSystem.travel_completed — runs the full async travel\n   146→## transition: disable input, fade out, swap biome, fade in, re-enable input.\n   147→func _on_travel_completed(destination_id: String) -> void:\n   148→\tif _is_transitioning:\n   149→\t\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: ignoring travel_completed — already transitioning\")\n   150→\t\treturn\n   151→\n   152→\t_is_transitioning = true\n   153→\ttravel_sequence_started.emit(destination_id)\n   154→\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(false)\n   155→\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: travel sequence started → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n   156→\n   157→\t# Fade to black\n   158→\tawait _fade_out()\n   159→\n   160→\t# Swap biome content\n   161→\tvar success: bool = execute_biome_swap(destination_id)\n   162→\n   163→\tif not success:\n   164→\t\t# Error recovery: fade back in and restore input\n   165→\t\tpush_error(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome swap failed for '%s' — recovering\" % destination_id)\n   166→\t\tawait _fade_in()\n   167→\t\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n   168→\t\t_is_transitioning = false\n   169→\t\treturn\n   170→\n   171→\t# Fade back in\n   172→\tawait _fade_in()\n   173→\n   174→\t# Restore input and mark transition complete\n   175→\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n   176→\t_is_transitioning = false\n   177→\ttravel_sequence_completed.emit(destination_id)\n   178→\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: travel sequence completed → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n   179→\n   180→\n   181→## Builds the full-screen fade overlay (CanvasLayer + ColorRect).\n   182→func _build_fade_overlay() -> void:\n   183→\tif not is_inside_tree():\n   184→\t\treturn\n   185→\n   186→\t_fade_layer = CanvasLayer.new()\n   187→\t_fade_layer.name = \"TravelFadeLayer\"\n   188→\t_fade_layer.layer = 10\n   189→\tadd_child(_fade_layer)\n   190→\n   191→\t_fade_rect = ColorRect.new()\n   192→\t_fade_rect.name = \"TravelFadeRect\"\n   193→\t_fade_rect.color = Color.BLACK\n   194→\t_fade_rect.set_anchors_preset(Control.PRESET_FULL_RECT)\n   195→\t_fade_rect.modulate.a = 0.0\n   196→\t_fade_rect.mouse_filter = Control.MOUSE_FILTER_IGNORE\n   197→\t_fade_layer.add_child(_fade_rect)\n   198→\n   199→\n   200→## Fades the overlay to fully opaque (black screen). No-op if no overlay exists.\n   201→func _fade_out() -> void:\n   202→\tif not _fade_rect or not is_inside_tree():\n   203→\t\treturn\n   204→\tvar tween: Tween = create_tween()\n   205→\ttween.tween_property(_fade_rect, \"modulate:a\", 1.0, FADE_DURATION)\n   206→\tawait tween.finished\n   207→\n   208→\n   209→## Fades the overlay to fully transparent (clear screen). No-op if no overlay exists.\n   210→func _fade_in() -> void:\n   211→\tif not _fade_rect or not is_inside_tree():\n   212→\t\treturn\n   213→\tvar tween: Tween = create_tween()\n   214→\ttween.tween_property(_fade_rect, \"modulate:a\", 0.0, FADE_DURATION)\n   215→\tawait tween.finished\n   216→\n   217→\n   218→## Removes all children from the biome container.\n   219→## Removes biome nodes first, then unregisters deposits from DepositRegistry.\n   220→## queue_free() is deferred, so deposits remain valid for unregistration after\n   221→## the biome is removed from the container.\n   222→func _clear_biome_container() -> void:\n   223→\tif not _biome_container:\n   224→\t\treturn\n   225→\tfor child: Node in _biome_container.get_children():\n   226→\t\t_biome_container.remove_child(child)\n   227→\t\tchild.queue_free()\n   228→\tvar registered: Array[Deposit] = DepositRegistry.get_all()\n   229→\tfor deposit: Deposit in registered:\n   230→\t\tif is_instance_valid(deposit):\n   231→\t\t\tDepositRegistry.unregister(deposit)\n   232→\t_current_biome_node = null\n   233→\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome container cleared\")\n   234→\n   235→\n   236→## Repositions the player and ship exterior at the biome spawn points.\n   237→func _reposition_at_spawn(biome_node: Node3D) -> void:\n   238→\tvar player_spawn: Vector3 = get_biome_player_spawn(biome_node)\n   239→\tvar ship_spawn: Vector3 = get_biome_ship_spawn(biome_node)\n   240→\n   241→\tif _player:\n   242→\t\t_player.position = player_spawn\n   243→\t\t# Reset velocity on the active character controller\n   244→\t\tvar first_person: CharacterBody3D = _player.get_node_or_null(\"FirstPersonController\") as CharacterBody3D\n   245→\t\tif first_person:\n   246→\t\t\tfirst_person.velocity = Vector3.ZERO\n   247→\t\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: player repositioned to %s\" % str(player_spawn))\n   248→\n   249→\tif _ship_exterior:\n   250→\t\t_ship_exterior.position = ship_spawn\n   251→\t\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: ship repositioned to %s\" % str(ship_spawn))\n   252→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"27545432-afd8-49d6-a610-1ce172c6710e","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\gameplay\\travel_sequence_manager.gd","content":"## TravelSequenceManager - Orchestrates inter-biome travel transitions: fade to black,\n## disable input, unload old biome, load destination biome, reposition player and ship\n## at spawn points, fade back in, re-enable input. Listens to NavigationSystem.travel_completed.\n## Owner: gameplay-programmer\nclass_name TravelSequenceManager\nextends Node\n\n\n# ── Signals ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Emitted when the travel transition sequence begins (fade-out starting).\nsignal travel_sequence_started(destination_id: String)\n\n## Emitted when the travel transition sequence finishes (fade-in complete, input restored).\nsignal travel_sequence_completed(destination_id: String)\n\n\n# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Duration of the fade-to-black and fade-from-black transitions in seconds.\nconst FADE_DURATION: float = 0.5\n\n\n# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Whether a travel transition is currently in progress.\nvar _is_transitioning: bool = false\n\n## Reference to the player root node for repositioning on arrival.\nvar _player: Node3D = null\n\n## Reference to the ship exterior for repositioning on arrival.\nvar _ship_exterior: ShipExterior = null\n\n## Container node whose children are replaced on biome swap.\nvar _biome_container: Node3D = null\n\n## The currently active biome scene node inside _biome_container.\nvar _current_biome_node: Node3D = null\n\n## CanvasLayer for the full-screen fade overlay.\nvar _fade_layer: CanvasLayer = null\n\n## ColorRect used as the fade-to-black overlay.\nvar _fade_rect: ColorRect = null\n\n\n# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Initialises the travel sequence manager with references to the player,\n## ship exterior, and biome container. Connects to NavigationSystem signals.\nfunc setup(player: Node3D, ship_exterior: ShipExterior, biome_container: Node3D) -> void:\n\t_player = player\n\t_ship_exterior = ship_exterior\n\t_biome_container = biome_container\n\tNavigationSystem.travel_completed.connect(_on_travel_completed)\n\t_build_fade_overlay()\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: setup complete\")\n\n\n## Disconnects from NavigationSystem. Call before freeing this node.\nfunc teardown() -> void:\n\tif NavigationSystem.travel_completed.is_connected(_on_travel_completed):\n\t\tNavigationSystem.travel_completed.disconnect(_on_travel_completed)\n\n\n## Returns true if a travel transition is currently in progress.\nfunc is_transitioning() -> bool:\n\treturn _is_transitioning\n\n\n## Returns the currently loaded biome scene node, or null if none loaded.\nfunc get_current_biome_node() -> Node3D:\n\treturn _current_biome_node\n\n\n## Executes the biome swap synchronously: clears the biome container, creates\n## the destination biome node, adds it to the container, and repositions the\n## player and ship at the new biome spawn points. Returns true on success.\nfunc execute_biome_swap(destination_id: String) -> bool:\n\tvar new_biome: Node3D = create_biome_node(destination_id)\n\tif new_biome == null:\n\t\tpush_error(\"TravelSequenceManager: unknown biome '%s' — swap aborted\" % destination_id)\n\t\treturn false\n\n\t# Clear existing biome content\n\t_clear_biome_container()\n\n\t# Add the new biome to the container\n\tnew_biome.name = \"Biome_%s\" % destination_id\n\t_biome_container.add_child(new_biome)\n\n\t# Some biomes auto-generate in _ready(), others need explicit calls\n\tif new_biome.get_child_count() == 0:\n\t\tif new_biome.has_method(\"generate\"):\n\t\t\tnew_biome.generate()\n\t\telif new_biome.has_method(\"build_scene\"):\n\t\t\tnew_biome.build_scene()\n\n\t_current_biome_node = new_biome\n\n\t# Reposition player and ship at the new biome spawn points\n\t_reposition_at_spawn(new_biome)\n\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome swap to '%s' complete\" % destination_id)\n\treturn true\n\n\n## Creates a biome scene node for the given biome ID. Returns null for invalid IDs.\nstatic func create_biome_node(biome_id: String) -> Node3D:\n\tmatch biome_id:\n\t\t\"shattered_flats\":\n\t\t\treturn ShatteredFlatsBiome.new()\n\t\t\"rock_warrens\":\n\t\t\treturn RockWarrensBiome.new()\n\t\t\"debris_field\":\n\t\t\treturn DebrisFieldBiome.new()\n\treturn null\n\n\n## Returns the player spawn position from a biome node using duck typing.\n## Checks for get_player_spawn_position() and get_player_spawn_point().\nstatic func get_biome_player_spawn(biome_node: Node3D) -> Vector3:\n\tif biome_node.has_method(\"get_player_spawn_position\"):\n\t\treturn biome_node.call(\"get_player_spawn_position\")\n\tif biome_node.has_method(\"get_player_spawn_point\"):\n\t\treturn biome_node.call(\"get_player_spawn_point\")\n\tpush_warning(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome node has no player spawn method\")\n\treturn Vector3.ZERO\n\n\n## Returns the ship spawn position from a biome node using duck typing.\n## Checks for get_ship_spawn_position() and get_ship_spawn_point().\nstatic func get_biome_ship_spawn(biome_node: Node3D) -> Vector3:\n\tif biome_node.has_method(\"get_ship_spawn_position\"):\n\t\treturn biome_node.call(\"get_ship_spawn_position\")\n\tif biome_node.has_method(\"get_ship_spawn_point\"):\n\t\treturn biome_node.call(\"get_ship_spawn_point\")\n\tpush_warning(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome node has no ship spawn method\")\n\treturn Vector3.ZERO\n\n\n# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Handles NavigationSystem.travel_completed — runs the full async travel\n## transition: disable input, fade out, swap biome, fade in, re-enable input.\nfunc _on_travel_completed(destination_id: String) -> void:\n\tif _is_transitioning:\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: ignoring travel_completed — already transitioning\")\n\t\treturn\n\n\t_is_transitioning = true\n\ttravel_sequence_started.emit(destination_id)\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(false)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: travel sequence started → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\n\t# Fade to black\n\tawait _fade_out()\n\n\t# Swap biome content\n\tvar success: bool = execute_biome_swap(destination_id)\n\n\tif not success:\n\t\t# Error recovery: fade back in and restore input\n\t\tpush_error(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome swap failed for '%s' — recovering\" % destination_id)\n\t\tawait _fade_in()\n\t\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\t\t_is_transitioning = false\n\t\treturn\n\n\t# Fade back in\n\tawait _fade_in()\n\n\t# Restore input and mark transition complete\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\t_is_transitioning = false\n\ttravel_sequence_completed.emit(destination_id)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: travel sequence completed → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\n\n## Builds the full-screen fade overlay (CanvasLayer + ColorRect).\nfunc _build_fade_overlay() -> void:\n\tif not is_inside_tree():\n\t\treturn\n\n\t_fade_layer = CanvasLayer.new()\n\t_fade_layer.name = \"TravelFadeLayer\"\n\t_fade_layer.layer = 10\n\tadd_child(_fade_layer)\n\n\t_fade_rect = ColorRect.new()\n\t_fade_rect.name = \"TravelFadeRect\"\n\t_fade_rect.color = Color.BLACK\n\t_fade_rect.set_anchors_preset(Control.PRESET_FULL_RECT)\n\t_fade_rect.modulate.a = 0.0\n\t_fade_rect.mouse_filter = Control.MOUSE_FILTER_IGNORE\n\t_fade_layer.add_child(_fade_rect)\n\n\n## Fades the overlay to fully opaque (black screen). No-op if no overlay exists.\nfunc _fade_out() -> void:\n\tif not _fade_rect or not is_inside_tree():\n\t\treturn\n\tvar tween: Tween = create_tween()\n\ttween.tween_property(_fade_rect, \"modulate:a\", 1.0, FADE_DURATION)\n\tawait tween.finished\n\n\n## Fades the overlay to fully transparent (clear screen). No-op if no overlay exists.\nfunc _fade_in() -> void:\n\tif not _fade_rect or not is_inside_tree():\n\t\treturn\n\tvar tween: Tween = create_tween()\n\ttween.tween_property(_fade_rect, \"modulate:a\", 0.0, FADE_DURATION)\n\tawait tween.finished\n\n\n## Removes all children from the biome container.\n## Removes biome nodes first, then unregisters deposits from DepositRegistry.\n## queue_free() is deferred, so deposits remain valid for unregistration after\n## the biome is removed from the container.\nfunc _clear_biome_container() -> void:\n\tif not _biome_container:\n\t\treturn\n\tfor child: Node in _biome_container.get_children():\n\t\t_biome_container.remove_child(child)\n\t\tchild.queue_free()\n\tvar registered: Array[Deposit] = DepositRegistry.get_all()\n\tfor deposit: Deposit in registered:\n\t\tif is_instance_valid(deposit):\n\t\t\tDepositRegistry.unregister(deposit)\n\t_current_biome_node = null\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome container cleared\")\n\n\n## Repositions the player and ship exterior at the biome spawn points.\nfunc _reposition_at_spawn(biome_node: Node3D) -> void:\n\tvar player_spawn: Vector3 = get_biome_player_spawn(biome_node)\n\tvar ship_spawn: Vector3 = get_biome_ship_spawn(biome_node)\n\n\tif _player:\n\t\t_player.position = player_spawn\n\t\t# Reset velocity on the active character controller\n\t\tvar first_person: CharacterBody3D = _player.get_node_or_null(\"FirstPersonController\") as CharacterBody3D\n\t\tif first_person:\n\t\t\tfirst_person.velocity = Vector3.ZERO\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: player repositioned to %s\" % str(player_spawn))\n\n\tif _ship_exterior:\n\t\t_ship_exterior.position = ship_spawn\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: ship repositioned to %s\" % str(ship_spawn))\n","numLines":252,"startLine":1,"totalLines":252}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01B22n5YrYmVHGuWfoELGn8T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018pWGFqN5xMQ2z5ZhehanuU","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\levels\\test_world.gd"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16236,"cache_read_input_tokens":34782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16236},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"d18bfd87-da07-499d-aebe-e0a6b35530af"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018pWGFqN5xMQ2z5ZhehanuU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## M4 greybox test world: bounded play area with ship interior, deposits, and all gameplay systems.\n     2→class_name TestWorld\n     3→extends Node3D\n     4→\n     5→# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n     6→const WORLD_SIZE: float = 100.0\n     7→const WALL_HEIGHT: float = 8.0\n     8→const DEPOSIT_SPREAD: float = 60.0\n     9→const DEPOSIT_VISUAL_SCALE := Vector3(3.2, 3.2, 3.2)\n    10→const DEPOSIT_COLLISION_RADIUS: float = 1.5\n    11→\n    12→## Ship interior is placed underground to isolate it from the exterior world.\n    13→const INTERIOR_Y_OFFSET: float = -50.0\n    14→\n    15→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    16→var _player: Node3D = null\n    17→var _first_person: CharacterBody3D = null\n    18→var _camera: Camera3D = null\n    19→var _scanner: Scanner = null\n    20→var _mining: Mining = null\n    21→var _hud: GameHUD = null\n    22→var _inventory_screen: InventoryScreen = null\n    23→var _ship_exterior: ShipExterior = null\n    24→var _deposit_container: Node3D = null\n    25→var _ship_interior: Node3D = null\n    26→var _ship_enter_zone: ShipEnterZone = null\n    27→var _player_near_ship_entrance: bool = false\n    28→var _transitioning: bool = false\n    29→var _module_placement_ui: ModulePlacementUI = null\n    30→var _recycler_panel: RecyclerPanel = null\n    31→var _tech_tree_panel: TechTreePanel = null\n    32→var _fabricator_panel: FabricatorPanel = null\n    33→var _automation_hub_panel: AutomationHubPanel = null\n    34→var _navigation_console: NavigationConsole = null\n    35→var _head_lamp_light: SpotLight3D = null\n    36→var _third_person: PlayerThirdPerson = null\n    37→var _player_manager: PlayerManager = null\n    38→var _drone_manager: DroneManager = null\n    39→var _zone_module_ids: Dictionary = {}\n    40→var _biome_content: Node3D = null\n    41→var _travel_manager: TravelSequenceManager = null\n    42→\n    43→# ── Built-in Virtual Methods ──────────────────────────────\n    44→\n    45→func _ready() -> void:\n    46→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: initializing\")\n    47→\t_build_environment()\n    48→\t_build_biome_content()\n    49→\t_build_ship()\n    50→\t_spawn_player()\n    51→\t_setup_gameplay_systems()\n    52→\t_setup_ship_interior()\n    53→\t_setup_hud()\n    54→\t_setup_ship_ui()\n    55→\t_setup_head_lamp()\n    56→\t_setup_drone_manager()\n    57→\t_setup_travel_sequence()\n    58→\tInput.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED)\n    59→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: initialization complete\")\n    60→\n    61→func _process(_delta: float) -> void:\n    62→\t_update_ship_interact()\n    63→\t_update_use_item()\n    64→\t_update_head_lamp_toggle()\n    65→\n    66→func _input(event: InputEvent) -> void:\n    67→\t# Toggle mouse capture with Escape\n    68→\tif event.is_action_pressed(\"pause\"):\n    69→\t\tif Input.get_mouse_mode() == Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED:\n    70→\t\t\tInput.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_VISIBLE)\n    71→\t\telse:\n    72→\t\t\tInput.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED)\n    73→\n    74→# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n    75→\n    76→func _build_environment() -> void:\n    77→\t# Sky and ambient lighting\n    78→\tvar env := WorldEnvironment.new()\n    79→\tvar environment := Environment.new()\n    80→\tenvironment.background_mode = Environment.BG_COLOR\n    81→\tenvironment.background_color = Color(\"#1a1a2e\")\n    82→\tenvironment.ambient_light_source = Environment.AMBIENT_SOURCE_COLOR\n    83→\tenvironment.ambient_light_color = Color(\"#404060\")\n    84→\tenvironment.ambient_light_energy = 0.4\n    85→\tenvironment.tonemap_mode = Environment.TONE_MAPPER_ACES\n    86→\tenv.environment = environment\n    87→\tadd_child(env)\n    88→\n    89→\t# Directional light (sun)\n    90→\tvar sun := DirectionalLight3D.new()\n    91→\tsun.rotation_degrees = Vector3(-45, 30, 0)\n    92→\tsun.light_color = Color(\"#ffe0c0\")\n    93→\tsun.light_energy = 1.2\n    94→\tsun.shadow_enabled = true\n    95→\tadd_child(sun)\n    96→\n    97→func _build_biome_content() -> void:\n    98→\t# Container for biome-specific content (ground, boundaries, deposits).\n    99→\t# TravelSequenceManager swaps this container's children on biome travel.\n   100→\t_biome_content = Node3D.new()\n   101→\t_biome_content.name = \"BiomeContent\"\n   102→\tadd_child(_biome_content)\n   103→\t_build_ground()\n   104→\t_build_boundaries()\n   105→\t_generate_deposits()\n   106→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: biome content built (starter biome)\")\n   107→\n   108→func _build_ground() -> void:\n   109→\tvar ground := StaticBody3D.new()\n   110→\tground.name = \"Ground\"\n   111→\tground.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT\n   112→\tground.collision_mask = 0\n   113→\n   114→\t# Visual mesh\n   115→\tvar mesh_inst := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   116→\tvar plane_mesh := PlaneMesh.new()\n   117→\tplane_mesh.size = Vector2(WORLD_SIZE * 2, WORLD_SIZE * 2)\n   118→\tmesh_inst.mesh = plane_mesh\n   119→\tvar material := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   120→\tmaterial.albedo_color = Color(\"#3a3a4a\")\n   121→\tmaterial.roughness = 0.9\n   122→\tmesh_inst.material_override = material\n   123→\tground.add_child(mesh_inst)\n   124→\n   125→\t# Collision\n   126→\tvar col_shape := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   127→\tvar box_shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   128→\tbox_shape.size = Vector3(WORLD_SIZE * 2, 0.1, WORLD_SIZE * 2)\n   129→\tcol_shape.shape = box_shape\n   130→\tcol_shape.position.y = -0.05\n   131→\tground.add_child(col_shape)\n   132→\n   133→\t_biome_content.add_child(ground)\n   134→\n   135→func _build_boundaries() -> void:\n   136→\tvar boundaries := Node3D.new()\n   137→\tboundaries.name = \"Boundaries\"\n   138→\t_biome_content.add_child(boundaries)\n   139→\n   140→\t# Four invisible walls\n   141→\tvar offsets: Array[Vector3] = [\n   142→\t\tVector3(WORLD_SIZE, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, 0),\n   143→\t\tVector3(-WORLD_SIZE, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, 0),\n   144→\t\tVector3(0, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, WORLD_SIZE),\n   145→\t\tVector3(0, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, -WORLD_SIZE),\n   146→\t]\n   147→\tvar sizes: Array[Vector3] = [\n   148→\t\tVector3(0.5, WALL_HEIGHT, WORLD_SIZE * 2),\n   149→\t\tVector3(0.5, WALL_HEIGHT, WORLD_SIZE * 2),\n   150→\t\tVector3(WORLD_SIZE * 2, WALL_HEIGHT, 0.5),\n   151→\t\tVector3(WORLD_SIZE * 2, WALL_HEIGHT, 0.5),\n   152→\t]\n   153→\n   154→\tfor i: int in range(4):\n   155→\t\tvar wall := StaticBody3D.new()\n   156→\t\twall.name = \"Wall_%d\" % i\n   157→\t\twall.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT\n   158→\t\twall.collision_mask = 0\n   159→\t\twall.position = offsets[i]\n   160→\n   161→\t\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   162→\t\tvar shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   163→\t\tshape.size = sizes[i]\n   164→\t\tcol.shape = shape\n   165→\t\twall.add_child(col)\n   166→\n   167→\t\tboundaries.add_child(wall)\n   168→\n   169→func _build_ship() -> void:\n   170→\tvar ship_scene: PackedScene = load(\"res://scenes/objects/ship_exterior.tscn\") as PackedScene\n   171→\tif not ship_scene:\n   172→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Could not load ship exterior scene!\")\n   173→\t\treturn\n   174→\t_ship_exterior = ship_scene.instantiate() as ShipExterior\n   175→\t_ship_exterior.name = \"Ship\"\n   176→\t_ship_exterior.position = Vector3.ZERO\n   177→\tadd_child(_ship_exterior)\n   178→\n   179→func _spawn_player() -> void:\n   180→\tvar player_scene: PackedScene = load(\"res://player/player.tscn\") as PackedScene\n   181→\tif not player_scene:\n   182→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Could not load player scene!\")\n   183→\t\treturn\n   184→\t_player = player_scene.instantiate()\n   185→\t_player.name = \"Player\"\n   186→\t_player.position = Vector3(0, 0.0, 24)  # Spawn near ship entrance (3× hull), capsule bottom at local Y=0\n   187→\tadd_child(_player)\n   188→\n   189→\t# Get controllers and camera\n   190→\t_first_person = _player.get_node(\"FirstPersonController\") as CharacterBody3D\n   191→\t_third_person = _player.get_node(\"ThirdPersonController\") as PlayerThirdPerson\n   192→\tif _first_person and _first_person.has_method(\"get_camera\"):\n   193→\t\t_camera = _first_person.get_camera()\n   194→\n   195→\t# Connect view mode switching\n   196→\t_player_manager = _player as PlayerManager\n   197→\tif _player_manager:\n   198→\t\t_player_manager.view_mode_changed.connect(_on_view_mode_changed)\n   199→\n   200→\t# Set player collision layer\n   201→\tif _first_person:\n   202→\t\t_first_person.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n   203→\t\t_first_person.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT | PhysicsLayers.INTERACTABLE\n   204→\n   205→func _generate_deposits() -> void:\n   206→\t_deposit_container = Node3D.new()\n   207→\t_deposit_container.name = \"Deposits\"\n   208→\t_biome_content.add_child(_deposit_container)\n   209→\n   210→\tvar deposits: Array[Deposit] = DepositRegistry.generate_m3_deposits(Vector3.ZERO, DEPOSIT_SPREAD)\n   211→\tvar scrap_mesh_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/props/mesh_resource_node_scrap.glb\")\n   212→\n   213→\tfor deposit: Deposit in deposits:\n   214→\t\t# Ensure deposit is on the ground\n   215→\t\tdeposit.position.y = 0.0\n   216→\t\t_deposit_container.add_child(deposit)\n   217→\t\tdeposit.depleted.connect(func() -> void:\n   218→\t\t\tDepositRegistry.unregister(deposit)\n   219→\t\t\tdeposit.queue_free()\n   220→\t\t)\n   221→\n   222→\t\t# Add visual mesh\n   223→\t\tif scrap_mesh_scene and scrap_mesh_scene is PackedScene:\n   224→\t\t\tvar mesh_instance: Node3D = (scrap_mesh_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n   225→\t\t\tmesh_instance.name = \"Mesh\"\n   226→\t\t\tmesh_instance.scale = DEPOSIT_VISUAL_SCALE\n   227→\t\t\tmesh_instance.position.y = 0.9\n   228→\t\t\tdeposit.add_child(mesh_instance)\n   229→\t\telse:\n   230→\t\t\t# Fallback: colored box\n   231→\t\t\tvar fallback := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   232→\t\t\tvar box := BoxMesh.new()\n   233→\t\t\tbox.size = Vector3(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)\n   234→\t\t\tfallback.mesh = box\n   235→\t\t\tvar mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   236→\t\t\tmat.albedo_color = Color(\"#D4AA00\")\n   237→\t\t\tfallback.material_override = mat\n   238→\t\t\tdeposit.add_child(fallback)\n   239→\n   240→\t\t# Add collision body for raycast detection\n   241→\t\tvar body := StaticBody3D.new()\n   242→\t\tbody.name = \"InteractBody\"\n   243→\t\tbody.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.INTERACTABLE\n   244→\t\tbody.collision_mask = 0\n   245→\t\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   246→\t\tvar sphere := SphereShape3D.new()\n   247→\t\tsphere.radius = DEPOSIT_COLLISION_RADIUS\n   248→\t\tcol.shape = sphere\n   249→\t\tcol.position.y = 0.9\n   250→\t\tbody.add_child(col)\n   251→\t\tdeposit.add_child(body)\n   252→\n   253→func _setup_gameplay_systems() -> void:\n   254→\tif not _camera or not _first_person:\n   255→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Camera or player not available for gameplay systems!\")\n   256→\t\treturn\n   257→\n   258→\t# Scanner\n   259→\t_scanner = Scanner.new()\n   260→\t_scanner.name = \"Scanner\"\n   261→\t_scanner.setup(_camera, _first_person)\n   262→\tadd_child(_scanner)\n   263→\n   264→\t# Mining\n   265→\t_mining = Mining.new()\n   266→\t_mining.name = \"Mining\"\n   267→\t_mining.setup(_camera, _first_person, _scanner)\n   268→\tadd_child(_mining)\n   269→\n   270→func _setup_hud() -> void:\n   271→\t# Main HUD (includes all UI panels and HUD elements as instanced subscenes)\n   272→\tvar hud_scene: PackedScene = preload(\"res://scenes/ui/game_hud.tscn\")\n   273→\t_hud = hud_scene.instantiate() as GameHUD\n   274→\t_hud.name = \"HUD\"\n   275→\tadd_child(_hud)\n   276→\tif _camera and _first_person and _scanner and _mining:\n   277→\t\t_hud.setup(_camera, _first_person, _scanner, _mining)\n   278→\n   279→\t# Wire the ship marker on the compass bar so the player can always see the ship bearing\n   280→\tif _ship_exterior:\n   281→\t\t_hud.set_ship_target(_ship_exterior)\n   282→\n   283→\t# Get panel references from the HUD\n   284→\t_inventory_screen = _hud.get_inventory_screen()\n   285→\t_module_placement_ui = _hud.get_module_placement_ui()\n   286→\t_recycler_panel = _hud.get_recycler_panel()\n   287→\t_tech_tree_panel = _hud.get_tech_tree_panel()\n   288→\t_fabricator_panel = _hud.get_fabricator_panel()\n   289→\t_automation_hub_panel = _hud.get_automation_hub_panel()\n   290→\t_navigation_console = _hud.get_navigation_console()\n   291→\n   292→func _setup_ship_interior() -> void:\n   293→\tif not _ship_exterior:\n   294→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: _ship_exterior is null — cannot setup ship interior!\")\n   295→\t\treturn\n   296→\t# Load and instance ship interior scene underground\n   297→\tvar interior_scene: PackedScene = load(\"res://scenes/gameplay/ship_interior.tscn\") as PackedScene\n   298→\tif not interior_scene:\n   299→\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Could not load ship interior scene!\")\n   300→\t\treturn\n   301→\t_ship_interior = interior_scene.instantiate()\n   302→\t_ship_interior.name = \"ShipInterior\"\n   303→\t_ship_interior.position = Vector3(0, INTERIOR_Y_OFFSET, 0)\n   304→\tadd_child(_ship_interior)\n   305→\n   306→\t# Position the cockpit viewport camera at the ship exterior front, looking forward\n   307→\tvar viewport_camera_pos := Vector3(0.0, 8.0, -23.0)\n   308→\t_ship_interior.setup_viewport_world(get_viewport().world_3d, viewport_camera_pos)\n   309→\n   310→\tif _first_person:\n   311→\t\t_ship_interior.setup(_first_person)\n   312→\n   313→\t# Set the exterior exit position outside the ship hull (3× hull Z-edge = 21, exit beyond it)\n   314→\t_ship_interior.set_exterior_position(Vector3(0, 0.0, 24))\n   315→\n   316→\t# Connect ship interior signals\n   317→\t_ship_interior.player_entered_ship.connect(_on_player_entered_ship)\n   318→\t_ship_interior.player_exited_ship.connect(_on_player_exited_ship)\n   319→\n   320→\t# Create a boarding zone that wraps the full ship hull so the player can board from any side.\n   321→\t# BoxShape3D is sized slightly larger than the ship's bounding box (~1–2 m clearance all around):\n   322→\t#   ship hull ≈ 26 m wide × 46 m long × 11 m tall (24× scaled mesh, center at Y=6.5).\n   323→\t#   boarding box: 28 m wide × 50 m long × 14 m tall, centered at local (0, 4.5, 0).\n   324→\t# Replaces the former single-point entrance trigger (TICKET-0206).\n   325→\t_ship_enter_zone = ShipEnterZone.new()\n   326→\t_ship_enter_zone.name = \"ShipEnterZone\"\n   327→\t_ship_enter_zone.collision_layer = 0\n   328→\t_ship_enter_zone.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n   329→\tvar enter_col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   330→\tvar enter_shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   331→\tenter_shape.size = Vector3(28.0, 14.0, 50.0)\n   332→\tenter_col.shape = enter_shape\n   333→\tenter_col.position = Vector3(0.0, 4.5, 0.0)\n   334→\t_ship_enter_zone.add_child(enter_col)\n   335→\t# Parent to ship exterior so the zone follows the ship on biome travel automatically.\n   336→\t# enter_col.position is a local offset from the ship center (TICKET-0207).\n   337→\t_ship_exterior.add_child(_ship_enter_zone)\n   338→\n   339→\t_ship_enter_zone.body_entered.connect(_on_ship_enter_zone_entered)\n   340→\t_ship_enter_zone.body_exited.connect(_on_ship_enter_zone_exited)\n   341→\t_ship_enter_zone.add_to_group(\"interaction_prompt_source\")\n   342→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: ship interior ready\")\n   343→\n   344→func _update_ship_interact() -> void:\n   345→\tif _transitioning or not _ship_interior:\n   346→\t\treturn\n   347→\tif _travel_manager and _travel_manager.is_transitioning():\n   348→\t\treturn\n   349→\n   350→\t# Don't process interact while a UI panel is open\n   351→\tif _module_placement_ui and _module_placement_ui.is_open():\n   352→\t\treturn\n   353→\tif _recycler_panel and _recycler_panel.is_open():\n   354→\t\treturn\n   355→\tif _tech_tree_panel and _tech_tree_panel.is_open():\n   356→\t\treturn\n   357→\tif _fabricator_panel and _fabricator_panel.is_open():\n   358→\t\treturn\n   359→\tif _automation_hub_panel and _automation_hub_panel.is_open():\n   360→\t\treturn\n   361→\tif _navigation_console and _navigation_console.is_open():\n   362→\t\treturn\n   363→\tif _inventory_screen and _inventory_screen.is_open():\n   364→\t\treturn\n   365→\n   366→\t# Enter ship from exterior\n   367→\tif _player_near_ship_entrance and not _ship_interior.is_player_inside():\n   368→\t\tif InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"interact\"):\n   369→\t\t\t_begin_enter_ship()\n   370→\t\t\treturn\n   371→\n   372→\t# Exit ship from interior exit zone\n   373→\tif _ship_interior.is_player_inside() and _ship_interior.is_player_in_exit_zone():\n   374→\t\tif InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"interact\"):\n   375→\t\t\t_begin_exit_ship()\n   376→\t\t\treturn\n   377→\n   378→\t# Interact with ship interior objects when inside\n   379→\tif _ship_interior.is_player_inside():\n   380→\t\tif InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"interact\"):\n   381→\t\t\t# Check cockpit navigation console\n   382→\t\t\tif _ship_interior.is_player_near_cockpit_console():\n   383→\t\t\t\tif _navigation_console:\n   384→\t\t\t\t\t_navigation_console.open_panel()\n   385→\t\t\t\treturn\n   386→\t\t\t# Check terminal\n   387→\t\t\tif _ship_interior.is_player_near_terminal():\n   388→\t\t\t\t_tech_tree_panel.open()\n   389→\t\t\t\treturn\n   390→\t\t\t# Check placement zones\n   391→\t\t\tvar zone_index: int = _ship_interior.get_nearby_zone_index()\n   392→\t\t\tif zone_index >= 0:\n   393→\t\t\t\tif _ship_interior.is_zone_occupied(zone_index):\n   394→\t\t\t\t\t_open_module_panel(zone_index)\n   395→\t\t\t\telse:\n   396→\t\t\t\t\t_module_placement_ui.open(zone_index)\n   397→\n   398→func _begin_enter_ship() -> void:\n   399→\t_transitioning = true\n   400→\tawait _ship_interior.enter_ship(_first_person)\n   401→\t_transitioning = false\n   402→\n   403→func _begin_exit_ship() -> void:\n   404→\t_transitioning = true\n   405→\tawait _ship_interior.exit_ship()\n   406→\t_transitioning = false\n   407→\n   408→func _update_use_item() -> void:\n   409→\tif not InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"use_item\"):\n   410→\t\treturn\n   411→\t# Spare Battery cannot be used inside the ship (suit auto-recharges there)\n   412→\tif _ship_interior and _ship_interior.is_player_inside():\n   413→\t\treturn\n   414→\t# Don't use while transitioning\n   415→\tif _transitioning:\n   416→\t\treturn\n   417→\t# Check if suit battery is already full\n   418→\tif SuitBattery.get_charge_percent() >= 1.0:\n   419→\t\tif _hud:\n   420→\t\t\t_hud.show_notification(\"Battery already full\", Color(\"#94A3B8\"))\n   421→\t\treturn\n   422→\t# Attempt to use a Spare Battery from inventory\n   423→\tvar success: bool = SpareBattery.use()\n   424→\tif success:\n   425→\t\tif _hud:\n   426→\t\t\t_hud.show_notification(\"Battery Recharged!\", Color(\"#00D4AA\"))\n   427→\telse:\n   428→\t\tif _hud:\n   429→\t\t\t_hud.show_notification(\"No Spare Batteries\", Color(\"#FF6B5A\"))\n   430→\n   431→func _setup_head_lamp() -> void:\n   432→\tif not _camera:\n   433→\t\treturn\n   434→\t# Create a SpotLight3D parented to the camera for head-lamp illumination\n   435→\t_head_lamp_light = SpotLight3D.new()\n   436→\t_head_lamp_light.name = \"HeadLampLight\"\n   437→\t_head_lamp_light.light_color = Color(\"#FFFBE6\")\n   438→\t_head_lamp_light.light_energy = 3.0\n   439→\t_head_lamp_light.spot_range = 30.0\n   440→\t_head_lamp_light.spot_angle = 35.0\n   441→\t_head_lamp_light.spot_attenuation = 0.8\n   442→\t_head_lamp_light.shadow_enabled = true\n   443→\t_head_lamp_light.visible = false\n   444→\t_camera.add_child(_head_lamp_light)\n   445→\t# Connect to HeadLamp signals\n   446→\tHeadLamp.head_lamp_toggled.connect(_on_head_lamp_toggled)\n   447→\t# Restore visual state if lamp was already equipped and active\n   448→\tif HeadLamp.is_equipped() and HeadLamp.is_active():\n   449→\t\t_head_lamp_light.visible = true\n   450→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: head lamp visual ready\")\n   451→\n   452→func _update_head_lamp_toggle() -> void:\n   453→\tif not InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"toggle_head_lamp\"):\n   454→\t\treturn\n   455→\tHeadLamp.toggle()\n   456→\n   457→func _on_head_lamp_toggled(active: bool) -> void:\n   458→\tif _head_lamp_light:\n   459→\t\t_head_lamp_light.visible = active\n   460→\n   461→func _setup_ship_ui() -> void:\n   462→\t# Panels are instanced in game_hud.tscn; connect signals and configure\n   463→\t_module_placement_ui.module_installed.connect(_on_module_installed)\n   464→\n   465→\t_automation_hub_panel.setup(Vector3.ZERO)  # Ship position for deposit distance calculations\n   466→\t_automation_hub_panel.drone_deployed.connect(_on_drone_deployed)\n   467→\t_automation_hub_panel.drones_recalled.connect(_on_drones_recalled)\n   468→\n   469→\t# Restore any modules already installed (e.g., from autoload state after scene reload)\n   470→\t_restore_installed_modules()\n   471→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: ship UI ready\")\n   472→\n   473→func _restore_installed_modules() -> void:\n   474→\tvar installed_ids: Array[String] = ModuleManager.get_installed_module_ids()\n   475→\tfor module_id: String in installed_ids:\n   476→\t\tvar zone_index: int = _ship_interior.get_first_empty_zone()\n   477→\t\tif zone_index >= 0:\n   478→\t\t\t_zone_module_ids[zone_index] = module_id\n   479→\t\t\t_place_module_visual(module_id, zone_index)\n   480→\n   481→func _on_module_installed(module_id: String, zone_index: int) -> void:\n   482→\t_zone_module_ids[zone_index] = module_id\n   483→\t_place_module_visual(module_id, zone_index)\n   484→\n   485→func _place_module_visual(module_id: String, zone_index: int) -> void:\n   486→\tif module_id == \"recycler\":\n   487→\t\tvar recycler_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/machines/mesh_recycler_module.glb\")\n   488→\t\tif recycler_scene and recycler_scene is PackedScene:\n   489→\t\t\tvar mesh_node: Node3D = (recycler_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n   490→\t\t\tmesh_node.name = \"RecyclerModule\"\n   491→\t\t\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, mesh_node)\n   492→\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed recycler mesh in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n   493→\t\telse:\n   494→\t\t\t_place_module_fallback(\"RecyclerModule\", Vector3(1.8, 1.4, 1.2), zone_index)\n   495→\telif module_id == \"fabricator\":\n   496→\t\tvar fabricator_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/machines/mesh_fabricator_module.glb\")\n   497→\t\tif fabricator_scene and fabricator_scene is PackedScene:\n   498→\t\t\tvar mesh_node: Node3D = (fabricator_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n   499→\t\t\tmesh_node.name = \"FabricatorModule\"\n   500→\t\t\t_add_interaction_area(mesh_node, Vector3(2.0, 1.2, 1.2))\n   501→\t\t\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, mesh_node)\n   502→\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed fabricator mesh in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n   503→\t\telse:\n   504→\t\t\t_place_module_fallback(\"FabricatorModule\", Vector3(2.0, 1.2, 1.2), zone_index)\n   505→\telif module_id == \"automation_hub\":\n   506→\t\tvar hub_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/machines/mesh_automation_hub_module.glb\")\n   507→\t\tif hub_scene and hub_scene is PackedScene:\n   508→\t\t\tvar mesh_node: Node3D = (hub_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n   509→\t\t\tmesh_node.name = \"AutomationHubModule\"\n   510→\t\t\t_add_interaction_area(mesh_node, Vector3(2.2, 1.4, 1.2))\n   511→\t\t\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, mesh_node)\n   512→\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed automation hub mesh in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n   513→\t\telse:\n   514→\t\t\t_place_module_fallback(\"AutomationHubModule\", Vector3(2.2, 1.4, 1.2), zone_index)\n   515→\n   516→func _place_module_fallback(module_name: String, size: Vector3, zone_index: int) -> void:\n   517→\tvar fallback := MeshInstance3D.new()\n   518→\tvar box := BoxMesh.new()\n   519→\tbox.size = size\n   520→\tfallback.mesh = box\n   521→\tvar mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n   522→\tmat.albedo_color = Color(\"#666666\")\n   523→\tfallback.material_override = mat\n   524→\tfallback.name = module_name\n   525→\tfallback.position.y = size.y / 2.0\n   526→\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, fallback)\n   527→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed %s fallback mesh in zone %d\" % [module_name, zone_index])\n   528→\n   529→func _open_module_panel(zone_index: int) -> void:\n   530→\tvar module_id: String = _zone_module_ids.get(zone_index, \"\") as String\n   531→\tmatch module_id:\n   532→\t\t\"recycler\":\n   533→\t\t\t_recycler_panel.open()\n   534→\t\t\"fabricator\":\n   535→\t\t\t_fabricator_panel.open()\n   536→\t\t\"automation_hub\":\n   537→\t\t\t_automation_hub_panel.open()\n   538→\t\t_:\n   539→\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: no panel for module '%s' at zone %d\" % [module_id, zone_index])\n   540→\n   541→func _setup_drone_manager() -> void:\n   542→\t_drone_manager = DroneManager.new()\n   543→\t_drone_manager.name = \"DroneManager\"\n   544→\tadd_child(_drone_manager)\n   545→\t_drone_manager.setup(Vector3.ZERO)\n   546→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: drone manager ready\")\n   547→\n   548→func _setup_travel_sequence() -> void:\n   549→\t_travel_manager = TravelSequenceManager.new()\n   550→\t_travel_manager.name = \"TravelSequenceManager\"\n   551→\tadd_child(_travel_manager)\n   552→\t_travel_manager.setup(_player, _ship_exterior, _biome_content)\n   553→\t_travel_manager.travel_sequence_started.connect(_on_travel_sequence_started)\n   554→\t_travel_manager.travel_sequence_completed.connect(_on_travel_sequence_completed)\n   555→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence manager ready\")\n   556→\n   557→func _on_travel_sequence_started(destination_id: String) -> void:\n   558→\t_transitioning = true\n   559→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence started → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n   560→\n   561→func _on_travel_sequence_completed(destination_id: String) -> void:\n   562→\t_transitioning = false\n   563→\t# ShipEnterZone is a child of _ship_exterior, so it follows the ship automatically (TICKET-0207).\n   564→\t# No manual repositioning needed here.\n   565→\t# Update ship interior exterior marker to match new ship position\n   566→\tif _ship_interior and _ship_exterior:\n   567→\t\tvar exit_offset: Vector3 = Vector3(0.0, 0.0, 24.0)\n   568→\t\t_ship_interior.set_exterior_position(_ship_exterior.position + exit_offset)\n   569→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence completed → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n   570→\n   571→func _on_drone_deployed(drone_id: int, program: DroneProgram) -> void:\n   572→\tif _drone_manager:\n   573→\t\t_drone_manager.spawn_drone(drone_id, program)\n   574→\n   575→func _on_drones_recalled() -> void:\n   576→\tif _drone_manager:\n   577→\t\t_drone_manager.recall_all_drones()\n   578→\n   579→func _add_interaction_area(parent: Node3D, size: Vector3) -> void:\n   580→\tvar area := Area3D.new()\n   581→\tarea.name = \"InteractionArea\"\n   582→\tarea.collision_layer = 1 << 3\n   583→\tarea.collision_mask = 1 << 0\n   584→\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n   585→\tcol.name = \"InteractionShape\"\n   586→\tvar shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n   587→\tshape.size = size + Vector3(0.5, 0.5, 0.5)\n   588→\tcol.shape = shape\n   589→\tcol.position = Vector3(0, size.y / 2.0, 0)\n   590→\tarea.add_child(col)\n   591→\tparent.add_child(area)\n   592→\n   593→func _on_ship_enter_zone_entered(body: Node3D) -> void:\n   594→\tif body == _first_person:\n   595→\t\t_player_near_ship_entrance = true\n   596→\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: player near ship entrance\")\n   597→\n   598→func _on_ship_enter_zone_exited(body: Node3D) -> void:\n   599→\tif body == _first_person:\n   600→\t\t_player_near_ship_entrance = false\n   601→\n   602→func _on_player_entered_ship() -> void:\n   603→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: player entered ship — activating ship HUD\")\n   604→\tif _hud:\n   605→\t\t_hud.show_ship_globals(true)\n   606→\tif _ship_enter_zone:\n   607→\t\t_ship_enter_zone.set_prompt_enabled(false)\n   608→\n   609→func _on_player_exited_ship() -> void:\n   610→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: player exited ship — deactivating ship HUD\")\n   611→\tif _ship_enter_zone:\n   612→\t\t_ship_enter_zone.set_prompt_enabled(true)\n   613→\tif _hud:\n   614→\t\t_hud.show_ship_globals(false)\n   615→\t# Close any open ship UI panels\n   616→\tif _recycler_panel and _recycler_panel.is_open():\n   617→\t\t_recycler_panel.close()\n   618→\tif _module_placement_ui and _module_placement_ui.is_open():\n   619→\t\t_module_placement_ui.close()\n   620→\tif _tech_tree_panel and _tech_tree_panel.is_open():\n   621→\t\t_tech_tree_panel.close()\n   622→\tif _fabricator_panel and _fabricator_panel.is_open():\n   623→\t\t_fabricator_panel.close()\n   624→\tif _automation_hub_panel and _automation_hub_panel.is_open():\n   625→\t\t_automation_hub_panel.close()\n   626→\tif _navigation_console and _navigation_console.is_open():\n   627→\t\t_navigation_console.close_panel()\n   628→\n   629→func _on_view_mode_changed(mode: String) -> void:\n   630→\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: view mode changed to %s\" % mode)\n   631→\tvar new_camera: Camera3D = null\n   632→\tif mode == \"third_person\" and _third_person:\n   633→\t\tnew_camera = _third_person.get_camera()\n   634→\telif _first_person and _first_person.has_method(\"get_camera\"):\n   635→\t\tnew_camera = _first_person.get_camera()\n   636→\tif new_camera:\n   637→\t\t_camera = new_camera\n   638→\t\tif _scanner:\n   639→\t\t\t_scanner.set_camera(new_camera)\n   640→\t\t\t_scanner.set_view_mode(mode)\n   641→\t\tif _mining:\n   642→\t\t\t_mining.set_camera(new_camera)\n   643→\t\tif _hud:\n   644→\t\t\tvar prompt_hud: InteractionPromptHUD = _hud.get_interaction_prompt_hud()\n   645→\t\t\tif prompt_hud:\n   646→\t\t\t\tprompt_hud.set_camera(new_camera)\n   647→\tif _hud:\n   648→\t\t_hud.set_crosshair_visible(mode == \"first_person\")\n   649→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"b7d711df-5e4d-4c02-81bb-fe7b428ed915","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\levels\\test_world.gd","content":"## M4 greybox test world: bounded play area with ship interior, deposits, and all gameplay systems.\nclass_name TestWorld\nextends Node3D\n\n# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst WORLD_SIZE: float = 100.0\nconst WALL_HEIGHT: float = 8.0\nconst DEPOSIT_SPREAD: float = 60.0\nconst DEPOSIT_VISUAL_SCALE := Vector3(3.2, 3.2, 3.2)\nconst DEPOSIT_COLLISION_RADIUS: float = 1.5\n\n## Ship interior is placed underground to isolate it from the exterior world.\nconst INTERIOR_Y_OFFSET: float = -50.0\n\n# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\nvar _player: Node3D = null\nvar _first_person: CharacterBody3D = null\nvar _camera: Camera3D = null\nvar _scanner: Scanner = null\nvar _mining: Mining = null\nvar _hud: GameHUD = null\nvar _inventory_screen: InventoryScreen = null\nvar _ship_exterior: ShipExterior = null\nvar _deposit_container: Node3D = null\nvar _ship_interior: Node3D = null\nvar _ship_enter_zone: ShipEnterZone = null\nvar _player_near_ship_entrance: bool = false\nvar _transitioning: bool = false\nvar _module_placement_ui: ModulePlacementUI = null\nvar _recycler_panel: RecyclerPanel = null\nvar _tech_tree_panel: TechTreePanel = null\nvar _fabricator_panel: FabricatorPanel = null\nvar _automation_hub_panel: AutomationHubPanel = null\nvar _navigation_console: NavigationConsole = null\nvar _head_lamp_light: SpotLight3D = null\nvar _third_person: PlayerThirdPerson = null\nvar _player_manager: PlayerManager = null\nvar _drone_manager: DroneManager = null\nvar _zone_module_ids: Dictionary = {}\nvar _biome_content: Node3D = null\nvar _travel_manager: TravelSequenceManager = null\n\n# ── Built-in Virtual Methods ──────────────────────────────\n\nfunc _ready() -> void:\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: initializing\")\n\t_build_environment()\n\t_build_biome_content()\n\t_build_ship()\n\t_spawn_player()\n\t_setup_gameplay_systems()\n\t_setup_ship_interior()\n\t_setup_hud()\n\t_setup_ship_ui()\n\t_setup_head_lamp()\n\t_setup_drone_manager()\n\t_setup_travel_sequence()\n\tInput.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: initialization complete\")\n\nfunc _process(_delta: float) -> void:\n\t_update_ship_interact()\n\t_update_use_item()\n\t_update_head_lamp_toggle()\n\nfunc _input(event: InputEvent) -> void:\n\t# Toggle mouse capture with Escape\n\tif event.is_action_pressed(\"pause\"):\n\t\tif Input.get_mouse_mode() == Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED:\n\t\t\tInput.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_VISIBLE)\n\t\telse:\n\t\t\tInput.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED)\n\n# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunc _build_environment() -> void:\n\t# Sky and ambient lighting\n\tvar env := WorldEnvironment.new()\n\tvar environment := Environment.new()\n\tenvironment.background_mode = Environment.BG_COLOR\n\tenvironment.background_color = Color(\"#1a1a2e\")\n\tenvironment.ambient_light_source = Environment.AMBIENT_SOURCE_COLOR\n\tenvironment.ambient_light_color = Color(\"#404060\")\n\tenvironment.ambient_light_energy = 0.4\n\tenvironment.tonemap_mode = Environment.TONE_MAPPER_ACES\n\tenv.environment = environment\n\tadd_child(env)\n\n\t# Directional light (sun)\n\tvar sun := DirectionalLight3D.new()\n\tsun.rotation_degrees = Vector3(-45, 30, 0)\n\tsun.light_color = Color(\"#ffe0c0\")\n\tsun.light_energy = 1.2\n\tsun.shadow_enabled = true\n\tadd_child(sun)\n\nfunc _build_biome_content() -> void:\n\t# Container for biome-specific content (ground, boundaries, deposits).\n\t# TravelSequenceManager swaps this container's children on biome travel.\n\t_biome_content = Node3D.new()\n\t_biome_content.name = \"BiomeContent\"\n\tadd_child(_biome_content)\n\t_build_ground()\n\t_build_boundaries()\n\t_generate_deposits()\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: biome content built (starter biome)\")\n\nfunc _build_ground() -> void:\n\tvar ground := StaticBody3D.new()\n\tground.name = \"Ground\"\n\tground.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT\n\tground.collision_mask = 0\n\n\t# Visual mesh\n\tvar mesh_inst := MeshInstance3D.new()\n\tvar plane_mesh := PlaneMesh.new()\n\tplane_mesh.size = Vector2(WORLD_SIZE * 2, WORLD_SIZE * 2)\n\tmesh_inst.mesh = plane_mesh\n\tvar material := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n\tmaterial.albedo_color = Color(\"#3a3a4a\")\n\tmaterial.roughness = 0.9\n\tmesh_inst.material_override = material\n\tground.add_child(mesh_inst)\n\n\t# Collision\n\tvar col_shape := CollisionShape3D.new()\n\tvar box_shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n\tbox_shape.size = Vector3(WORLD_SIZE * 2, 0.1, WORLD_SIZE * 2)\n\tcol_shape.shape = box_shape\n\tcol_shape.position.y = -0.05\n\tground.add_child(col_shape)\n\n\t_biome_content.add_child(ground)\n\nfunc _build_boundaries() -> void:\n\tvar boundaries := Node3D.new()\n\tboundaries.name = \"Boundaries\"\n\t_biome_content.add_child(boundaries)\n\n\t# Four invisible walls\n\tvar offsets: Array[Vector3] = [\n\t\tVector3(WORLD_SIZE, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, 0),\n\t\tVector3(-WORLD_SIZE, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, 0),\n\t\tVector3(0, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, WORLD_SIZE),\n\t\tVector3(0, WALL_HEIGHT / 2.0, -WORLD_SIZE),\n\t]\n\tvar sizes: Array[Vector3] = [\n\t\tVector3(0.5, WALL_HEIGHT, WORLD_SIZE * 2),\n\t\tVector3(0.5, WALL_HEIGHT, WORLD_SIZE * 2),\n\t\tVector3(WORLD_SIZE * 2, WALL_HEIGHT, 0.5),\n\t\tVector3(WORLD_SIZE * 2, WALL_HEIGHT, 0.5),\n\t]\n\n\tfor i: int in range(4):\n\t\tvar wall := StaticBody3D.new()\n\t\twall.name = \"Wall_%d\" % i\n\t\twall.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT\n\t\twall.collision_mask = 0\n\t\twall.position = offsets[i]\n\n\t\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n\t\tvar shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n\t\tshape.size = sizes[i]\n\t\tcol.shape = shape\n\t\twall.add_child(col)\n\n\t\tboundaries.add_child(wall)\n\nfunc _build_ship() -> void:\n\tvar ship_scene: PackedScene = load(\"res://scenes/objects/ship_exterior.tscn\") as PackedScene\n\tif not ship_scene:\n\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Could not load ship exterior scene!\")\n\t\treturn\n\t_ship_exterior = ship_scene.instantiate() as ShipExterior\n\t_ship_exterior.name = \"Ship\"\n\t_ship_exterior.position = Vector3.ZERO\n\tadd_child(_ship_exterior)\n\nfunc _spawn_player() -> void:\n\tvar player_scene: PackedScene = load(\"res://player/player.tscn\") as PackedScene\n\tif not player_scene:\n\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Could not load player scene!\")\n\t\treturn\n\t_player = player_scene.instantiate()\n\t_player.name = \"Player\"\n\t_player.position = Vector3(0, 0.0, 24)  # Spawn near ship entrance (3× hull), capsule bottom at local Y=0\n\tadd_child(_player)\n\n\t# Get controllers and camera\n\t_first_person = _player.get_node(\"FirstPersonController\") as CharacterBody3D\n\t_third_person = _player.get_node(\"ThirdPersonController\") as PlayerThirdPerson\n\tif _first_person and _first_person.has_method(\"get_camera\"):\n\t\t_camera = _first_person.get_camera()\n\n\t# Connect view mode switching\n\t_player_manager = _player as PlayerManager\n\tif _player_manager:\n\t\t_player_manager.view_mode_changed.connect(_on_view_mode_changed)\n\n\t# Set player collision layer\n\tif _first_person:\n\t\t_first_person.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n\t\t_first_person.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT | PhysicsLayers.INTERACTABLE\n\nfunc _generate_deposits() -> void:\n\t_deposit_container = Node3D.new()\n\t_deposit_container.name = \"Deposits\"\n\t_biome_content.add_child(_deposit_container)\n\n\tvar deposits: Array[Deposit] = DepositRegistry.generate_m3_deposits(Vector3.ZERO, DEPOSIT_SPREAD)\n\tvar scrap_mesh_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/props/mesh_resource_node_scrap.glb\")\n\n\tfor deposit: Deposit in deposits:\n\t\t# Ensure deposit is on the ground\n\t\tdeposit.position.y = 0.0\n\t\t_deposit_container.add_child(deposit)\n\t\tdeposit.depleted.connect(func() -> void:\n\t\t\tDepositRegistry.unregister(deposit)\n\t\t\tdeposit.queue_free()\n\t\t)\n\n\t\t# Add visual mesh\n\t\tif scrap_mesh_scene and scrap_mesh_scene is PackedScene:\n\t\t\tvar mesh_instance: Node3D = (scrap_mesh_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n\t\t\tmesh_instance.name = \"Mesh\"\n\t\t\tmesh_instance.scale = DEPOSIT_VISUAL_SCALE\n\t\t\tmesh_instance.position.y = 0.9\n\t\t\tdeposit.add_child(mesh_instance)\n\t\telse:\n\t\t\t# Fallback: colored box\n\t\t\tvar fallback := MeshInstance3D.new()\n\t\t\tvar box := BoxMesh.new()\n\t\t\tbox.size = Vector3(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)\n\t\t\tfallback.mesh = box\n\t\t\tvar mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n\t\t\tmat.albedo_color = Color(\"#D4AA00\")\n\t\t\tfallback.material_override = mat\n\t\t\tdeposit.add_child(fallback)\n\n\t\t# Add collision body for raycast detection\n\t\tvar body := StaticBody3D.new()\n\t\tbody.name = \"InteractBody\"\n\t\tbody.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.INTERACTABLE\n\t\tbody.collision_mask = 0\n\t\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n\t\tvar sphere := SphereShape3D.new()\n\t\tsphere.radius = DEPOSIT_COLLISION_RADIUS\n\t\tcol.shape = sphere\n\t\tcol.position.y = 0.9\n\t\tbody.add_child(col)\n\t\tdeposit.add_child(body)\n\nfunc _setup_gameplay_systems() -> void:\n\tif not _camera or not _first_person:\n\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Camera or player not available for gameplay systems!\")\n\t\treturn\n\n\t# Scanner\n\t_scanner = Scanner.new()\n\t_scanner.name = \"Scanner\"\n\t_scanner.setup(_camera, _first_person)\n\tadd_child(_scanner)\n\n\t# Mining\n\t_mining = Mining.new()\n\t_mining.name = \"Mining\"\n\t_mining.setup(_camera, _first_person, _scanner)\n\tadd_child(_mining)\n\nfunc _setup_hud() -> void:\n\t# Main HUD (includes all UI panels and HUD elements as instanced subscenes)\n\tvar hud_scene: PackedScene = preload(\"res://scenes/ui/game_hud.tscn\")\n\t_hud = hud_scene.instantiate() as GameHUD\n\t_hud.name = \"HUD\"\n\tadd_child(_hud)\n\tif _camera and _first_person and _scanner and _mining:\n\t\t_hud.setup(_camera, _first_person, _scanner, _mining)\n\n\t# Wire the ship marker on the compass bar so the player can always see the ship bearing\n\tif _ship_exterior:\n\t\t_hud.set_ship_target(_ship_exterior)\n\n\t# Get panel references from the HUD\n\t_inventory_screen = _hud.get_inventory_screen()\n\t_module_placement_ui = _hud.get_module_placement_ui()\n\t_recycler_panel = _hud.get_recycler_panel()\n\t_tech_tree_panel = _hud.get_tech_tree_panel()\n\t_fabricator_panel = _hud.get_fabricator_panel()\n\t_automation_hub_panel = _hud.get_automation_hub_panel()\n\t_navigation_console = _hud.get_navigation_console()\n\nfunc _setup_ship_interior() -> void:\n\tif not _ship_exterior:\n\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: _ship_exterior is null — cannot setup ship interior!\")\n\t\treturn\n\t# Load and instance ship interior scene underground\n\tvar interior_scene: PackedScene = load(\"res://scenes/gameplay/ship_interior.tscn\") as PackedScene\n\tif not interior_scene:\n\t\tpush_error(\"TestWorld: Could not load ship interior scene!\")\n\t\treturn\n\t_ship_interior = interior_scene.instantiate()\n\t_ship_interior.name = \"ShipInterior\"\n\t_ship_interior.position = Vector3(0, INTERIOR_Y_OFFSET, 0)\n\tadd_child(_ship_interior)\n\n\t# Position the cockpit viewport camera at the ship exterior front, looking forward\n\tvar viewport_camera_pos := Vector3(0.0, 8.0, -23.0)\n\t_ship_interior.setup_viewport_world(get_viewport().world_3d, viewport_camera_pos)\n\n\tif _first_person:\n\t\t_ship_interior.setup(_first_person)\n\n\t# Set the exterior exit position outside the ship hull (3× hull Z-edge = 21, exit beyond it)\n\t_ship_interior.set_exterior_position(Vector3(0, 0.0, 24))\n\n\t# Connect ship interior signals\n\t_ship_interior.player_entered_ship.connect(_on_player_entered_ship)\n\t_ship_interior.player_exited_ship.connect(_on_player_exited_ship)\n\n\t# Create a boarding zone that wraps the full ship hull so the player can board from any side.\n\t# BoxShape3D is sized slightly larger than the ship's bounding box (~1–2 m clearance all around):\n\t#   ship hull ≈ 26 m wide × 46 m long × 11 m tall (24× scaled mesh, center at Y=6.5).\n\t#   boarding box: 28 m wide × 50 m long × 14 m tall, centered at local (0, 4.5, 0).\n\t# Replaces the former single-point entrance trigger (TICKET-0206).\n\t_ship_enter_zone = ShipEnterZone.new()\n\t_ship_enter_zone.name = \"ShipEnterZone\"\n\t_ship_enter_zone.collision_layer = 0\n\t_ship_enter_zone.collision_mask = PhysicsLayers.PLAYER\n\tvar enter_col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n\tvar enter_shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n\tenter_shape.size = Vector3(28.0, 14.0, 50.0)\n\tenter_col.shape = enter_shape\n\tenter_col.position = Vector3(0.0, 4.5, 0.0)\n\t_ship_enter_zone.add_child(enter_col)\n\t# Parent to ship exterior so the zone follows the ship on biome travel automatically.\n\t# enter_col.position is a local offset from the ship center (TICKET-0207).\n\t_ship_exterior.add_child(_ship_enter_zone)\n\n\t_ship_enter_zone.body_entered.connect(_on_ship_enter_zone_entered)\n\t_ship_enter_zone.body_exited.connect(_on_ship_enter_zone_exited)\n\t_ship_enter_zone.add_to_group(\"interaction_prompt_source\")\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: ship interior ready\")\n\nfunc _update_ship_interact() -> void:\n\tif _transitioning or not _ship_interior:\n\t\treturn\n\tif _travel_manager and _travel_manager.is_transitioning():\n\t\treturn\n\n\t# Don't process interact while a UI panel is open\n\tif _module_placement_ui and _module_placement_ui.is_open():\n\t\treturn\n\tif _recycler_panel and _recycler_panel.is_open():\n\t\treturn\n\tif _tech_tree_panel and _tech_tree_panel.is_open():\n\t\treturn\n\tif _fabricator_panel and _fabricator_panel.is_open():\n\t\treturn\n\tif _automation_hub_panel and _automation_hub_panel.is_open():\n\t\treturn\n\tif _navigation_console and _navigation_console.is_open():\n\t\treturn\n\tif _inventory_screen and _inventory_screen.is_open():\n\t\treturn\n\n\t# Enter ship from exterior\n\tif _player_near_ship_entrance and not _ship_interior.is_player_inside():\n\t\tif InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"interact\"):\n\t\t\t_begin_enter_ship()\n\t\t\treturn\n\n\t# Exit ship from interior exit zone\n\tif _ship_interior.is_player_inside() and _ship_interior.is_player_in_exit_zone():\n\t\tif InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"interact\"):\n\t\t\t_begin_exit_ship()\n\t\t\treturn\n\n\t# Interact with ship interior objects when inside\n\tif _ship_interior.is_player_inside():\n\t\tif InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"interact\"):\n\t\t\t# Check cockpit navigation console\n\t\t\tif _ship_interior.is_player_near_cockpit_console():\n\t\t\t\tif _navigation_console:\n\t\t\t\t\t_navigation_console.open_panel()\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t# Check terminal\n\t\t\tif _ship_interior.is_player_near_terminal():\n\t\t\t\t_tech_tree_panel.open()\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t# Check placement zones\n\t\t\tvar zone_index: int = _ship_interior.get_nearby_zone_index()\n\t\t\tif zone_index >= 0:\n\t\t\t\tif _ship_interior.is_zone_occupied(zone_index):\n\t\t\t\t\t_open_module_panel(zone_index)\n\t\t\t\telse:\n\t\t\t\t\t_module_placement_ui.open(zone_index)\n\nfunc _begin_enter_ship() -> void:\n\t_transitioning = true\n\tawait _ship_interior.enter_ship(_first_person)\n\t_transitioning = false\n\nfunc _begin_exit_ship() -> void:\n\t_transitioning = true\n\tawait _ship_interior.exit_ship()\n\t_transitioning = false\n\nfunc _update_use_item() -> void:\n\tif not InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"use_item\"):\n\t\treturn\n\t# Spare Battery cannot be used inside the ship (suit auto-recharges there)\n\tif _ship_interior and _ship_interior.is_player_inside():\n\t\treturn\n\t# Don't use while transitioning\n\tif _transitioning:\n\t\treturn\n\t# Check if suit battery is already full\n\tif SuitBattery.get_charge_percent() >= 1.0:\n\t\tif _hud:\n\t\t\t_hud.show_notification(\"Battery already full\", Color(\"#94A3B8\"))\n\t\treturn\n\t# Attempt to use a Spare Battery from inventory\n\tvar success: bool = SpareBattery.use()\n\tif success:\n\t\tif _hud:\n\t\t\t_hud.show_notification(\"Battery Recharged!\", Color(\"#00D4AA\"))\n\telse:\n\t\tif _hud:\n\t\t\t_hud.show_notification(\"No Spare Batteries\", Color(\"#FF6B5A\"))\n\nfunc _setup_head_lamp() -> void:\n\tif not _camera:\n\t\treturn\n\t# Create a SpotLight3D parented to the camera for head-lamp illumination\n\t_head_lamp_light = SpotLight3D.new()\n\t_head_lamp_light.name = \"HeadLampLight\"\n\t_head_lamp_light.light_color = Color(\"#FFFBE6\")\n\t_head_lamp_light.light_energy = 3.0\n\t_head_lamp_light.spot_range = 30.0\n\t_head_lamp_light.spot_angle = 35.0\n\t_head_lamp_light.spot_attenuation = 0.8\n\t_head_lamp_light.shadow_enabled = true\n\t_head_lamp_light.visible = false\n\t_camera.add_child(_head_lamp_light)\n\t# Connect to HeadLamp signals\n\tHeadLamp.head_lamp_toggled.connect(_on_head_lamp_toggled)\n\t# Restore visual state if lamp was already equipped and active\n\tif HeadLamp.is_equipped() and HeadLamp.is_active():\n\t\t_head_lamp_light.visible = true\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: head lamp visual ready\")\n\nfunc _update_head_lamp_toggle() -> void:\n\tif not InputManager.is_action_just_pressed(\"toggle_head_lamp\"):\n\t\treturn\n\tHeadLamp.toggle()\n\nfunc _on_head_lamp_toggled(active: bool) -> void:\n\tif _head_lamp_light:\n\t\t_head_lamp_light.visible = active\n\nfunc _setup_ship_ui() -> void:\n\t# Panels are instanced in game_hud.tscn; connect signals and configure\n\t_module_placement_ui.module_installed.connect(_on_module_installed)\n\n\t_automation_hub_panel.setup(Vector3.ZERO)  # Ship position for deposit distance calculations\n\t_automation_hub_panel.drone_deployed.connect(_on_drone_deployed)\n\t_automation_hub_panel.drones_recalled.connect(_on_drones_recalled)\n\n\t# Restore any modules already installed (e.g., from autoload state after scene reload)\n\t_restore_installed_modules()\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: ship UI ready\")\n\nfunc _restore_installed_modules() -> void:\n\tvar installed_ids: Array[String] = ModuleManager.get_installed_module_ids()\n\tfor module_id: String in installed_ids:\n\t\tvar zone_index: int = _ship_interior.get_first_empty_zone()\n\t\tif zone_index >= 0:\n\t\t\t_zone_module_ids[zone_index] = module_id\n\t\t\t_place_module_visual(module_id, zone_index)\n\nfunc _on_module_installed(module_id: String, zone_index: int) -> void:\n\t_zone_module_ids[zone_index] = module_id\n\t_place_module_visual(module_id, zone_index)\n\nfunc _place_module_visual(module_id: String, zone_index: int) -> void:\n\tif module_id == \"recycler\":\n\t\tvar recycler_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/machines/mesh_recycler_module.glb\")\n\t\tif recycler_scene and recycler_scene is PackedScene:\n\t\t\tvar mesh_node: Node3D = (recycler_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n\t\t\tmesh_node.name = \"RecyclerModule\"\n\t\t\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, mesh_node)\n\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed recycler mesh in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n\t\telse:\n\t\t\t_place_module_fallback(\"RecyclerModule\", Vector3(1.8, 1.4, 1.2), zone_index)\n\telif module_id == \"fabricator\":\n\t\tvar fabricator_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/machines/mesh_fabricator_module.glb\")\n\t\tif fabricator_scene and fabricator_scene is PackedScene:\n\t\t\tvar mesh_node: Node3D = (fabricator_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n\t\t\tmesh_node.name = \"FabricatorModule\"\n\t\t\t_add_interaction_area(mesh_node, Vector3(2.0, 1.2, 1.2))\n\t\t\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, mesh_node)\n\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed fabricator mesh in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n\t\telse:\n\t\t\t_place_module_fallback(\"FabricatorModule\", Vector3(2.0, 1.2, 1.2), zone_index)\n\telif module_id == \"automation_hub\":\n\t\tvar hub_scene: Resource = load(\"res://assets/meshes/machines/mesh_automation_hub_module.glb\")\n\t\tif hub_scene and hub_scene is PackedScene:\n\t\t\tvar mesh_node: Node3D = (hub_scene as PackedScene).instantiate()\n\t\t\tmesh_node.name = \"AutomationHubModule\"\n\t\t\t_add_interaction_area(mesh_node, Vector3(2.2, 1.4, 1.2))\n\t\t\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, mesh_node)\n\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed automation hub mesh in zone %d\" % zone_index)\n\t\telse:\n\t\t\t_place_module_fallback(\"AutomationHubModule\", Vector3(2.2, 1.4, 1.2), zone_index)\n\nfunc _place_module_fallback(module_name: String, size: Vector3, zone_index: int) -> void:\n\tvar fallback := MeshInstance3D.new()\n\tvar box := BoxMesh.new()\n\tbox.size = size\n\tfallback.mesh = box\n\tvar mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()\n\tmat.albedo_color = Color(\"#666666\")\n\tfallback.material_override = mat\n\tfallback.name = module_name\n\tfallback.position.y = size.y / 2.0\n\t_ship_interior.place_module_in_zone(zone_index, fallback)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: placed %s fallback mesh in zone %d\" % [module_name, zone_index])\n\nfunc _open_module_panel(zone_index: int) -> void:\n\tvar module_id: String = _zone_module_ids.get(zone_index, \"\") as String\n\tmatch module_id:\n\t\t\"recycler\":\n\t\t\t_recycler_panel.open()\n\t\t\"fabricator\":\n\t\t\t_fabricator_panel.open()\n\t\t\"automation_hub\":\n\t\t\t_automation_hub_panel.open()\n\t\t_:\n\t\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: no panel for module '%s' at zone %d\" % [module_id, zone_index])\n\nfunc _setup_drone_manager() -> void:\n\t_drone_manager = DroneManager.new()\n\t_drone_manager.name = \"DroneManager\"\n\tadd_child(_drone_manager)\n\t_drone_manager.setup(Vector3.ZERO)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: drone manager ready\")\n\nfunc _setup_travel_sequence() -> void:\n\t_travel_manager = TravelSequenceManager.new()\n\t_travel_manager.name = \"TravelSequenceManager\"\n\tadd_child(_travel_manager)\n\t_travel_manager.setup(_player, _ship_exterior, _biome_content)\n\t_travel_manager.travel_sequence_started.connect(_on_travel_sequence_started)\n\t_travel_manager.travel_sequence_completed.connect(_on_travel_sequence_completed)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence manager ready\")\n\nfunc _on_travel_sequence_started(destination_id: String) -> void:\n\t_transitioning = true\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence started → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\nfunc _on_travel_sequence_completed(destination_id: String) -> void:\n\t_transitioning = false\n\t# ShipEnterZone is a child of _ship_exterior, so it follows the ship automatically (TICKET-0207).\n\t# No manual repositioning needed here.\n\t# Update ship interior exterior marker to match new ship position\n\tif _ship_interior and _ship_exterior:\n\t\tvar exit_offset: Vector3 = Vector3(0.0, 0.0, 24.0)\n\t\t_ship_interior.set_exterior_position(_ship_exterior.position + exit_offset)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence completed → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\nfunc _on_drone_deployed(drone_id: int, program: DroneProgram) -> void:\n\tif _drone_manager:\n\t\t_drone_manager.spawn_drone(drone_id, program)\n\nfunc _on_drones_recalled() -> void:\n\tif _drone_manager:\n\t\t_drone_manager.recall_all_drones()\n\nfunc _add_interaction_area(parent: Node3D, size: Vector3) -> void:\n\tvar area := Area3D.new()\n\tarea.name = \"InteractionArea\"\n\tarea.collision_layer = 1 << 3\n\tarea.collision_mask = 1 << 0\n\tvar col := CollisionShape3D.new()\n\tcol.name = \"InteractionShape\"\n\tvar shape := BoxShape3D.new()\n\tshape.size = size + Vector3(0.5, 0.5, 0.5)\n\tcol.shape = shape\n\tcol.position = Vector3(0, size.y / 2.0, 0)\n\tarea.add_child(col)\n\tparent.add_child(area)\n\nfunc _on_ship_enter_zone_entered(body: Node3D) -> void:\n\tif body == _first_person:\n\t\t_player_near_ship_entrance = true\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: player near ship entrance\")\n\nfunc _on_ship_enter_zone_exited(body: Node3D) -> void:\n\tif body == _first_person:\n\t\t_player_near_ship_entrance = false\n\nfunc _on_player_entered_ship() -> void:\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: player entered ship — activating ship HUD\")\n\tif _hud:\n\t\t_hud.show_ship_globals(true)\n\tif _ship_enter_zone:\n\t\t_ship_enter_zone.set_prompt_enabled(false)\n\nfunc _on_player_exited_ship() -> void:\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: player exited ship — deactivating ship HUD\")\n\tif _ship_enter_zone:\n\t\t_ship_enter_zone.set_prompt_enabled(true)\n\tif _hud:\n\t\t_hud.show_ship_globals(false)\n\t# Close any open ship UI panels\n\tif _recycler_panel and _recycler_panel.is_open():\n\t\t_recycler_panel.close()\n\tif _module_placement_ui and _module_placement_ui.is_open():\n\t\t_module_placement_ui.close()\n\tif _tech_tree_panel and _tech_tree_panel.is_open():\n\t\t_tech_tree_panel.close()\n\tif _fabricator_panel and _fabricator_panel.is_open():\n\t\t_fabricator_panel.close()\n\tif _automation_hub_panel and _automation_hub_panel.is_open():\n\t\t_automation_hub_panel.close()\n\tif _navigation_console and _navigation_console.is_open():\n\t\t_navigation_console.close_panel()\n\nfunc _on_view_mode_changed(mode: String) -> void:\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: view mode changed to %s\" % mode)\n\tvar new_camera: Camera3D = null\n\tif mode == \"third_person\" and _third_person:\n\t\tnew_camera = _third_person.get_camera()\n\telif _first_person and _first_person.has_method(\"get_camera\"):\n\t\tnew_camera = _first_person.get_camera()\n\tif new_camera:\n\t\t_camera = new_camera\n\t\tif _scanner:\n\t\t\t_scanner.set_camera(new_camera)\n\t\t\t_scanner.set_view_mode(mode)\n\t\tif _mining:\n\t\t\t_mining.set_camera(new_camera)\n\t\tif _hud:\n\t\t\tvar prompt_hud: InteractionPromptHUD = _hud.get_interaction_prompt_hud()\n\t\t\tif prompt_hud:\n\t\t\t\tprompt_hud.set_camera(new_camera)\n\tif _hud:\n\t\t_hud.set_crosshair_visible(mode == \"first_person\")\n","numLines":649,"startLine":1,"totalLines":649}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018VhcEvexMc8zFQawxWjkCp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full flow. Let me trace the issue:\n\n1. `NavigationConsole._on_confirm_pressed()` (line 692-700):\n   - Checks `_selected_biome_id` is not empty\n   - Checks `NavigationSystem.can_travel_to(_selected_biome_id)` returns true\n   - Emits