8→\n     9→# ── Signals ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n    10→\n    11→signal generation_completed\n    12→\n    13→\n    14→# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n    15→\n    16→## Fixed seed for deterministic terrain generation (from BiomeRegistry).\n    17→const BIOME_SEED: int = 2047\n    18→\n    19→## Terrain extent in metres.\n    20→const TERRAIN_SIZE: float = 500.0\n    21→\n    22→## Ship/player spawn clearing radius in metres.\n    23→const SHIP_CLEARING_RADIUS: float = 20.0\n    24→\n    25→## Walkable clearance radius around resource positions in metres.\n    26→const RESOURCE_CLEARANCE_RADIUS: float = 3.0\n    27→\n    28→## Maximum terrain slope for resource placement (degrees).\n    29→const RESOURCE_SLOPE_MAX: float = 30.0\n    30→\n    31→## Minimum spacing between resource positions (metres).\n    32→const RESOURCE_SPACING: float = 15.0\n    33→\n    34→## Scrap Metal surface deposit count range per acceptance criteria.\n    35→const SCRAP_METAL_SURFACE_MIN: int = 5\n    36→const SCRAP_METAL_SURFACE_MAX: int = 8\n    37→\n    38→## Cryonite surface deposit count range per acceptance criteria.\n    39→const CRYONITE_SURFACE_MIN: int = 4\n    40→const CRYONITE_SURFACE_MAX: int = 7\n    41→\n    42→## Number of deep nodes per resource type.\n    43→const DEEP_NODES_PER_TYPE: int = 1\n    44→\n    45→## Deep node quantity — high value; infinite flag means it never depletes.\n    46→const DEEP_NODE_QUANTITY: int = 100\n    47→\n    48→## Surface deposit quantity range.\n    49→const SURFACE_NODE_MIN_QUANTITY: int = 15\n    50→const SURFACE_NODE_MAX_QUANTITY: int = 40\n    51→\n    52→## Deep node yield rate multiplier (10% of surface speed).\n    53→const DEEP_NODE_YIELD_RATE: float = 0.1\n    54→\n    55→## Rock formation grid spacing — metres between formation placement checks.\n    56→const FORMATION_GRID_SPACING: float = 12.0\n    57→\n    58→## Exclusion radius around spawn and resource positions — no formations placed here.\n    59→const FORMATION_EXCLUSION_RADIUS: float = 6.0\n    60→\n    61→## Rock formation height range (metres).\n    62→const MIN_FORMATION_HEIGHT: float = 6.0\n    63→const MAX_FORMATION_HEIGHT: float = 18.0\n    64→\n    65→## Rock formation width range (metres).\n    66→const MIN_FORMATION_WIDTH: float = 2.0\n    67→const MAX_FORMATION_WIDTH: float = 6.0\n    68→\n    69→## Probability of placing a formation at a valid grid point.\n    70→const FORMATION_DENSITY: float = 0.65\n    71→\n    72→## Margin from terrain edges for formation placement (metres).\n    73→const FORMATION_EDGE_MARGIN: float = 30.0\n    74→\n    75→## Player spawn offset from ship spawn (metres).\n    76→const PLAYER_SPAWN_OFFSET: Vector3 = Vector3(5.0, 0.0, 5.0)\n    77→\n    78→## Margin from terrain edges for resource placement (metres).\n    79→const RESOURCE_EDGE_MARGIN: float = 50.0\n    80→\n    81→## RNG seed offsets for independent deterministic sequences.\n    82→const RNG_OFFSET_FORMATIONS: int = 7919\n    83→const RNG_OFFSET_DEPOSITS: int = 3571\n    84→\n    85→\n    86→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    87→\n    88→var _terrain_result: TerrainGenerationResult = null\n    89→var _archetype: BiomeArchetypeConfig = null\n    90→var _player_spawn_position: Vector3 = Vector3.ZERO\n    91→var _ship_spawn_position: Vector3 = Vector3.ZERO\n    92→var _rock_formation_count: int = 0\n    93→\n    94→## Pre-computed resource positions (Vector3 with Y from heightmap).\n    95→var _scrap_metal_surface_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\n    96→var _cryonite_surface_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\n    97→var _deep_scrap_metal_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\n    98→var _deep_cryonite_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\n    99→\n   100→## Per-deposit quantities for fuel cell sufficiency tracking.\n   101→var _surface_scrap_metal_quantities: Array[int] = []\n   102→var _surface_cryonite_quantities: Array[int] = []\n   103→\n   104→\n   105→# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n   106→\n   107→## Returns the fixed seed used for this biome.\n   108→func get_biome_seed() -> int:\n   109→\treturn BIOME_SEED\n   110→\n   111→\n   112→## Returns the biome archetype configuration.\n   113→func get_archetype() -> BiomeArchetypeConfig:\n   114→\treturn _archetype\n   115→\n   116→\n   117→## Returns the terrain generation result.\n   118→func get_terrain_result() -> TerrainGenerationResult:\n   119→\treturn _terrain_result\n   120→\n   121→\n   122→## Returns the player spawn world position.\n   123→func get_player_spawn_position() -> Vector3:\n   124→\treturn _player_spawn_position\n   125→\n   126→\n   127→## Returns the ship spawn world position.\n   128→func get_ship_spawn_position() -> Vector3:\n   129→\treturn _ship_spawn_position\n   130→\n   131→\n   132→## Returns the number of Scrap Metal surface deposit nodes.\n   133→func get_scrap_metal_surface_count() -> int:\n   134→\treturn _scrap_metal_surface_positions.size()\n   135→\n   136→\n   137→## Returns the number of Cryonite surface deposit nodes.\n   138→func get_cryonite_surface_count() -> int:\n   139→\treturn _cryonite_surface_positions.size()\n   140→\n   141→\n   142→## Returns the number of deep Scrap Metal nodes.\n   143→func get_deep_scrap_metal_count() -> int:\n   144→\treturn _deep_scrap_metal_positions.size()\n   145→\n   146→\n   147→## Returns the number of deep Cryonite nodes.\n   148→func get_deep_cryonite_count() -> int:\n   149→\treturn _deep_cryonite_positions.size()\n   150→\n   151→\n   152→## Returns the count of rock formations placed in the biome.\n   153→func get_rock_formation_count() -> int:\n   154→\treturn _rock_formation_count\n   155→\n   156→\n   157→## Returns the total extractable Scrap Metal quantity across all surface and deep deposits.\n   158→func get_total_scrap_metal_quantity() -> int:\n   159→\tvar total: int = 0\n   160→\tfor qty: int in _surface_scrap_metal_quantities:\n   161→\t\ttotal += qty\n   162→\t# Deep nodes contribute their nominal quantity\n   163→\ttotal += _deep_scrap_metal_positions.size() * DEEP_NODE_QUANTITY\n   164→\treturn total\n   165→\n   166→\n   167→## Returns the total extractable Cryonite quantity across all surface and deep deposits.\n   168→func get_total_cryonite_quantity() -> int:\n   169→\tvar total: int = 0\n   170→\tfor qty: int in _surface_cryonite_quantities:\n   171→\t\ttotal += qty\n   172→\ttotal += _deep_cryonite_positions.size() * DEEP_NODE_QUANTITY\n   173→\treturn total\n   174→\n   175→\n   176→## Generates the entire Rock Warrens biome: terrain, rock formations,\n   177→## resource deposits, spawn points, and world boundary.\n   178→func generate() -> void:\n   179→\t_archetype = BiomeArchetypeConfig.rock_warrens()\n   180→\n   181→\t# Pre-compute resource positions using seeded RNG\n   182→\tvar position_rng: RandomNumberGenerator = RandomNumberGenerator.new()\n   183→\tposition_rng.seed = BIOME_SEED\n   184→\t_precompute_resource_positions(position_rng)\n   185→\n   186→\t# Build feature requests and generate terrain\n   187→\tvar requests: Array[TerrainFeatureRequest] = _build_feature_requests()\n   188→\tvar generator: TerrainGenerator = TerrainGenerator.new()\n   189→\t_terrain_result = generator.generate(BIOME_SEED, _archetype, requests)\n   190→\n   191→\t# Update positions with confirmed terrain heights\n   192→\t_update_positions_from_result()\n   193→\n   194→\t# Build visual scene\n   195→\t_build_terrain_mesh()\n   196→\t_build_rock_formations()\n   197→\t_place_deposits()\n   198→\t_create_spawn_points()\n   199→\t_setup_world_boundary()\n   200→\n   201→\tGlobal.log(\"RockWarrensBiome: generation complete — %d formations, %d scrap deposits, %d cryonite deposits\" % [\n   202→\t\t_rock_formation_count,\n   203→\t\tget_scrap_metal_surface_count() + get_deep_scrap_metal_count(),\n   204→\t\tget_cryonite_surface_count() + get_deep_cryonite_count(),\n   205→\t])\n   206→\tgeneration_completed.emit()\n   207→\n   208→\n   209→# ── Private Methods: Position Pre-computation ────────────\n   210→\n   211→## Pre-computes resource node positions using a seeded RNG for deterministic layout.\n   212→## Positions are distributed across the biome with minimum spacing between them.\n   213→func _precompute_resource_positions(rng: RandomNumberGenerator) -> void:\n   214→\tvar all_positions: Array[Vector2] = []\n   215→\tvar usable_min: float = RESOURCE_EDGE_MARGIN\n   216→\tvar usable_max: float = TERRAIN_SIZE - RESOURCE_EDGE_MARGIN\n   217→\n   218→\t# Determine counts from seeded RNG for deterministic variability\n   219→\tvar scrap_count: int = rng.randi_range(SCRAP_METAL_SURFACE_MIN, SCRAP_METAL_SURFACE_MAX)\n   220→\tvar cryo_count: int = rng.randi_range(CRYONITE_SURFACE_MIN, CRYONITE_SURFACE_MAX)\n   221→\n   222→\t# Scrap Metal surface positions\n   223→\tfor i: int in range(scrap_count):\n   224→\t\tvar pos: Vector2 = _find_valid_position(rng, all_positions, usable_min, usable_max)\n   225→\t\tall_positions.append(pos)\n   226→\t\t_scrap_metal_surface_positions.append(Vector3(pos.x, 0.0, pos.y))\n   227→\n   228→\t# Cryonite surface positions\n   229→\tfor i: int in range(cryo_count):\n   230→\t\tvar pos: Vector2 = _find_valid_position(rng, all_positions, usable_min, usable_max)\n   231→\t\tall_positions.append(pos)\n   232→\t\t_cryonite_surface_positions.append(Vector3(pos.x, 0.0, pos.y))\n   233→\n   234→\t# Deep Scrap Metal positions\n   235→\tfor i: int in range(DEEP_NODES_PER_TYPE):\n   236→\t\tvar pos: Vector2 = _find_valid_position(rng, all_positions, usable_min, usable_max)\n   237→\t\tall_positions.append(pos)\n   238→\t\t_deep_scrap_metal_positions.append(Vector3(pos.x, 0.0, pos.y))\n   239→\n   240→\t# Deep Cryonite positions\n   241→\tfor i: int in range(DEEP_NODES_PER_TYPE):\n   242→\t\tvar pos: Vector2 = _find_valid_position(rng, all_positions, usable_min, usable_max)\n   243→\t\tall_positions.append(pos)\n   244→\t\t_deep_cryonite_positions.append(Vector3(pos.x, 0.0, pos.y))\n   245→\n   246→\n   247→## Finds a valid XZ position spaced away from existing positions.\n   248→func _find_valid_position(\n   249→\trng: RandomNumberGenerator,\n   250→\texisting: Array[Vector2],\n   251→\tpos_min: float,\n   252→\tpos_max: float\n   253→) -> Vector2:\n   254→\tvar max_attempts: int = 100\n   255→\tfor attempt: int in range(max_attempts):\n   256→\t\tvar candidate: Vector2 = Vector2(\n   257→\t\t\trng.randf_range(pos_min, pos_max),\n   258→\t\t\trng.randf_range(pos_min, pos_max)\n   259→\t\t)\n   260→\t\tvar too_close: bool = false\n   261→\t\tfor other: Vector2 in existing:\n   262→\t\t\tif candidate.distance_to(other) < RESOURCE_SPACING:\n   263→\t\t\t\ttoo_close = true\n   264→\t\t\t\tbreak\n   265→\t\tif not too_close:\n   266→\t\t\treturn candidate\n   267→\t# Fallback — return a random position if spacing can't be satisfied\n   268→\treturn Vector2(rng.randf_range(pos_min, pos_max), rng.randf_range(pos_min, pos_max))\n   269→\n   270→\n   271→# ── Private Methods: Feature Requests ────────────────────\n   272→\n   273→## Builds the array of TerrainFeatureRequests for terrain generation.\n   274→## Request 0: clearing at edge for ship spawn.\n   275→## Requests 1..N: walkable clearance around each resource position.\n   276→func _build_feature_requests() -> Array[TerrainFeatureRequest]:\n   277→\tvar requests: Array[TerrainFeatureRequest] = []\n   278→\n   279→\t# Request 0: Ship/player spawn clearing near the biome edge\n   280→\trequests.append(TerrainFeatureRequest.create_clearing(SHIP_CLEARING_RADIUS, \"edge\"))\n   281→\n   282→\t# Walkable clearance around every resource position to guarantee reachability\n   283→\tvar all_resource_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\n   284→\tall_resource_positions.append_array(_scrap_metal_surface_positions)\n   285→\tall_resource_positions.append_array(_cryonite_surface_positions)\n   286→\tall_resource_positions.append_array(_deep_scrap_metal_positions)\n   287→\tall_resource_positions.append_array(_deep_cryonite_positions)\n   288→\n   289→\tfor pos: Vector3 in all_resource_positions:\n   290→\t\tvar clearance_position: Vector2 = Vector2(pos.x, pos.z)\n   291→\t\trequests.append(\n   292→\t\t\tTerrainFeatureRequest.create_walkable_clearance(clearance_position, RESOURCE_CLEARANCE_RADIUS)\n   293→\t\t)\n   294→\n   295→\treturn requests\n   296→\n   297→\n   298→# ── Private Methods: Position Update ─────────────────────\n   299→\n   300→## Updates pre-computed resource positions with actual terrain heights from the\n   301→## generation result's confirmed positions.\n   302→func _update_positions_from_result() -> void:\n   303→\tif _terrain_result == null:\n   304→\t\treturn\n   305→\n   306→\t# Request 0 is the clearing — extract spawn position\n   307→\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(0):\n   308→\t\tvar clearing_positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[0]\n   309→\t\tif clearing_positions.size() > 0:\n   310→\t\t\tvar clearing_center: Vector3 = clearing_positions[0]\n   311→\t\t\t_ship_spawn_position = clearing_center\n   312→\t\t\t_player_spawn_position = clearing_center + PLAYER_SPAWN_OFFSET\n   313→\n   314→\t# Requests 1..N are walkable clearances — update Y heights in order\n   315→\tvar request_index: int = 1\n   316→\n   317→\tfor i: int in range(_scrap_metal_surface_positions.size()):\n   318→\t\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(request_index):\n   319→\t\t\tvar positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[request_index]\n   320→\t\t\tif positions.size() > 0:\n   321→\t\t\t\t_scrap_metal_surface_positions[i] = positions[0]\n   322→\t\trequest_index += 1\n   323→\n   324→\tfor i: int in range(_cryonite_surface_positions.size()):\n   325→\t\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(request_index):\n   326→\t\t\tvar positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[request_index]\n   327→\t\t\tif positions.size() > 0:\n   328→\t\t\t\t_cryonite_surface_positions[i] = positions[0]\n   329→\t\trequest_index += 1\n   330→\n   331→\tfor i: int in range(_deep_scrap_metal_positions.size()):\n   332→\t\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(request_index):\n   333→\t\t\tvar positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[request_index]\n   334→\t\t\tif positions.size() > 0:\n   335→\t\t\t\t_deep_scrap_metal_positions[i] = positions[0]\n   336→\t\trequest_index += 1\n   337→\n   338→\tfor i: int in range(_deep_cryonite_positions.size()):\n   339→\t\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(request_index):\n   340→\t\t\tvar positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[request_index]\n   341→\t\t\tif positions.size() > 0:\n   342→\t\t\t\t_deep_cryonite_positions[i] = positions[0]\n   343→\t\trequest_index += 1\n   344→\n   345→\n   346→# ── Private Methods: Scene Construction ──────────────────\n   347→\n   348→## Creates the terrain visual mesh and collision body from the generation result.\n   349→func _build_terrain_mesh() -> void:\n   350→\tvar mesh_instance: MeshInstance3D = MeshInstance3D.new()\n   351→\tmesh_instance.name = \"TerrainMesh\"\n   352→\tmesh_instance.mesh = _terrain_result.terrain_mesh\n   353→\tadd_child(mesh_instance)\n   354→\n   355→\tvar static_body: StaticBody3D = StaticBody3D.new()\n   356→\tstatic_body.name = \"TerrainCollision\"\n   357→\tstatic_body.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT\n   358→\tstatic_body.collision_mask = 0\n   359→\n   360→\tvar collision_shape: CollisionShape3D = CollisionShape3D.new()\n   361→\tcollision_shape.name = \"CollisionShape3D\"\n   362→\tcollision_shape.shape = _terrain_result.collision_shape\n   363→\tstatic_body.add_child(collision_shape)\n   364→\tadd_child(static_body)\n   365→\n   366→\n   367→## Places rock formations (CSGBox3D stacks) across the biome, avoiding cleared zones.\n   368→## Formations create tight corridors with short sight lines between navigable areas.\n   369→func _build_rock_formations() -> void:\n   370→\tvar formations_parent: Node3D = Node3D.new()\n   371→\tformations_parent.name = \"RockFormations\"\n   372→\tadd_child(formations_parent)\n   373→\n   374→\tvar formation_rng: RandomNumberGenerator = RandomNumberGenerator.new()\n   375→\tformation_rng.seed = BIOME_SEED + RNG_OFFSET_FORMATIONS\n   376→\n   377→\t# Build exclusion zones from spawn clearing and resource positions\n   378→\tvar exclusion_zones: Array[Vector2] = _get_exclusion_zones()\n   379→\n   380→\t# Place formations on a grid with randomized offset and density filtering\n   381→\tvar grid_start: float = FORMATION_EDGE_MARGIN\n   382→\tvar grid_end: float = TERRAIN_SIZE - FORMATION_EDGE_MARGIN\n   383→\tvar x: float = grid_start\n   384→\n   385→\twhile x < grid_end:\n   386→\t\tvar z: float = grid_start\n   387→\t\twhile z < grid_end:\n   388→\t\t\tvar offset_x: float = formation_rng.randf_range(-3.0, 3.0)\n   389→\t\t\tvar offset_z: float = formation_rng.randf_range(-3.0, 3.0)\n   390→\t\t\tvar world_x: float = clampf(x + offset_x, grid_start, grid_end)\n   391→\t\t\tvar world_z: float = clampf(z + offset_z, grid_start, grid_end)\n   392→\n   393→\t\t\t# Skip if inside an exclusion zone\n   394→\t\t\tvar excluded: bool = false\n   395→\t\t\tvar candidate_2d: Vector2 = Vector2(world_x, world_z)\n   396→\t\t\tfor zone: Vector2 in exclusion_zones:\n   397→\t\t\t\tif candidate_2d.distance_to(zone) < FORMATION_EXCLUSION_RADIUS:\n   398→\t\t\t\t\texcluded = true\n   399→\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n   400→\n   401→\t\t\t# Density filtering — skip some grid points for corridor variety\n   402→\t\t\tif not excluded and formation_rng.randf() < FORMATION_DENSITY:\n   403→\t\t\t\tvar terrain_y: float = _get_terrain_height(world_x, world_z)\n   404→\t\t\t\tvar formation: Node3D = _create_rock_formation(\n   405→\t\t\t\t\tformation_rng, world_x, terrain_y, world_z\n   406→\t\t\t\t)\n   407→\t\t\t\tformations_parent.add_child(formation)\n   408→\t\t\t\t_rock_formation_count += 1\n   409→\n   410→\t\t\tz += FORMATION_GRID_SPACING\n   411→\t\tx += FORMATION_GRID_SPACING\n   412→\n   413→\n   414→## Returns exclusion zones (XZ positions) where rock formations must not be placed.\n   415→func _get_exclusion_zones() -> Array[Vector2]:\n   416→\tvar zones: Array[Vector2] = []\n   417→\n   418→\t# Ship spawn clearing\n   419→\tzones.append(Vector2(_ship_spawn_position.x, _ship_spawn_position.z))\n   420→\n   421→\t# All resource positions\n   422→\tfor pos: Vector3 in _scrap_metal_surface_positions:\n   423→\t\tzones.append(Vector2(pos.x, pos.z))\n   424→\tfor pos: Vector3 in _cryonite_surface_positions:\n   425→\t\tzones.append(Vector2(pos.x, pos.z))\n   426→\tfor pos: Vector3 in _deep_scrap_metal_positions:\n   427→\t\tzones.append(Vector2(pos.x, pos.z))\n   428→\tfor pos: Vector3 in _deep_cryonite_positions:\n   429→\t\tzones.append(Vector2(pos.x, pos.z))\n   430→\n   431→\treturn zones\n   432→\n   433→\n   434→## Creates a single rock formation node with 1–3 stacked CSGBox3D blocks.\n   435→func _create_rock_formation(\n   436→\tformation_rng: RandomNumberGenerator,\n   437→\tworld_x: float,\n   438→\tterrain_y: float,\n   439→\tworld_z: float\n   440→) -> Node3D:\n   441→\tvar formation: Node3D = Node3D.new()\n   442→\tformation.name = \"RockFormation_%04d\" % _rock_formation_count\n   443→\tformation.position = Vector3(world_x, terrain_y, world_z)\n   444→\n   445→\tvar stack_count: int = formation_rng.randi_range(1, 3)\n   446→\tvar current_y: float = 0.0\n   447→\n   448→\tfor i: int in range(stack_count):\n   449→\t\tvar block: CSGBox3D = CSGBox3D.new()\n   450→\t\tblock.name = \"Block_%d\" % i\n   451→\n   452→\t\tvar block_width: float = formation_rng.randf_range(MIN_FORMATION_WIDTH, MAX_FORMATION_WIDTH)\n   453→\t\tvar per_block_min: float = MIN_FORMATION_HEIGHT / float(stack_count)\n   454→\t\tvar per_block_max: float = MAX_FORMATION_HEIGHT / float(stack_count)\n   455→\t\tvar block_height: float = formation_rng.randf_range(per_block_min, per_block_max)\n   456→\t\tvar block_depth: float = formation_rng.randf_range(MIN_FORMATION_WIDTH, MAX_FORMATION_WIDTH)\n   457→\n   458→\t\tblock.size = Vector3(block_width, block_height, block_depth)\n   459→\t\tblock.position = Vector3(0.0, current_y + block_height * 0.5, 0.0)\n   460→\t\t# Slight yaw rotation for natural rocky appearance\n   461→\t\tblock.rotation.y = formation_rng.randf_range(-0.3, 0.3)\n   462→\t\tblock.use_collision = true\n   463→\n   464→\t\tformation.add_child(block)\n   465→\t\tcurrent_y += block_height\n   466→\n   467→\treturn formation\n   468→\n   469→\n   470→## Places deposit nodes at confirmed resource positions.\n   471→func _place_deposits() -> void:\n   472→\tvar deposits_parent: Node3D = Node3D.new()\n   473→\tdeposits_parent.name = \"Deposits\"\n   474→\tadd_child(deposits_parent)\n   475→\n   476→\tvar deposit_rng: RandomNumberGenerator = RandomNumberGenerator.new()\n   477→\tdeposit_rng.seed = BIOME_SEED + RNG_OFFSET_DEPOSITS\n   478→\n   479→\t# Place Scrap Metal surface deposits\n   480→\t_surface_scrap_metal_quantities.clear()\n   481→\tfor i: int in range(_scrap_metal_surface_positions.size()):\n   482→\t\tvar pos: Vector3 = _scrap_metal_surface_positions[i]\n   483→\t\tvar quantity: int = deposit_rng.randi_range(SURFACE_NODE_MIN_QUANTITY, SURFACE_NODE_MAX_QUANTITY)\n   484→\t\t_surface_scrap_metal_quantities.append(quantity)\n   485→\t\tvar deposit: Deposit = _create_deposit(\n   486→\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.SCRAP_METAL,\n   487→\t\t\tquantity,\n   488→\t\t\tpos,\n   489→\t\t\tfalse,\n   490→\t\t\t\"ScrapMetal_%d\" % i\n   491→\t\t)\n   492→\t\tdeposits_parent.add_child(deposit)\n   493→\n   494→\t# Place Cryonite surface deposits\n   495→\t_surface_cryonite_quantities.clear()\n   496→\tfor i: int in range(_cryonite_surface_positions.size()):\n   497→\t\tvar pos: Vector3 = _cryonite_surface_positions[i]\n   498→\t\tvar quantity: int = deposit_rng.randi_range(SURFACE_NODE_MIN_QUANTITY, SURFACE_NODE_MAX_QUANTITY)\n   499→\t\t_surface_cryonite_quantities.append(quantity)\n   500→\t\tvar deposit: Deposit = _create_deposit(\n   501→\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.CRYONITE,\n   502→\t\t\tquantity,\n   503→\t\t\tpos,\n   504→\t\t\tfalse,\n   505→\t\t\t\"Cryonite_%d\" % i\n   506→\t\t)\n   507→\t\tdeposits_parent.add_child(deposit)\n   508→\n   509→\t# Place deep Scrap Metal nodes\n   510→\tfor i: int in range(_deep_scrap_metal_positions.size()):\n   511→\t\tvar pos: Vector3 = _deep_scrap_metal_positions[i]\n   512→\t\tvar deposit: Deposit = _create_deposit(\n   513→\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.SCRAP_METAL,\n   514→\t\t\tDEEP_NODE_QUANTITY,\n   515→\t\t\tpos,\n   516→\t\t\ttrue,\n   517→\t\t\t\"DeepScrapMetal_%d\" % i\n   518→\t\t)\n   519→\t\tdeposits_parent.add_child(deposit)\n   520→\n   521→\t# Place deep Cryonite nodes\n   522→\tfor i: int in range(_deep_cryonite_positions.size()):\n   523→\t\tvar pos: Vector3 = _deep_cryonite_positions[i]\n   524→\t\tvar deposit: Deposit = _create_deposit(\n   525→\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.CRYONITE,\n   526→\t\t\tDEEP_NODE_QUANTITY,\n   527→\t\t\tpos,\n   528→\t\t\ttrue,\n   529→\t\t\t\"DeepCryonite_%d\" % i\n   530→\t\t)\n   531→\t\tdeposits_parent.add_child(deposit)\n   532→\n   533→\n   534→## Creates a single deposit node configured for the given resource type and position.\n   535→func _create_deposit(\n   536→\tresource_type: ResourceDefs.ResourceType,\n   537→\tquantity: int,\n   538→\tworld_position: Vector3,\n   539→\tis_deep: bool,\n   540→\tdeposit_name: String\n   541→) -> Deposit:\n   542→\tvar deposit: Deposit = Deposit.new()\n   543→\tdeposit.name = deposit_name\n   544→\tdeposit.setup(\n   545→\t\tresource_type,\n   546→\t\tResourceDefs.Purity.THREE_STAR,\n   547→\t\tResourceDefs.DensityTier.MEDIUM,\n   548→\t\tquantity\n   549→\t)\n   550→\tdeposit.position = world_position\n   551→\n   552→\tif is_deep:\n   553→\t\tdeposit.infinite = true\n   554→\t\tdeposit.yield_rate = DEEP_NODE_YIELD_RATE\n   555→\t\tdeposit.add_to_group(\"deep_deposit\")\n   556→\telse:\n   557→\t\tdeposit.add_to_group(\"surface_deposit\")\n   558→\n   559→\tdeposit.add_to_group(\"interactable\")\n   560→\n   561→\t# Add interaction collision body so scanner raycast (mask=INTERACTABLE) can hit deposits\n   562→\tvar interact_body: StaticBody3D = StaticBody3D.new()\n   563→\tinteract_body.name = \"InteractBody\"\n   564→\tinteract_body.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.INTERACTABLE\n   565→\tinteract_body.collision_mask = 0\n   566→\tvar interact_col: CollisionShape3D = CollisionShape3D.new()\n   567→\tinteract_col.name = \"CollisionShape3D\"\n   568→\tvar interact_box: BoxShape3D = BoxShape3D.new()\n   569→\tinteract_box.size = Vector3(1.5, 1.5, 1.5)\n   570→\tinteract_col.shape = interact_box\n   571→\tinteract_body.add_child(interact_col)\n   572→\tdeposit.add_child(interact_body)\n   573→\n   574→\t# Register with DepositRegistry so scanner ping can detect this deposit\n   575→\tDepositRegistry.register(deposit)\n   576→\n   577→\treturn deposit\n   578→\n   579→\n   580→## Creates Marker3D nodes for player and ship spawn points.\n   581→func _create_spawn_points() -> void:\n   582→\tvar player_marker: Marker3D = Marker3D.new()\n   583→\tplayer_marker.name = \"PlayerSpawnPoint\"\n   584→\tplayer_marker.position = _player_spawn_position\n   585→\tadd_child(player_marker)\n   586→\n   587→\tvar ship_marker: Marker3D = Marker3D.new()\n   588→\tship_marker.name = \"ShipSpawnPoint\"\n   589→\tship_marker.position = _ship_spawn_position\n   590→\tadd_child(ship_marker)\n   591→\n   592→\n   593→## Sets up the world boundary manager with invisible walls.\n   594→func _setup_world_boundary() -> void:\n   595→\tvar boundary: WorldBoundaryManager = WorldBoundaryManager.new()\n   596→\tboundary.name = \"WorldBoundaryManager\"\n   597→\tadd_child(boundary)\n   598→\tboundary.initialize(_archetype)\n   599→\n   600→\n   601→# ── Private Methods: Helpers ─────────────────────────────\n   602→\n   603→## Gets the terrain height at a world XZ position by sampling the heightmap.\n   604→func _get_terrain_height(world_x: float, world_z: float) -> float:\n   605→\tif _terrain_result == null or _terrain_result.heightmap.is_empty():\n   606→\t\treturn 0.0\n   607→\tvar resolution: int = _terrain_result.heightmap_resolution\n   608→\tvar spacing: float = TERRAIN_SIZE / float(resolution - 1)\n   609→\tvar xi: int = clampi(roundi(world_x / spacing), 0, resolution - 1)\n   610→\tvar zi: int = clampi(roundi(world_z / spacing), 0, resolution - 1)\n   611→\treturn _terrain_result.heightmap[zi * resolution + xi]\n   612→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"f0b715bb-0a9d-433a-9e3e-f1ef60e56f0b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\gameplay\\rock_warrens_biome.gd","content":"## Rock Warrens biome — dense rock formations creating tight navigable corridors\n## with low visibility. Mixed resource profile: Scrap Metal and Cryonite pockets.\n## Must contain sufficient resources to craft at least one Fuel Cell.\n## Owner: gameplay-programmer\nclass_name RockWarrensBiome\nextends Node3D\n\n\n# ── Signals ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nsignal generation_completed\n\n\n# ── Constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Fixed seed for deterministic terrain generation (from BiomeRegistry).\nconst BIOME_SEED: int = 2047\n\n## Terrain extent in metres.\nconst TERRAIN_SIZE: float = 500.0\n\n## Ship/player spawn clearing radius in metres.\nconst SHIP_CLEARING_RADIUS: float = 20.0\n\n## Walkable clearance radius around resource positions in metres.\nconst RESOURCE_CLEARANCE_RADIUS: float = 3.0\n\n## Maximum terrain slope for resource placement (degrees).\nconst RESOURCE_SLOPE_MAX: float = 30.0\n\n## Minimum spacing between resource positions (metres).\nconst RESOURCE_SPACING: float = 15.0\n\n## Scrap Metal surface deposit count range per acceptance criteria.\nconst SCRAP_METAL_SURFACE_MIN: int = 5\nconst SCRAP_METAL_SURFACE_MAX: int = 8\n\n## Cryonite surface deposit count range per acceptance criteria.\nconst CRYONITE_SURFACE_MIN: int = 4\nconst CRYONITE_SURFACE_MAX: int = 7\n\n## Number of deep nodes per resource type.\nconst DEEP_NODES_PER_TYPE: int = 1\n\n## Deep node quantity — high value; infinite flag means it never depletes.\nconst DEEP_NODE_QUANTITY: int = 100\n\n## Surface deposit quantity range.\nconst SURFACE_NODE_MIN_QUANTITY: int = 15\nconst SURFACE_NODE_MAX_QUANTITY: int = 40\n\n## Deep node yield rate multiplier (10% of surface speed).\nconst DEEP_NODE_YIELD_RATE: float = 0.1\n\n## Rock formation grid spacing — metres between formation placement checks.\nconst FORMATION_GRID_SPACING: float = 12.0\n\n## Exclusion radius around spawn and resource positions — no formations placed here.\nconst FORMATION_EXCLUSION_RADIUS: float = 6.0\n\n## Rock formation height range (metres).\nconst MIN_FORMATION_HEIGHT: float = 6.0\nconst MAX_FORMATION_HEIGHT: float = 18.0\n\n## Rock formation width range (metres).\nconst MIN_FORMATION_WIDTH: float = 2.0\nconst MAX_FORMATION_WIDTH: float = 6.0\n\n## Probability of placing a formation at a valid grid point.\nconst FORMATION_DENSITY: float = 0.65\n\n## Margin from terrain edges for formation placement (metres).\nconst FORMATION_EDGE_MARGIN: float = 30.0\n\n## Player spawn offset from ship spawn (metres).\nconst PLAYER_SPAWN_OFFSET: Vector3 = Vector3(5.0, 0.0, 5.0)\n\n## Margin from terrain edges for resource placement (metres).\nconst RESOURCE_EDGE_MARGIN: float = 50.0\n\n## RNG seed offsets for independent deterministic sequences.\nconst RNG_OFFSET_FORMATIONS: int = 7919\nconst RNG_OFFSET_DEPOSITS: int = 3571\n\n\n# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n\nvar _terrain_result: TerrainGenerationResult = null\nvar _archetype: BiomeArchetypeConfig = null\nvar _player_spawn_position: Vector3 = Vector3.ZERO\nvar _ship_spawn_position: Vector3 = Vector3.ZERO\nvar _rock_formation_count: int = 0\n\n## Pre-computed resource positions (Vector3 with Y from heightmap).\nvar _scrap_metal_surface_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\nvar _cryonite_surface_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\nvar _deep_scrap_metal_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\nvar _deep_cryonite_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\n\n## Per-deposit quantities for fuel cell sufficiency tracking.\nvar _surface_scrap_metal_quantities: Array[int] = []\nvar _surface_cryonite_quantities: Array[int] = []\n\n\n# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Returns the fixed seed used for this biome.\nfunc get_biome_seed() -> int:\n\treturn BIOME_SEED\n\n\n## Returns the biome archetype configuration.\nfunc get_archetype() -> BiomeArchetypeConfig:\n\treturn _archetype\n\n\n## Returns the terrain generation result.\nfunc get_terrain_result() -> TerrainGenerationResult:\n\treturn _terrain_result\n\n\n## Returns the player spawn world position.\nfunc get_player_spawn_position() -> Vector3:\n\treturn _player_spawn_position\n\n\n## Returns the ship spawn world position.\nfunc get_ship_spawn_position() -> Vector3:\n\treturn _ship_spawn_position\n\n\n## Returns the number of Scrap Metal surface deposit nodes.\nfunc get_scrap_metal_surface_count() -> int:\n\treturn _scrap_metal_surface_positions.size()\n\n\n## Returns the number of Cryonite surface deposit nodes.\nfunc get_cryonite_surface_count() -> int:\n\treturn _cryonite_surface_positions.size()\n\n\n## Returns the number of deep Scrap Metal nodes.\nfunc get_deep_scrap_metal_count() -> int:\n\treturn _deep_scrap_metal_positions.size()\n\n\n## Returns the number of deep Cryonite nodes.\nfunc get_deep_cryonite_count() -> int:\n\treturn _deep_cryonite_positions.size()\n\n\n## Returns the count of rock formations placed in the biome.\nfunc get_rock_formation_count() -> int:\n\treturn _rock_formation_count\n\n\n## Returns the total extractable Scrap Metal quantity across all surface and deep deposits.\nfunc get_total_scrap_metal_quantity() -> int:\n\tvar total: int = 0\n\tfor qty: int in _surface_scrap_metal_quantities:\n\t\ttotal += qty\n\t# Deep nodes contribute their nominal quantity\n\ttotal += _deep_scrap_metal_positions.size() * DEEP_NODE_QUANTITY\n\treturn total\n\n\n## Returns the total extractable Cryonite quantity across all surface and deep deposits.\nfunc get_total_cryonite_quantity() -> int:\n\tvar total: int = 0\n\tfor qty: int in _surface_cryonite_quantities:\n\t\ttotal += qty\n\ttotal += _deep_cryonite_positions.size() * DEEP_NODE_QUANTITY\n\treturn total\n\n\n## Generates the entire Rock Warrens biome: terrain, rock formations,\n## resource deposits, spawn points, and world boundary.\nfunc generate() -> void:\n\t_archetype = BiomeArchetypeConfig.rock_warrens()\n\n\t# Pre-compute resource positions using seeded RNG\n\tvar position_rng: RandomNumberGenerator = RandomNumberGenerator.new()\n\tposition_rng.seed = BIOME_SEED\n\t_precompute_resource_positions(position_rng)\n\n\t# Build feature requests and generate terrain\n\tvar requests: Array[TerrainFeatureRequest] = _build_feature_requests()\n\tvar generator: TerrainGenerator = TerrainGenerator.new()\n\t_terrain_result = generator.generate(BIOME_SEED, _archetype, requests)\n\n\t# Update positions with confirmed terrain heights\n\t_update_positions_from_result()\n\n\t# Build visual scene\n\t_build_terrain_mesh()\n\t_build_rock_formations()\n\t_place_deposits()\n\t_create_spawn_points()\n\t_setup_world_boundary()\n\n\tGlobal.log(\"RockWarrensBiome: generation complete — %d formations, %d scrap deposits, %d cryonite deposits\" % [\n\t\t_rock_formation_count,\n\t\tget_scrap_metal_surface_count() + get_deep_scrap_metal_count(),\n\t\tget_cryonite_surface_count() + get_deep_cryonite_count(),\n\t])\n\tgeneration_completed.emit()\n\n\n# ── Private Methods: Position Pre-computation ────────────\n\n## Pre-computes resource node positions using a seeded RNG for deterministic layout.\n## Positions are distributed across the biome with minimum spacing between them.\nfunc _precompute_resource_positions(rng: RandomNumberGenerator) -> void:\n\tvar all_positions: Array[Vector2] = []\n\tvar usable_min: float = RESOURCE_EDGE_MARGIN\n\tvar usable_max: float = TERRAIN_SIZE - RESOURCE_EDGE_MARGIN\n\n\t# Determine counts from seeded RNG for deterministic variability\n\tvar scrap_count: int = rng.randi_range(SCRAP_METAL_SURFACE_MIN, SCRAP_METAL_SURFACE_MAX)\n\tvar cryo_count: int = rng.randi_range(CRYONITE_SURFACE_MIN, CRYONITE_SURFACE_MAX)\n\n\t# Scrap Metal surface positions\n\tfor i: int in range(scrap_count):\n\t\tvar pos: Vector2 = _find_valid_position(rng, all_positions, usable_min, usable_max)\n\t\tall_positions.append(pos)\n\t\t_scrap_metal_surface_positions.append(Vector3(pos.x, 0.0, pos.y))\n\n\t# Cryonite surface positions\n\tfor i: int in range(cryo_count):\n\t\tvar pos: Vector2 = _find_valid_position(rng, all_positions, usable_min, usable_max)\n\t\tall_positions.append(pos)\n\t\t_cryonite_surface_positions.append(Vector3(pos.x, 0.0, pos.y))\n\n\t# Deep Scrap Metal positions\n\tfor i: int in range(DEEP_NODES_PER_TYPE):\n\t\tvar pos: Vector2 = _find_valid_position(rng, all_positions, usable_min, usable_max)\n\t\tall_positions.append(pos)\n\t\t_deep_scrap_metal_positions.append(Vector3(pos.x, 0.0, pos.y))\n\n\t# Deep Cryonite positions\n\tfor i: int in range(DEEP_NODES_PER_TYPE):\n\t\tvar pos: Vector2 = _find_valid_position(rng, all_positions, usable_min, usable_max)\n\t\tall_positions.append(pos)\n\t\t_deep_cryonite_positions.append(Vector3(pos.x, 0.0, pos.y))\n\n\n## Finds a valid XZ position spaced away from existing positions.\nfunc _find_valid_position(\n\trng: RandomNumberGenerator,\n\texisting: Array[Vector2],\n\tpos_min: float,\n\tpos_max: float\n) -> Vector2:\n\tvar max_attempts: int = 100\n\tfor attempt: int in range(max_attempts):\n\t\tvar candidate: Vector2 = Vector2(\n\t\t\trng.randf_range(pos_min, pos_max),\n\t\t\trng.randf_range(pos_min, pos_max)\n\t\t)\n\t\tvar too_close: bool = false\n\t\tfor other: Vector2 in existing:\n\t\t\tif candidate.distance_to(other) < RESOURCE_SPACING:\n\t\t\t\ttoo_close = true\n\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\tif not too_close:\n\t\t\treturn candidate\n\t# Fallback — return a random position if spacing can't be satisfied\n\treturn Vector2(rng.randf_range(pos_min, pos_max), rng.randf_range(pos_min, pos_max))\n\n\n# ── Private Methods: Feature Requests ────────────────────\n\n## Builds the array of TerrainFeatureRequests for terrain generation.\n## Request 0: clearing at edge for ship spawn.\n## Requests 1..N: walkable clearance around each resource position.\nfunc _build_feature_requests() -> Array[TerrainFeatureRequest]:\n\tvar requests: Array[TerrainFeatureRequest] = []\n\n\t# Request 0: Ship/player spawn clearing near the biome edge\n\trequests.append(TerrainFeatureRequest.create_clearing(SHIP_CLEARING_RADIUS, \"edge\"))\n\n\t# Walkable clearance around every resource position to guarantee reachability\n\tvar all_resource_positions: Array[Vector3] = []\n\tall_resource_positions.append_array(_scrap_metal_surface_positions)\n\tall_resource_positions.append_array(_cryonite_surface_positions)\n\tall_resource_positions.append_array(_deep_scrap_metal_positions)\n\tall_resource_positions.append_array(_deep_cryonite_positions)\n\n\tfor pos: Vector3 in all_resource_positions:\n\t\tvar clearance_position: Vector2 = Vector2(pos.x, pos.z)\n\t\trequests.append(\n\t\t\tTerrainFeatureRequest.create_walkable_clearance(clearance_position, RESOURCE_CLEARANCE_RADIUS)\n\t\t)\n\n\treturn requests\n\n\n# ── Private Methods: Position Update ─────────────────────\n\n## Updates pre-computed resource positions with actual terrain heights from the\n## generation result's confirmed positions.\nfunc _update_positions_from_result() -> void:\n\tif _terrain_result == null:\n\t\treturn\n\n\t# Request 0 is the clearing — extract spawn position\n\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(0):\n\t\tvar clearing_positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[0]\n\t\tif clearing_positions.size() > 0:\n\t\t\tvar clearing_center: Vector3 = clearing_positions[0]\n\t\t\t_ship_spawn_position = clearing_center\n\t\t\t_player_spawn_position = clearing_center + PLAYER_SPAWN_OFFSET\n\n\t# Requests 1..N are walkable clearances — update Y heights in order\n\tvar request_index: int = 1\n\n\tfor i: int in range(_scrap_metal_surface_positions.size()):\n\t\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(request_index):\n\t\t\tvar positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[request_index]\n\t\t\tif positions.size() > 0:\n\t\t\t\t_scrap_metal_surface_positions[i] = positions[0]\n\t\trequest_index += 1\n\n\tfor i: int in range(_cryonite_surface_positions.size()):\n\t\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(request_index):\n\t\t\tvar positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[request_index]\n\t\t\tif positions.size() > 0:\n\t\t\t\t_cryonite_surface_positions[i] = positions[0]\n\t\trequest_index += 1\n\n\tfor i: int in range(_deep_scrap_metal_positions.size()):\n\t\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(request_index):\n\t\t\tvar positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[request_index]\n\t\t\tif positions.size() > 0:\n\t\t\t\t_deep_scrap_metal_positions[i] = positions[0]\n\t\trequest_index += 1\n\n\tfor i: int in range(_deep_cryonite_positions.size()):\n\t\tif _terrain_result.confirmed_positions.has(request_index):\n\t\t\tvar positions: Array = _terrain_result.confirmed_positions[request_index]\n\t\t\tif positions.size() > 0:\n\t\t\t\t_deep_cryonite_positions[i] = positions[0]\n\t\trequest_index += 1\n\n\n# ── Private Methods: Scene Construction ──────────────────\n\n## Creates the terrain visual mesh and collision body from the generation result.\nfunc _build_terrain_mesh() -> void:\n\tvar mesh_instance: MeshInstance3D = MeshInstance3D.new()\n\tmesh_instance.name = \"TerrainMesh\"\n\tmesh_instance.mesh = _terrain_result.terrain_mesh\n\tadd_child(mesh_instance)\n\n\tvar static_body: StaticBody3D = StaticBody3D.new()\n\tstatic_body.name = \"TerrainCollision\"\n\tstatic_body.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.ENVIRONMENT\n\tstatic_body.collision_mask = 0\n\n\tvar collision_shape: CollisionShape3D = CollisionShape3D.new()\n\tcollision_shape.name = \"CollisionShape3D\"\n\tcollision_shape.shape = _terrain_result.collision_shape\n\tstatic_body.add_child(collision_shape)\n\tadd_child(static_body)\n\n\n## Places rock formations (CSGBox3D stacks) across the biome, avoiding cleared zones.\n## Formations create tight corridors with short sight lines between navigable areas.\nfunc _build_rock_formations() -> void:\n\tvar formations_parent: Node3D = Node3D.new()\n\tformations_parent.name = \"RockFormations\"\n\tadd_child(formations_parent)\n\n\tvar formation_rng: RandomNumberGenerator = RandomNumberGenerator.new()\n\tformation_rng.seed = BIOME_SEED + RNG_OFFSET_FORMATIONS\n\n\t# Build exclusion zones from spawn clearing and resource positions\n\tvar exclusion_zones: Array[Vector2] = _get_exclusion_zones()\n\n\t# Place formations on a grid with randomized offset and density filtering\n\tvar grid_start: float = FORMATION_EDGE_MARGIN\n\tvar grid_end: float = TERRAIN_SIZE - FORMATION_EDGE_MARGIN\n\tvar x: float = grid_start\n\n\twhile x < grid_end:\n\t\tvar z: float = grid_start\n\t\twhile z < grid_end:\n\t\t\tvar offset_x: float = formation_rng.randf_range(-3.0, 3.0)\n\t\t\tvar offset_z: float = formation_rng.randf_range(-3.0, 3.0)\n\t\t\tvar world_x: float = clampf(x + offset_x, grid_start, grid_end)\n\t\t\tvar world_z: float = clampf(z + offset_z, grid_start, grid_end)\n\n\t\t\t# Skip if inside an exclusion zone\n\t\t\tvar excluded: bool = false\n\t\t\tvar candidate_2d: Vector2 = Vector2(world_x, world_z)\n\t\t\tfor zone: Vector2 in exclusion_zones:\n\t\t\t\tif candidate_2d.distance_to(zone) < FORMATION_EXCLUSION_RADIUS:\n\t\t\t\t\texcluded = true\n\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n\n\t\t\t# Density filtering — skip some grid points for corridor variety\n\t\t\tif not excluded and formation_rng.randf() < FORMATION_DENSITY:\n\t\t\t\tvar terrain_y: float = _get_terrain_height(world_x, world_z)\n\t\t\t\tvar formation: Node3D = _create_rock_formation(\n\t\t\t\t\tformation_rng, world_x, terrain_y, world_z\n\t\t\t\t)\n\t\t\t\tformations_parent.add_child(formation)\n\t\t\t\t_rock_formation_count += 1\n\n\t\t\tz += FORMATION_GRID_SPACING\n\t\tx += FORMATION_GRID_SPACING\n\n\n## Returns exclusion zones (XZ positions) where rock formations must not be placed.\nfunc _get_exclusion_zones() -> Array[Vector2]:\n\tvar zones: Array[Vector2] = []\n\n\t# Ship spawn clearing\n\tzones.append(Vector2(_ship_spawn_position.x, _ship_spawn_position.z))\n\n\t# All resource positions\n\tfor pos: Vector3 in _scrap_metal_surface_positions:\n\t\tzones.append(Vector2(pos.x, pos.z))\n\tfor pos: Vector3 in _cryonite_surface_positions:\n\t\tzones.append(Vector2(pos.x, pos.z))\n\tfor pos: Vector3 in _deep_scrap_metal_positions:\n\t\tzones.append(Vector2(pos.x, pos.z))\n\tfor pos: Vector3 in _deep_cryonite_positions:\n\t\tzones.append(Vector2(pos.x, pos.z))\n\n\treturn zones\n\n\n## Creates a single rock formation node with 1–3 stacked CSGBox3D blocks.\nfunc _create_rock_formation(\n\tformation_rng: RandomNumberGenerator,\n\tworld_x: float,\n\tterrain_y: float,\n\tworld_z: float\n) -> Node3D:\n\tvar formation: Node3D = Node3D.new()\n\tformation.name = \"RockFormation_%04d\" % _rock_formation_count\n\tformation.position = Vector3(world_x, terrain_y, world_z)\n\n\tvar stack_count: int = formation_rng.randi_range(1, 3)\n\tvar current_y: float = 0.0\n\n\tfor i: int in range(stack_count):\n\t\tvar block: CSGBox3D = CSGBox3D.new()\n\t\tblock.name = \"Block_%d\" % i\n\n\t\tvar block_width: float = formation_rng.randf_range(MIN_FORMATION_WIDTH, MAX_FORMATION_WIDTH)\n\t\tvar per_block_min: float = MIN_FORMATION_HEIGHT / float(stack_count)\n\t\tvar per_block_max: float = MAX_FORMATION_HEIGHT / float(stack_count)\n\t\tvar block_height: float = formation_rng.randf_range(per_block_min, per_block_max)\n\t\tvar block_depth: float = formation_rng.randf_range(MIN_FORMATION_WIDTH, MAX_FORMATION_WIDTH)\n\n\t\tblock.size = Vector3(block_width, block_height, block_depth)\n\t\tblock.position = Vector3(0.0, current_y + block_height * 0.5, 0.0)\n\t\t# Slight yaw rotation for natural rocky appearance\n\t\tblock.rotation.y = formation_rng.randf_range(-0.3, 0.3)\n\t\tblock.use_collision = true\n\n\t\tformation.add_child(block)\n\t\tcurrent_y += block_height\n\n\treturn formation\n\n\n## Places deposit nodes at confirmed resource positions.\nfunc _place_deposits() -> void:\n\tvar deposits_parent: Node3D = Node3D.new()\n\tdeposits_parent.name = \"Deposits\"\n\tadd_child(deposits_parent)\n\n\tvar deposit_rng: RandomNumberGenerator = RandomNumberGenerator.new()\n\tdeposit_rng.seed = BIOME_SEED + RNG_OFFSET_DEPOSITS\n\n\t# Place Scrap Metal surface deposits\n\t_surface_scrap_metal_quantities.clear()\n\tfor i: int in range(_scrap_metal_surface_positions.size()):\n\t\tvar pos: Vector3 = _scrap_metal_surface_positions[i]\n\t\tvar quantity: int = deposit_rng.randi_range(SURFACE_NODE_MIN_QUANTITY, SURFACE_NODE_MAX_QUANTITY)\n\t\t_surface_scrap_metal_quantities.append(quantity)\n\t\tvar deposit: Deposit = _create_deposit(\n\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.SCRAP_METAL,\n\t\t\tquantity,\n\t\t\tpos,\n\t\t\tfalse,\n\t\t\t\"ScrapMetal_%d\" % i\n\t\t)\n\t\tdeposits_parent.add_child(deposit)\n\n\t# Place Cryonite surface deposits\n\t_surface_cryonite_quantities.clear()\n\tfor i: int in range(_cryonite_surface_positions.size()):\n\t\tvar pos: Vector3 = _cryonite_surface_positions[i]\n\t\tvar quantity: int = deposit_rng.randi_range(SURFACE_NODE_MIN_QUANTITY, SURFACE_NODE_MAX_QUANTITY)\n\t\t_surface_cryonite_quantities.append(quantity)\n\t\tvar deposit: Deposit = _create_deposit(\n\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.CRYONITE,\n\t\t\tquantity,\n\t\t\tpos,\n\t\t\tfalse,\n\t\t\t\"Cryonite_%d\" % i\n\t\t)\n\t\tdeposits_parent.add_child(deposit)\n\n\t# Place deep Scrap Metal nodes\n\tfor i: int in range(_deep_scrap_metal_positions.size()):\n\t\tvar pos: Vector3 = _deep_scrap_metal_positions[i]\n\t\tvar deposit: Deposit = _create_deposit(\n\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.SCRAP_METAL,\n\t\t\tDEEP_NODE_QUANTITY,\n\t\t\tpos,\n\t\t\ttrue,\n\t\t\t\"DeepScrapMetal_%d\" % i\n\t\t)\n\t\tdeposits_parent.add_child(deposit)\n\n\t# Place deep Cryonite nodes\n\tfor i: int in range(_deep_cryonite_positions.size()):\n\t\tvar pos: Vector3 = _deep_cryonite_positions[i]\n\t\tvar deposit: Deposit = _create_deposit(\n\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.CRYONITE,\n\t\t\tDEEP_NODE_QUANTITY,\n\t\t\tpos,\n\t\t\ttrue,\n\t\t\t\"DeepCryonite_%d\" % i\n\t\t)\n\t\tdeposits_parent.add_child(deposit)\n\n\n## Creates a single deposit node configured for the given resource type and position.\nfunc _create_deposit(\n\tresource_type: ResourceDefs.ResourceType,\n\tquantity: int,\n\tworld_position: Vector3,\n\tis_deep: bool,\n\tdeposit_name: String\n) -> Deposit:\n\tvar deposit: Deposit = Deposit.new()\n\tdeposit.name = deposit_name\n\tdeposit.setup(\n\t\tresource_type,\n\t\tResourceDefs.Purity.THREE_STAR,\n\t\tResourceDefs.DensityTier.MEDIUM,\n\t\tquantity\n\t)\n\tdeposit.position = world_position\n\n\tif is_deep:\n\t\tdeposit.infinite = true\n\t\tdeposit.yield_rate = DEEP_NODE_YIELD_RATE\n\t\tdeposit.add_to_group(\"deep_deposit\")\n\telse:\n\t\tdeposit.add_to_group(\"surface_deposit\")\n\n\tdeposit.add_to_group(\"interactable\")\n\n\t# Add interaction collision body so scanner raycast (mask=INTERACTABLE) can hit deposits\n\tvar interact_body: StaticBody3D = StaticBody3D.new()\n\tinteract_body.name = \"InteractBody\"\n\tinteract_body.collision_layer = PhysicsLayers.INTERACTABLE\n\tinteract_body.collision_mask = 0\n\tvar interact_col: CollisionShape3D = CollisionShape3D.new()\n\tinteract_col.name = \"CollisionShape3D\"\n\tvar interact_box: BoxShape3D = BoxShape3D.new()\n\tinteract_box.size = Vector3(1.5, 1.5, 1.5)\n\tinteract_col.shape = interact_box\n\tinteract_body.add_child(interact_col)\n\tdeposit.add_child(interact_body)\n\n\t# Register with DepositRegistry so scanner ping can detect this deposit\n\tDepositRegistry.register(deposit)\n\n\treturn deposit\n\n\n## Creates Marker3D nodes for player and ship spawn points.\nfunc _create_spawn_points() -> void:\n\tvar player_marker: Marker3D = Marker3D.new()\n\tplayer_marker.name = \"PlayerSpawnPoint\"\n\tplayer_marker.position = _player_spawn_position\n\tadd_child(player_marker)\n\n\tvar ship_marker: Marker3D = Marker3D.new()\n\tship_marker.name = \"ShipSpawnPoint\"\n\tship_marker.position = _ship_spawn_position\n\tadd_child(ship_marker)\n\n\n## Sets up the world boundary manager with invisible walls.\nfunc _setup_world_boundary() -> void:\n\tvar boundary: WorldBoundaryManager = WorldBoundaryManager.new()\n\tboundary.name = \"WorldBoundaryManager\"\n\tadd_child(boundary)\n\tboundary.initialize(_archetype)\n\n\n# ── Private Methods: Helpers ─────────────────────────────\n\n## Gets the terrain height at a world XZ position by sampling the heightmap.\nfunc _get_terrain_height(world_x: float, world_z: float) -> float:\n\tif _terrain_result == null or _terrain_result.heightmap.is_empty():\n\t\treturn 0.0\n\tvar resolution: int = _terrain_result.heightmap_resolution\n\tvar spacing: float = TERRAIN_SIZE / float(resolution - 1)\n\tvar xi: int = clampi(roundi(world_x / spacing), 0, resolution - 1)\n\tvar zi: int = clampi(roundi(world_z / spacing), 0, resolution - 1)\n\treturn _terrain_result.heightmap[zi * resolution + xi]\n","numLines":612,"startLine":1,"totalLines":612}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CuigebzCiFv8CruUZCKnfS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, I now see the RockWarrensBiome. It has `generate()` method and does have `get_player_spawn_position()` and `get_ship_spawn_position()`. The biome also has a `_ready()` method? Let me check... no, it doesn't override `_ready()`. So when `RockWarrensBiome.new()` is created and added to the scene tree, it doesn't auto-generate.\n\nLooking at `execute_biome_swap`:\n```gdscript\nfunc execute_biome_swap(destination_id: String) -> bool:\n    var new_biome: Node3D = create_biome_node(destination_id)\n\n\n```\n\nAfter adding the biome to the scene, the code checks if it's empty and calls either `generate()` or `build_scene()` depending on which method exists, then repositions the player and ship at their spawn points.\n\n```\nThe spawn positions come from the biome's `get_player_spawn_position()` and `get_ship_spawn_position()` methods, which should return valid Vector3 values set during generation. So the biome swap logic looks sound—the terrain should update, and both player and ship should reposition correctly. But wait, I just realized something about the NavigationConsole: when `_on_confirm_pressed` closes the panel, it calls `_animate_close()` which hides the CanvasLayer, and then `close_panel()` calls `Input.set_mouse`—that's where the thought cuts off, but this might be interfering with the biome transition somehow.\n```\n_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED)` and re-enables gameplay inputs via `InputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)`. This creates a race condition where inputs get re-enabled during the transition when they should stay disabled. Even so, that shouldn't prevent the fade and biome swap from happening. I'm wondering if `_on_confirm_pressed()` is actually being called at all, or if `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel` is failing silently somewhere.\n\nIf `NavigationSystem` were null, it would throw a push_error that wouldn't crash the game but would log to the Godot console — not the in-game display. But we know `NavigationSystem` is an autoload and `can_travel_to()` works fine, so that's not it. I think I need to step back and reconsider the whole flow from a different angle.\n\nLet me trace through what happens when the confirm button is pressed: `initiate_travel()` runs synchronously, which triggers fuel consumption and emits signals that cascade through the UI updates, state transitions, and eventually the fade animation. The issue might be in how these synchronous and asynchronous operations are interleaving.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the real problem could be in `_refresh_detail()` — when it calls `get_travel_cost()` during the fuel change callback, we're already partway through `initiate_travel()` with the state set to `PREPARING`. Let me check the exact state transitions and when that cost calculation happens. I'm checking the pure calculation functions that determine travel feasibility. Both `get_travel_cost` and `can_travel_to` perform straightforward math without state guards, so after fuel consumption reduces the current amount, the cost calculation stays the same while the available fuel drops below what's needed for travel. cost for the same trip is still 250. 750 >= 250 → true. So `can_travel_to` still returns true.\n\nWait, actually, that depends on the cost. If the cost is high enough that consuming it brings the fuel below the cost, then `can_travel_to` would return false. For example, if fuel is 1000 and cost is 600, after consuming 600, the fuel is 400. 400 >= 600 → false. So `can_travel_to` returns false and the button is disabled.\n\nBut this only affects the UI — it doesn't prevent the ongoing travel.\n\nHmm, but what about a more edge case: what if the fuel is EXACTLY equal to the cost? Then after consuming, fuel is 0, and `can_travel_to` returns false (0 >= cost → false if cost > 0). Button is disabled.\n\nBut again, this is just UI. It doesn't affect the travel that's already in progress.\n\nOK, let me try one more thing. What if `_refresh_detail()` is called during the button click processing? The button enters its pressed state when the user clicks, but if `_refresh_detail()` runs and sets `disabled = true` before the pressed signal fires, the signal might not trigger at all. Let me trace through this scenario: user presses the button, it enters pressed state, then `_refresh_detail()` gets called and disables it mid-click.\n\nActually, I think the real issue might be in the keyboard input path. If the user opens the console and presses a key to confirm travel, `_on_confirm_pressed` gets called from the input handler, but `_selected_biome_id` might be empty because the user never explicitly selected a biome.\n\nLet me trace through what happens: when the console opens, the map loses focus and `_selected_index` resets to 0. If the user then presses Enter, it selects the first biome and sets `_selected_biome_id` properly. But if something's off with the timing or the selection logic, the ID could still be empty when the confirm button fires. The button should be disabled when no biome is selected, which prevents clicking CONFIRM TRAVEL without choosing one first. But the producer reports the button is enabled and clickable, so something else must be causing the issue. I've narrowed it down to a potential race condition in `close_panel()` that might be interfering with the input state management.\n\nNow I'm wondering if the real problem is that `_on_fuel_changed` gets triggered during the travel sequence and somehow disrupts the flow. Let me trace through what happens when the confirm button is pressed and `initiate_travel` is called.\n\nWhen fuel gets consumed, it emits a signal that triggers the console's refresh logic. The console checks if it's still open, recalculates whether the player can afford the destination based on the new fuel amount, and potentially disables the button. This all happens while the travel sequence is already in motion.\n\nThen the state machine progresses through IN_TRANSIT and ARRIVING before settling into IDLE, at which point it emits the travel_completed signal. This wakes up the TravelSequenceManager, which sets a transitioning flag, disables input, and starts fading out the screen. Meanwhile, the biome_changed signal fires and gets logged. Finally, back in the confirm handler, the panel closes.\n\nAfter the fade completes half a second later, the manager resumes and executes the biome swap—instantiating the new Rock Warrens biome with all its terrain and spawned elements, repositioning both the player and ship at their designated spawn points, then fading back in.\n\nOnce that second fade finishes, inputs are re-enabled, the transition flag clears, and the travel completion signal fires to notify the world that the biome change is done. The whole process takes about a second total—half a second fading to black, half a second fading back in with the new environment loaded—which should produce a noticeable but smooth transition effect.\n\nBut wait, I'm wondering if there's actually a different problem here. What if the CONFIRM TRAVEL button's signal is properly connected but the button itself isn't receiving mouse input due to how Godot handles UI events through nested containers? If the button sits inside a ScrollContainer with a PanelContainer parent, the mouse events might not bubble up correctly, which would prevent the button from ever registering a click in the first place. The ScrollContainer might be consuming mouse events before they reach the button, preventing clicks from registering even when the button is visible on screen.\n\nActually, looking at Godot 4's behavior more carefully — the `scroll_deadzone` defaults to 0, which means clicks should pass through to children immediately without waiting for drag detection. So that's probably not the culprit here. There might be something else about the environment or setup causing the issue.\n\nLet me trace through the `_input` method more carefully. When the CONFIRM TRAVEL button gets clicked, the mouse button press event fires and `_input` gets called. The `ui_cancel` check fails, so execution continues into the focus logic...\n\nActually, I think I've found it. The mouse click doesn't match any of the action checks in the input handler, so the event propagates normally to the GUI system and the button receives the click as expected. But here's what I'm realizing now: the button press does trigger `_on_confirm_pressed`, which calls `initiate_travel`, which emits `travel_completed`, which calls `_on_travel_completed` and creates the fade-out tween. The problem might be that the tween itself never actually completes.\n\nWhat if the NavigationConsole's `_animate_close()` is somehow interfering with the TravelSequenceManager's tween? In Godot 4, tweens are bound to the scene tree and shouldn't interfere with each other, so this would be a pretty unlikely engine bug. But I'm starting to think the real issue is something simpler—there's probably a subtle problem with how the tween is being awaited or how the sequence is structured that's preventing it from finishing properly.\n\nActually, wait. I think I've been missing something obvious. The `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()` might be emitting `travel_completed` synchronously, but the handler in TravelSequenceManager is an async function with `await` statements. That mismatch could be causing the signal to fire before the async handler is properly set up to receive it.\n\nLet me trace through the execution: `travel_completed.emit()` triggers `_on_travel_completed`, which runs synchronously until it hits the first `await _fade_out()`, then suspends. Control returns to `initiate_travel()`, which continues and emits `biome_changed`. Then `close_panel()` gets called. The fade-out tween is running in the background, and after 0.5 seconds the handler resumes. But if the TravelSequenceManager node gets removed from the scene tree during that window, the callback would never resume and the transition would hang.\n\nLooking at `close_panel()`, it only hides the NavigationConsole and re-enables inputs—it doesn't remove any nodes. The TravelSequenceManager is a child of TestWorld, not the NavigationConsole, so it's safe. And nothing in TestWorld is connected to the `panel_closed` signal anyway.\n\nI'm going to add some logging to `_on_confirm_pres