che `_selected_biome_id` in a local variable before closing in case the panel closure clears it. Let me check what `close_panel()` actually does...\n\nExamining the close_panel method...\n\nIt doesn't clear `_selected_biome_id`, just sets `_is_open` to false, re-enables inputs, captures the mouse, animates the close, and emits a signal. But `open_panel()` does reset `_selected_biome_id` to an empty string, so if that gets called again it would be cleared. However, `open_panel()` has an early return if the panel's already open, so that shouldn't be an issue here.\n\nNow I'm implementing the fix by creating a `_close_for_travel()` method that mirrors `close_panel()` but skips re-enabling gameplay inputs, then updating `_on_confirm_pressed` to call this new method instead and adding some logging for the early returns. This keeps the change minimal and focused on preventing the input race condition.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9168,"cache_read_input_tokens":111012,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9168},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"bb48a19d-efdf-4465-8003-b33559e08416"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CuigebzCiFv8CruUZCKnfS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RxZ7A6QJc4R5uYfZAmuf6x","name":"TodoWrite","input":{"todos":[{"content":"Diagnose why CONFIRM TRAVEL button does nothing","status":"completed","activeForm":"Diagnosing CONFIRM TRAVEL signal chain"},{"content":"Fix _on_confirm_pressed — close_panel() re-enables inputs during transition","status":"in_progress","activeForm":"Fixing _on_confirm_pressed race condition"},{"content":"Add logging for silent early returns in _on_confirm_pressed","status":"pend