sage","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PPicnNJcfHtUzphhB9phUL","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\tests\\test_navigation_console_unit.gd"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":894,"cache_read_input_tokens":143372,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":894},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"e1b0cd42-586b-4473-af06-0099f1806adf"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PPicnNJcfHtUzphhB9phUL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Unit tests for the NavigationConsole modal panel. Verifies open/close\n     2→## behavior, destination selection, confirm button state, fuel sufficiency\n     3→## gating, and travel initiation on confirm.\n     4→##\n     5→## Coverage target: 85% (per docs/studio/tdd-process-m8.md)\n     6→## Ticket: TICKET-0167\n     7→class_name TestNavigationConsoleUnit\n     8→extends TestSuite\n     9→\n    10→\n    11→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    12→\n    13→var _console: NavigationConsole = null\n    14→var _spy: SignalSpy = null\n    15→\n    16→\n    17→# ── Setup / Teardown ──────────────────────────────────────\n    18→\n    19→func before_each() -> void:\n    20→\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n    21→\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n    22→\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n    23→\tShipState.reset()\n    24→\t_console = NavigationConsole.new()\n    25→\tadd_child(_console)\n    26→\t# Wait one frame for _ready to complete\n    27→\tawait get_tree().process_frame\n    28→\t_spy = SignalSpy.new()\n    29→\t_spy.watch(_console, \"travel_confirmed\")\n    30→\t_spy.watch(_console, \"panel_closed\")\n    31→\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"travel_completed\")\n    32→\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"travel_blocked\")\n    33→\n    34→\n    35→func after_each() -> void:\n    36→\tif _console and _console.is_open():\n    37→\t\t_console.close_panel()\n    38→\tif _console:\n    39→\t\t_console.queue_free()\n    40→\t\t_console = null\n    41→\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n    42→\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n    43→\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n    44→\tShipState.reset()\n    45→\t_spy.clear()\n    46→\t_spy = null\n    47→\n    48→\n    49→# ── Test Registration ─────────────────────────────────────\n    50→\n    51→func register_tests() -> void:\n    52→\t# Open / close behavior\n    53→\tadd_test(\"console_starts_closed\", _test_console_starts_closed)\n    54→\tadd_test(\"console_opens_successfully\", _test_console_opens_successfully)\n    55→\tadd_test(\"console_closes_successfully\", _test_console_closes_successfully)\n    56→\tadd_test(\"console_emits_panel_closed_on_close\", _test_console_emits_panel_closed_on_close)\n    57→\tadd_test(\"console_double_open_is_noop\", _test_console_double_open_is_noop)\n    58→\tadd_test(\"console_double_close_is_noop\", _test_console_double_close_is_noop)\n    59→\n    60→\t# Destination selection\n    61→\tadd_test(\"console_no_selection_on_open\", _test_console_no_selection_on_open)\n    62→\tadd_test(\"console_confirm_disabled_when_no_selection\", _test_console_confirm_disabled_when_no_selection)\n    63→\n    64→\t# Fuel sufficiency gating\n    65→\tadd_test(\"console_confirm_disabled_when_fuel_empty\", _test_console_confirm_disabled_when_fuel_empty)\n    66→\tadd_test(\"console_confirm_enabled_when_fuel_sufficient\", _test_console_confirm_enabled_when_fuel_sufficient)\n    67→\n    68→\t# Travel initiation\n    69→\tadd_test(\"console_travel_confirmed_signal_on_confirm\", _test_console_travel_confirmed_signal_on_confirm)\n    70→\tadd_test(\"console_closes_after_confirm\", _test_console_closes_after_confirm)\n    71→\tadd_test(\"console_travel_initiated_on_confirm\", _test_console_travel_initiated_on_confirm)\n    72→\n    73→\t# Biome node display\n    74→\tadd_test(\"console_shows_destination_biomes\", _test_console_shows_destination_biomes)\n    75→\tadd_test(\"console_excludes_current_biome_from_destinations\", _test_console_excludes_current_biome_from_destinations)\n    76→\n    77→\n    78→# ── Helpers ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n    79→\n    80→## Drains FuelSystem to zero so any weighted travel attempt will be blocked.\n    81→func _drain_fuel_to_zero() -> void:\n    82→\tFuelSystem.consume_fuel(FuelSystem.fuel_max)\n    83→\n    84→\n    85→## Simulates selecting a biome in the console by calling internal select method.\n    86→func _select_destination(biome_id: String) -> void:\n    87→\t# Access the internal select method via the public test helper pattern\n    88→\t_console._select_biome(biome_id)\n    89→\n    90→\n    91→# ── Test Methods ──────────────────────────────────────────\n    92→\n    93→# -- Open / close --\n    94→\n    95→func _test_console_starts_closed() -> void:\n    96→\tassert_false(_console.is_open(),\n    97→\t\t\"NavigationConsole should start in closed state\")\n    98→\n    99→\n   100→func _test_console_opens_successfully() -> void:\n   101→\t_console.open_panel()\n   102→\tassert_true(_console.is_open(),\n   103→\t\t\"NavigationConsole should be open after open_panel()\")\n   104→\n   105→\n   106→func _test_console_closes_successfully() -> void:\n   107→\t_console.open_panel()\n   108→\t_console.close_panel()\n   109→\tassert_false(_console.is_open(),\n   110→\t\t\"NavigationConsole should be closed after close_panel()\")\n   111→\n   112→\n   113→func _test_console_emits_panel_closed_on_close() -> void:\n   114→\t_console.open_panel()\n   115→\t_console.close_panel()\n   116→\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"panel_closed\",\n   117→\t\t\"panel_closed signal should fire on close_panel()\")\n   118→\n   119→\n   120→func _test_console_double_open_is_noop() -> void:\n   121→\t_console.open_panel()\n   122→\t_console.open_panel()\n   123→\tassert_true(_console.is_open(),\n   124→\t\t\"Double open should not cause errors — panel stays open\")\n   125→\n   126→\n   127→func _test_console_double_close_is_noop() -> void:\n   128→\t_console.open_panel()\n   129→\t_console.close_panel()\n   130→\t_console.close_panel()\n   131→\tassert_false(_console.is_open(),\n   132→\t\t\"Double close should not cause errors — panel stays closed\")\n   133→\n   134→\n   135→# -- Destination selection --\n   136→\n   137→func _test_console_no_selection_on_open() -> void:\n   138→\t_console.open_panel()\n   139→\tassert_equal(_console._selected_biome_id, \"\",\n   140→\t\t\"No biome should be selected when panel first opens\")\n   141→\n   142→\n   143→func _test_console_confirm_disabled_when_no_selection() -> void:\n   144→\t_console.open_panel()\n   145→\tassert_true(_console._confirm_button.disabled,\n   146→\t\t\"Confirm button should be disabled when no destination is selected\")\n   147→\n   148→\n   149→# -- Fuel sufficiency --\n   150→\n   151→func _test_console_confirm_disabled_when_fuel_empty() -> void:\n   152→\t# Add inventory items so travel cost is non-zero\n   153→\tPlayerInventory.add_item(\n   154→\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.METAL, ResourceDefs.Purity.ONE_STAR, 50)\n   155→\t_drain_fuel_to_zero()\n   156→\t_console.open_panel()\n   157→\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n   158→\tassert_true(_console._confirm_button.disabled,\n   159→\t\t\"Confirm button should be disabled when fuel is insufficient\")\n   160→\n   161→\n   162→func _test_console_confirm_enabled_when_fuel_sufficient() -> void:\n   163→\t# Full tank with base ship weight — cost is affordable\n   164→\t_console.open_panel()\n   165→\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n   166→\tassert_false(_console._confirm_button.disabled,\n   167→\t\t\"Confirm button should be enabled when fuel is sufficient\")\n   168→\n   169→\n   170→# -- Travel initiation --\n   171→\n   172→func _test_console_travel_confirmed_signal_on_confirm() -> void:\n   173→\t_console.open_panel()\n   174→\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n   175→\t_console._on_confirm_pressed()\n   176→\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_confirmed\",\n   177→\t\t\"travel_confirmed signal should fire when confirm is pressed\")\n   178→\n   179→\n   180→func _test_console_closes_after_confirm() -> void:\n   181→\t_console.open_panel()\n   182→\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n   183→\t_console._on_confirm_pressed()\n   184→\tassert_false(_console.is_open(),\n   185→\t\t\"Panel should close after confirming travel\")\n   186→\n   187→\n   188→func _test_console_travel_initiated_on_confirm() -> void:\n   189→\t_console.open_panel()\n   190→\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n   191→\t_console._on_confirm_pressed()\n   192→\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_completed\",\n   193→\t\t\"NavigationSystem.travel_completed should fire after confirm\")\n   194→\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"rock_warrens\",\n   195→\t\t\"Current biome should update to rock_warrens after travel\")\n   196→\n   197→\n   198→# -- Biome node display --\n   199→\n   200→func _test_console_shows_destination_biomes() -> void:\n   201→\t_console.open_panel()\n   202→\t# Current biome is shattered_flats, so destinations should include rock_warrens and debris_field\n   203→\tassert_true(_console._biome_node_ids.has(\"rock_warrens\"),\n   204→\t\t\"Destination nodes should include rock_warrens\")\n   205→\tassert_true(_console._biome_node_ids.has(\"debris_field\"),\n   206→\t\t\"Destination nodes should include debris_field\")\n   207→\n   208→\n   209→func _test_console_excludes_current_biome_from_destinations() -> void:\n   210→\t_console.open_panel()\n   211→\tassert_false(_console._biome_node_ids.has(\"shattered_flats\"),\n   212→\t\t\"Current biome should not appear in destination nodes\")\n   213→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"479801c5-6985-4811-8fc4-5ed7161d6515","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\tests\\test_navigation_console_unit.gd","content":"## Unit tests for the NavigationConsole modal panel. Verifies open/close\n## behavior, destination selection, confirm button state, fuel sufficiency\n## gating, and travel initiation on confirm.\n##\n## Coverage target: 85% (per docs/studio/tdd-process-m8.md)\n## Ticket: TICKET-0167\nclass_name TestNavigationConsoleUnit\nextends TestSuite\n\n\n# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n\nvar _console: NavigationConsole = null\nvar _spy: SignalSpy = null\n\n\n# ── Setup / Teardown ──────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunc before_each() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n\tShipState.reset()\n\t_console = NavigationConsole.new()\n\tadd_child(_console)\n\t# Wait one frame for _ready to complete\n\tawait get_tree().process_frame\n\t_spy = SignalSpy.new()\n\t_spy.watch(_console, \"travel_confirmed\")\n\t_spy.watch(_console, \"panel_closed\")\n\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"travel_completed\")\n\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"travel_blocked\")\n\n\nfunc after_each() -> void:\n\tif _console and _console.is_open():\n\t\t_console.close_panel()\n\tif _console:\n\t\t_console.queue_free()\n\t\t_console = null\n\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n\tShipState.reset()\n\t_spy.clear()\n\t_spy = null\n\n\n# ── Test Registration ─────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunc register_tests() -> void:\n\t# Open / close behavior\n\tadd_test(\"console_starts_closed\", _test_console_starts_closed)\n\tadd_test(\"console_opens_successfully\", _test_console_opens_successfully)\n\tadd_test(\"console_closes_successfully\", _test_console_closes_successfully)\n\tadd_test(\"console_emits_panel_closed_on_close\", _test_console_emits_panel_closed_on_close)\n\tadd_test(\"console_double_open_is_noop\", _test_console_double_open_is_noop)\n\tadd_test(\"console_double_close_is_noop\", _test_console_double_close_is_noop)\n\n\t# Destination selection\n\tadd_test(\"console_no_selection_on_open\", _test_console_no_selection_on_open)\n\tadd_test(\"console_confirm_disabled_when_no_selection\", _test_console_confirm_disabled_when_no_selection)\n\n\t# Fuel sufficiency gating\n\tadd_test(\"console_confirm_disabled_when_fuel_empty\", _test_console_confirm_disabled_when_fuel_empty)\n\tadd_test(\"console_confirm_enabled_when_fuel_sufficient\", _test_console_confirm_enabled_when_fuel_sufficient)\n\n\t# Travel initiation\n\tadd_test(\"console_travel_confirmed_signal_on_confirm\", _test_console_travel_confirmed_signal_on_confirm)\n\tadd_test(\"console_closes_after_confirm\", _test_console_closes_after_confirm)\n\tadd_test(\"console_travel_initiated_on_confirm\", _test_console_travel_initiated_on_confirm)\n\n\t# Biome node display\n\tadd_test(\"console_shows_destination_biomes\", _test_console_shows_destination_biomes)\n\tadd_test(\"console_excludes_current_biome_from_destinations\", _test_console_excludes_current_biome_from_destinations)\n\n\n# ── Helpers ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Drains FuelSystem to zero so any weighted travel attempt will be blocked.\nfunc _drain_fuel_to_zero() -> void:\n\tFuelSystem.consume_fuel(FuelSystem.fuel_max)\n\n\n## Simulates selecting a biome in the console by calling internal select method.\nfunc _select_destination(biome_id: String) -> void:\n\t# Access the internal select method via the public test helper pattern\n\t_console._select_biome(biome_id)\n\n\n# ── Test Methods ──────────────────────────────────────────\n\n# -- Open / close --\n\nfunc _test_console_starts_closed() -> void:\n\tassert_false(_console.is_open(),\n\t\t\"NavigationConsole should start in closed state\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_opens_successfully() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\tassert_true(_console.is_open(),\n\t\t\"NavigationConsole should be open after open_panel()\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_closes_successfully() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t_console.close_panel()\n\tassert_false(_console.is_open(),\n\t\t\"NavigationConsole should be closed after close_panel()\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_emits_panel_closed_on_close() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t_console.close_panel()\n\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"panel_closed\",\n\t\t\"panel_closed signal should fire on close_panel()\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_double_open_is_noop() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\tassert_true(_console.is_open(),\n\t\t\"Double open should not cause errors — panel stays open\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_double_close_is_noop() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t_console.close_panel()\n\t_console.close_panel()\n\tassert_false(_console.is_open(),\n\t\t\"Double close should not cause errors — panel stays closed\")\n\n\n# -- Destination selection --\n\nfunc _test_console_no_selection_on_open() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\tassert_equal(_console._selected_biome_id, \"\",\n\t\t\"No biome should be selected when panel first opens\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_confirm_disabled_when_no_selection() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\tassert_true(_console._confirm_button.disabled,\n\t\t\"Confirm button should be disabled when no destination is selected\")\n\n\n# -- Fuel sufficiency --\n\nfunc _test_console_confirm_disabled_when_fuel_empty() -> void:\n\t# Add inventory items so travel cost is non-zero\n\tPlayerInventory.add_item(\n\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.METAL, ResourceDefs.Purity.ONE_STAR, 50)\n\t_drain_fuel_to_zero()\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_true(_console._confirm_button.disabled,\n\t\t\"Confirm button should be disabled when fuel is insufficient\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_confirm_enabled_when_fuel_sufficient() -> void:\n\t# Full tank with base ship weight — cost is affordable\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_false(_console._confirm_button.disabled,\n\t\t\"Confirm button should be enabled when fuel is sufficient\")\n\n\n# -- Travel initiation --\n\nfunc _test_console_travel_confirmed_signal_on_confirm() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n\t_console._on_confirm_pressed()\n\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_confirmed\",\n\t\t\"travel_confirmed signal should fire when confirm is pressed\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_closes_after_confirm() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n\t_console._on_confirm_pressed()\n\tassert_false(_console.is_open(),\n\t\t\"Panel should close after confirming travel\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_travel_initiated_on_confirm() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t_select_destination(\"rock_warrens\")\n\t_console._on_confirm_pressed()\n\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_completed\",\n\t\t\"NavigationSystem.travel_completed should fire after confirm\")\n\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"rock_warrens\",\n\t\t\"Current biome should update to rock_warrens after travel\")\n\n\n# -- Biome node display --\n\nfunc _test_console_shows_destination_biomes() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\t# Current biome is shattered_flats, so destinations should include rock_warrens and debris_field\n\tassert_true(_console._biome_node_ids.has(\"rock_warrens\"),\n\t\t\"Destination nodes should include rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_true(_console._biome_node_ids.has(\"debris_field\"),\n\t\t\"Destination nodes should include debris_field\")\n\n\nfunc _test_console_excludes_current_biome_from_destinations() -> void:\n\t_console.open_panel()\n\tassert_false(_console._biome_node_ids.has(\"shattered_flats\"),\n\t\t\"Current biome should not appear in destination nodes\")\n","numLines":213,"startLine":1,"totalLines":213}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LMBbhb3ZCAmrZnrPtN6jDp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The test `_test_console_closes_after_confirm` checks that `_console.is_open()` is false after `_on_confirm_pressed()`. In the original code, `close_panel()` was called which sets `_is_open = false`. In my fix, `_close_for_travel()` also sets `_is_open = false`. So this test should still pass.\n\nThe test `_test_console_travel_initiated_on_confirm` checks that:\n1. `travel_completed` signal was emitted\n2. `current_biome` is \"rock_warrens\"\n\nIn my fix, the order changed: `_close_for_travel()` is called BEFORE `initiate_travel()`. \n\nSince `_close_for_travel()` only handles UI cleanup and doesn't touch the NavigationSystem, the travel logic still runs correctly and emits the signal as expected. The remaining tests for `travel_confirmed` and `panel_closed` signals should also pass since those emissions happen in the right order.\n\nLet me trace through `_test_console_closes_after_confirm` more carefully: when `_on_confirm_pressed()` executes, it closes the UI first, then initiates travel. If a `fuel_changed` signal fires during travel, the console won't refresh because it's already closed. my changes. The reordering and new method shouldn't break any existing tests. Now I need to verify the travel sequence tests aren't affected by these changes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3063,"cache_read_input_tokens":144266,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3063},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"8ebdaea5-f36c-4ebb-9a01-7e7803c51062"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LMBbhb3ZCAmrZnrPtN6jDp","type":