## Coverage target: 75% (per docs/studio/tdd-process-m8.md — biome travel mechanics)\n     8→## Ticket: TICKET-0168\n     9→class_name TestTravelSequenceUnit\n    10→extends TestSuite\n    11→\n    12→\n    13→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    14→\n    15→var _manager: TravelSequenceManager = null\n    16→var _container: Node3D = null\n    17→var _spy: SignalSpy = null\n    18→\n    19→\n    20→# ── Setup / Teardown ──────────────────────────────────────\n    21→\n    22→func before_each() -> void:\n    23→\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n    24→\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n    25→\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n    26→\tShipState.reset()\n    27→\tResourceRespawnSystem.reset()\n    28→\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n    29→\n    30→\t_container = Node3D.new()\n    31→\t_manager = TravelSequenceManager.new()\n    32→\t_manager.setup(null, null, _container)\n    33→\n    34→\t_spy = SignalSpy.new()\n    35→\t_spy.watch(_manager, \"travel_sequence_started\")\n    36→\t_spy.watch(_manager, \"travel_sequence_completed\")\n    37→\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"travel_completed\")\n    38→\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"biome_changed\")\n    39→\n    40→\n    41→func after_each() -> void:\n    42→\t_spy.clear()\n    43→\t_spy = null\n    44→\n    45→\tif _manager:\n    46→\t\t_manager.teardown()\n    47→\t\t_manager.free()\n    48→\t\t_manager = null\n    49→\n    50→\tif _container:\n    51→\t\tfor child: Node in _container.get_children():\n    52→\t\t\tchild.free()\n    53→\t\t_container.free()\n    54→\t\t_container = null\n    55→\n    56→\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n    57→\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n    58→\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n    59→\tShipState.reset()\n    60→\tResourceRespawnSystem.reset()\n    61→\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n    62→\n    63→\n    64→# ── Test Registration ─────────────────────────────────────\n    65→\n    66→func register_tests() -> void:\n    67→\t# Biome creation by ID\n    68→\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node)\n    69→\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node)\n    70→\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node)\n    71→\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null\", _test_create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null)\n    72→\n    73→\t# Initial state\n    74→\tadd_test(\"initial_is_transitioning_is_false\", _test_initial_is_transitioning_is_false)\n    75→\n    76→\t# Travel sequence signal flow\n    77→\tadd_test(\"travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel\", _test_travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel)\n    78→\tadd_test(\"travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap\", _test_travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap)\n    79→\tadd_test(\"biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel\", _test_biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel)\n    80→\n    81→\t# Input management\n    82→\tadd_test(\"input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes\", _test_input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes)\n    83→\n    84→\t# Biome swap\n    85→\tadd_test(\"current_biome_node_updated_after_travel\", _test_current_biome_node_updated_after_travel)\n    86→\tadd_test(\"biome_container_has_child_after_travel\", _test_biome_container_has_child_after_travel)\n    87→\tadd_test(\"old_biome_removed_on_second_travel\", _test_old_biome_removed_on_second_travel)\n    88→\n    89→\t# Player/ship spawn position\n    90→\tadd_test(\"get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position\", _test_get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position)\n    91→\tadd_test(\"get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position\", _test_get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position)\n    92→\n    93→\t# Error handling\n    94→\tadd_test(\"invalid_biome_swap_returns_false\", _test_invalid_biome_swap_returns_false)\n    95→\tadd_test(\"input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap\", _test_input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap)\n    96→\tadd_test(\"sequential_travel_works_correctly\", _test_sequential_travel_works_correctly)\n    97→\n    98→\n    99→# ── Test Methods: Biome Creation ─────────────────────────\n   100→\n   101→func _test_create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node() -> void:\n   102→\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"shattered_flats\")\n   103→\tassert_not_null(node,\n   104→\t\t\"create_biome_node('shattered_flats') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n   105→\tif node:\n   106→\t\tnode.free()\n   107→\n   108→\n   109→func _test_create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node() -> void:\n   110→\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n   111→\tassert_not_null(node,\n   112→\t\t\"create_biome_node('rock_warrens') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n   113→\tif node:\n   114→\t\tnode.free()\n   115→\n   116→\n   117→func _test_create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node() -> void:\n   118→\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"debris_field\")\n   119→\tassert_not_null(node,\n   120→\t\t\"create_biome_node('debris_field') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n   121→\tif node:\n   122→\t\tnode.free()\n   123→\n   124→\n   125→func _test_create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null() -> void:\n   126→\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"unknown_void\")\n   127→\tassert_null(node,\n   128→\t\t\"create_biome_node with invalid ID should return null\")\n   129→\n   130→\n   131→# ── Test Methods: Initial State ──────────────────────────\n   132→\n   133→func _test_initial_is_transitioning_is_false() -> void:\n   134→\tassert_false(_manager.is_transitioning(),\n   135→\t\t\"TravelSequenceManager should not be transitioning initially\")\n   136→\n   137→\n   138→# ── Test Methods: Signal Flow ────────────────────────────\n   139→\n   140→func _test_travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel() -> void:\n   141→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   142→\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_sequence_started\",\n   143→\t\t\"travel_sequence_started should emit when NavigationSystem.travel_completed fires\")\n   144→\n   145→\n   146→func _test_travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap() -> void:\n   147→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   148→\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_sequence_completed\",\n   149→\t\t\"travel_sequence_completed should emit after biome swap finishes\")\n   150→\n   151→\n   152→func _test_biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel() -> void:\n   153→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   154→\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"biome_changed\",\n   155→\t\t\"NavigationSystem.biome_changed should fire on successful travel\")\n   156→\n   157→\n   158→# ── Test Methods: Input Management ───────────────────────\n   159→\n   160→func _test_input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes() -> void:\n   161→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   162→\tassert_true(InputManager.is_gameplay_inputs_enabled(),\n   163→\t\t\"Gameplay inputs should be re-enabled after travel sequence completes\")\n   164→\n   165→\n   166→# ── Test Methods: Biome Swap ─────────────────────────────\n   167→\n   168→func _test_current_biome_node_updated_after_travel() -> void:\n   169→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   170→\tvar biome_node: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n   171→\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n   172→\t\t\"Current biome node should be set after travel completes\")\n   173→\n   174→\n   175→func _test_biome_container_has_child_after_travel() -> void:\n   176→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   177→\tassert_true(_container.get_child_count() > 0,\n   178→\t\t\"Biome container should have a child biome node after travel\")\n   179→\n   180→\n   181→func _test_old_biome_removed_on_second_travel() -> void:\n   182→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   183→\tvar first_biome: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n   184→\tassert_not_null(first_biome,\n   185→\t\t\"First biome node should exist after first travel\")\n   186→\n   187→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"debris_field\")\n   188→\t# Container should have exactly one child (the new biome)\n   189→\tassert_equal(_container.get_child_count(), 1,\n   190→\t\t\"Container should have exactly one biome node after second travel\")\n   191→\tvar second_biome: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n   192→\tassert_not_null(second_biome,\n   193→\t\t\"Second biome node should exist after second travel\")\n   194→\n   195→\n   196→# ── Test Methods: Spawn Positions ────────────────────────\n   197→\n   198→func _test_get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position() -> void:\n   199→\tvar biome_node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n   200→\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n   201→\t\t\"Biome node should be created for spawn point test\")\n   202→\tif biome_node:\n   203→\t\tadd_child(biome_node)\n   204→\t\tif biome_node.has_method(\"generate\"):\n   205→\t\t\tbiome_node.generate()\n   206→\t\tvar spawn: Vector3 = TravelSequenceManager.get_biome_player_spawn(biome_node)\n   207→\t\tvar is_nonzero: bool = spawn != Vector3.ZERO\n   208→\t\tassert_true(is_nonzero,\n   209→\t\t\t\"Player spawn position should be a non-zero Vector3\")\n   210→\t\tbiome_node.queue_free()\n   211→\n   212→\n   213→func _test_get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position() -> void:\n   214→\tvar biome_node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n   215→\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n   216→\t\t\"Biome node should be created for spawn point test\")\n   217→\tif biome_node:\n   218→\t\tadd_child(biome_node)\n   219→\t\tif biome_node.has_method(\"generate\"):\n   220→\t\t\tbiome_node.generate()\n   221→\t\tvar spawn: Vector3 = TravelSequenceManager.get_biome_ship_spawn(biome_node)\n   222→\t\tvar is_nonzero: bool = spawn != Vector3.ZERO\n   223→\t\tassert_true(is_nonzero,\n   224→\t\t\t\"Ship spawn position should be a non-zero Vector3\")\n   225→\t\tbiome_node.queue_free()\n   226→\n   227→\n   228→# ── Test Methods: Error Handling ─────────────────────────\n   229→\n   230→func _test_invalid_biome_swap_returns_false() -> void:\n   231→\tvar result: bool = _manager.execute_biome_swap(\"nonexistent_biome\")\n   232→\tassert_false(result,\n   233→\t\t\"execute_biome_swap with invalid biome should return false\")\n   234→\n   235→\n   236→func _test_input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap() -> void:\n   237→\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n   238→\t_manager.execute_biome_swap(\"invalid_zone\")\n   239→\tassert_true(InputManager.is_gameplay_inputs_enabled(),\n   240→\t\t\"Input should remain enabled after a failed biome swap\")\n   241→\n   242→\n   243→func _test_sequential_travel_works_correctly() -> void:\n   244→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   245→\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"rock_warrens\",\n   246→\t\t\"Should be at rock_warrens after first travel\")\n   247→\n   248→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"debris_field\")\n   249→\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"debris_field\",\n   250→\t\t\"Should be at debris_field after second travel\")\n   251→\n   252→\tvar biome_node: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n   253→\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n   254→\t\t\"Current biome node should be set after sequential travel\")\n   255→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"e01f344f-7f55-43ec-b130-d87ae90289e7","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\tests\\test_travel_sequence_unit.gd","content":"## Unit tests for the travel sequence system. Verifies biome creation by ID,\n## transition state management, signal emissions, input toggling, and error\n## handling during inter-biome travel. Covers TICKET-0168 acceptance criteria:\n## scene transition completes, player position valid after arrival,\n## biome_changed signal fired, input re-enabled.\n##\n## Coverage target: 75% (per docs/studio/tdd-process-m8.md — biome travel mechanics)\n## Ticket: TICKET-0168\nclass_name TestTravelSequenceUnit\nextends TestSuite\n\n\n# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n\nvar _manager: TravelSequenceManager = null\nvar _container: Node3D = null\nvar _spy: SignalSpy = null\n\n\n# ── Setup / Teardown ──────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunc before_each() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n\tShipState.reset()\n\tResourceRespawnSystem.reset()\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\n\t_container = Node3D.new()\n\t_manager = TravelSequenceManager.new()\n\t_manager.setup(null, null, _container)\n\n\t_spy = SignalSpy.new()\n\t_spy.watch(_manager, \"travel_sequence_started\")\n\t_spy.watch(_manager, \"travel_sequence_completed\")\n\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"travel_completed\")\n\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"biome_changed\")\n\n\nfunc after_each() -> void:\n\t_spy.clear()\n\t_spy = null\n\n\tif _manager:\n\t\t_manager.teardown()\n\t\t_manager.free()\n\t\t_manager = null\n\n\tif _container:\n\t\tfor child: Node in _container.get_children():\n\t\t\tchild.free()\n\t\t_container.free()\n\t\t_container = null\n\n\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n\tShipState.reset()\n\tResourceRespawnSystem.reset()\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\n\n# ── Test Registration ─────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunc register_tests() -> void:\n\t# Biome creation by ID\n\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node)\n\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node)\n\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node)\n\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null\", _test_create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null)\n\n\t# Initial state\n\tadd_test(\"initial_is_transitioning_is_false\", _test_initial_is_transitioning_is_false)\n\n\t# Travel sequence signal flow\n\tadd_test(\"travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel\", _test_travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel)\n\tadd_test(\"travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap\", _test_travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap)\n\tadd_test(\"biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel\", _test_biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel)\n\n\t# Input management\n\tadd_test(\"input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes\", _test_input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes)\n\n\t# Biome swap\n\tadd_test(\"current_biome_node_updated_after_travel\", _test_current_biome_node_updated_after_travel)\n\tadd_test(\"biome_container_has_child_after_travel\", _test_biome_container_has_child_after_travel)\n\tadd_test(\"old_biome_removed_on_second_travel\", _test_old_biome_removed_on_second_travel)\n\n\t# Player/ship spawn position\n\tadd_test(\"get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position\", _test_get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position)\n\tadd_test(\"get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position\", _test_get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position)\n\n\t# Error handling\n\tadd_test(\"invalid_biome_swap_returns_false\", _test_invalid_biome_swap_returns_false)\n\tadd_test(\"input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap\", _test_input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap)\n\tadd_test(\"sequential_travel_works_correctly\", _test_sequential_travel_works_correctly)\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Biome Creation ─────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node() -> void:\n\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"shattered_flats\")\n\tassert_not_null(node,\n\t\t\"create_biome_node('shattered_flats') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n\tif node:\n\t\tnode.free()\n\n\nfunc _test_create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node() -> void:\n\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_not_null(node,\n\t\t\"create_biome_node('rock_warrens') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n\tif node:\n\t\tnode.free()\n\n\nfunc _test_create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node() -> void:\n\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"debris_field\")\n\tassert_not_null(node,\n\t\t\"create_biome_node('debris_field') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n\tif node:\n\t\tnode.free()\n\n\nfunc _test_create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null() -> void:\n\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"unknown_void\")\n\tassert_null(node,\n\t\t\"create_biome_node with invalid ID should return null\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Initial State ──────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_initial_is_transitioning_is_false() -> void:\n\tassert_false(_manager.is_transitioning(),\n\t\t\"TravelSequenceManager should not be transitioning initially\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Signal Flow ────────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_sequence_started\",\n\t\t\"travel_sequence_started should emit when NavigationSystem.travel_completed fires\")\n\n\nfunc _test_travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_sequence_completed\",\n\t\t\"travel_sequence_completed should emit after biome swap finishes\")\n\n\nfunc _test_biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"biome_changed\",\n\t\t\"NavigationSystem.biome_changed should fire on successful travel\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Input Management ───────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_true(InputManager.is_gameplay_inputs_enabled(),\n\t\t\"Gameplay inputs should be re-enabled after travel sequence completes\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Biome Swap ─────────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_current_biome_node_updated_after_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tvar biome_node: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n\t\t\"Current biome node should be set after travel completes\")\n\n\nfunc _test_biome_container_has_child_after_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_true(_container.get_child_count() > 0,\n\t\t\"Biome container should have a child biome node after travel\")\n\n\nfunc _test_old_biome_removed_on_second_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tvar first_biome: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n\tassert_not_null(first_biome,\n\t\t\"First biome node should exist after first travel\")\n\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"debris_field\")\n\t# Container should have exactly one child (the new biome)\n\tassert_equal(_container.get_child_count(), 1,\n\t\t\"Container should have exactly one biome node after second travel\")\n\tvar second_biome: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n\tassert_not_null(second_biome,\n\t\t\"Second biome node should exist after second travel\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Spawn Positions ────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position() -> void:\n\tvar biome_node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n\t\t\"Biome node should be created for spawn point test\")\n\tif biome_node:\n\t\tadd_child(biome_node)\n\t\tif biome_node.has_method(\"generate\"):\n\t\t\tbiome_node.generate()\n\t\tvar spawn: Vector3 = TravelSequenceManager.get_biome_player_spawn(biome_node)\n\t\tvar is_nonzero: bool = spawn != Vector3.ZERO\n\t\tassert_true(is_nonzero,\n\t\t\t\"Player spawn position should be a non-zero Vector3\")\n\t\tbiome_node.queue_free()\n\n\nfunc _test_get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position() -> void:\n\tvar biome_node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n\t\t\"Biome node should be created for spawn point test\")\n\tif biome_node:\n\t\tadd_child(biome_node)\n\t\tif biome_node.has_method(\"generate\"):\n\t\t\tbiome_node.generate()\n\t\tvar spawn: Vector3 = TravelSequenceManager.get_biome_ship_spawn(biome_node)\n\t\tvar is_nonzero: bool = spawn != Vector3.ZERO\n\t\tassert_true(is_nonzero,\n\t\t\t\"Ship spawn position should be a non-zero Vector3\")\n\t\tbiome_node.queue_free()\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Error Handling ─────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_invalid_biome_swap_returns_false() -> void:\n\tvar result: bool = _manager.execute_biome_swap(\"nonexistent_biome\")\n\tassert_false(result,\n\t\t\"execute_biome_swap with invalid biome should return false\")\n\n\nfunc _test_input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap() -> void:\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\t_manager.execute_biome_swap(\"invalid_zone\")\n\tassert_true(InputManager.is_gameplay_inputs_enabled(),\n\t\t\"Input should remain enabled after a failed biome swap\")\n\n\nfunc _test_sequential_travel_works_correctly() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"rock_warrens\",\n\t\t\"Should be at rock_warrens after first travel\")\n\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"debris_field\")\n\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"debris_field\",\n\t\t\"Should be at debris_field after second travel\")\n\n\tvar biome_node: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n\t\t\"Current biome node should be set after sequential travel\")\n","numLines":255,"startLine":1,"totalLines":255}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01NJ1eZesDC6pckaRe1Qzurc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The travel sequence tests call `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")` directly, not through the NavigationConsole. So my changes to `_on_confirm_pressed` don't affect these tests at all. Good.\n\nThe navigation console tests call `_console._on_confirm_pressed()` directly. Let me check if any of them would break:\n\n1. `_test_console_travel_confirmed_signal_on_confirm` — calls `_on_confirm_pressed()`, checks `travel_confirmed` signal. My fix emits `travel_confirmed` before `_close_for_travel()`. Should pass.\n\n\n2. `_test_console_closes_after_confirm` — calls `_on_confirm_pressed()`, checks `is_open() == false`. My fix calls `_close_for_travel()` which sets `_is_open = false`. Should pass.\n3. `_test_console_travel_initiated_on_confirm` — calls `_on_confirm_pressed()`, checks `travel_completed` signal and `current_biome`. Since `initiate_travel` runs synchronously and gets called after `_close_for_travel()`, the signal and biome state should be updated by the time the test checks them. Should pass.\n\nNow I'm looking at `_test_input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes` — it initiates travel and expects inputs to be re-enabled afterward. The `_on_travel_completed` handler disables inputs first, then runs through fade-out and fade-in tweens before re-enabling them. The test might be checking inputs before those tweens finish, so I need to verify the timing works out correctly. The `_fade_out()` function creates a tween that animates the fade rectangle's alpha to 1.0 over a duration, then awaits it to finish. But in the test, the manager isn't added to the scene tree, so `is_inside_tree()` returns false and the function returns early without awaiting anything — meaning inputs get re-enabled immediately, which is why the test passes even though it doesn't explicitly await the travel sequence. The 