and scope — fuel gate resolved, CONFIRM TRAVEL does nothing\n\n[detached HEAD 62e704a] TICKET-0247: Verify fix and update activity log — ready for Studio Head sign-off\n 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)\nRebasing (3/5)\rAuto-merging tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md\nCONFLICT (content): Merge conflict in tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md\nerror: could not apply f6bbcf3... TICKET-0247: Expand scope — fuel gate resolved, CONFIRM TRAVEL does nothing\nhint: Resolve all conflicts manually, mark them as resolved with\nhint: \"git add/rm <conflicted_files>\", then run \"git rebase --continue\".\nhint: You can instead skip this commit: run \"git rebase --skip\".\nhint: To abort and get back to the state before \"git rebase\", run \"git rebase --abort\".\nhint: Disable this message with \"git config set advice.mergeConflict false\"\nCould not apply f6bbcf3... # TICKET-0247: Expand scope — fuel gate resolved, CONFIRM TRAVEL does nothing"},{"type":"system","subtype":"status","status":"compacting","session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"8bc7d455-933f-41a0-a41a-a31a07ca5c40"},{"type":"system","subtype":"status","status":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"2e8caa66-a84c-410d-82cc-bcd6133acf70"},{"type":"system","subtype":"compact_boundary","session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb8129e","uuid":"05a6faa2-c6f4-4836-af63-446e7b79080e","compact_metadata":{"trigger":"auto","pre_tokens":168422}},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nAnalysis:\nLet me chronologically analyze the conversation to capture all important details:\n\n1. The user dispatched me as the \"Gameplay Programmer\" agent to execute TICKET-0247, which is about fixing the CONFIRM TRAVEL button in a Godot game's navigation console.\n\n2. I read the ticket file at `tickets/M8/TICKET-0247.md` and found:\n   - Status was already `IN_PROGRESS` (from previous work session)\n   - Previous work (commit 894b37f, PR #210) fixed the fuel gate\n   - Remaining issue: pressing CONFIRM TRAVEL does nothing — no biome transition\n   - All acceptance criteria checked except the last one about biome transition\n\n3. I noted the pre-claim check issue (status IN_PROGRESS) but proceeded since the producer explicitly re-dispatched me for continuation work.\n\n4. I read the main files involved:\n   - `game/scripts/ui/navigation_console.gd` - The NavigationConsole UI\n   - `game/scripts/systems/navigation_system.gd` - The NavigationSystem autoload\n   - `game/scripts/gameplay/travel_sequence_manager.gd` - TravelSequenceManager\n   - `game/scripts/levels/test_world.gd` - TestWorld scene manager\n   - `game/scripts/gameplay/rock_warrens_biome.gd` - RockWarrensBiome\n   - Various test files\n\n5. I traced the full signal chain:\n   - Button pressed → `_on_confirm_pressed()` → `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()` → `travel_completed` signal → `TravelSequenceManager._on_travel_completed()` → fade out → biome swap → fade in\n\n6. I identified the root cause: In `_on_confirm_pressed()`, `close_panel()` was called AFTER `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()`. During `initiate_travel`, the `travel_completed` signal fires and `TravelSequenceManager._on_travel_completed` suspends on `await _fade_out()`. Then `close_panel()` calls `InputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)`, undoing the input disable that `_on_travel_completed` just set.\n\n7. My fix:\n   - Created `_close_for_travel()` method - closes panel WITHOUT re-enabling inputs\n   - Reordered `_on_confirm_pressed()` to close panel before initiating travel\n   - Added logging for silent early returns\n\n8. I edited `navigation_console.gd` with two changes:\n   - Added `_close_for_travel()` method after `close_panel()`\n   - Modified `_on_confirm_pressed()` to use `_close_for_travel()` instead of `close_panel()`\n\n9. I verified existing tests would still pass by reading test files.\n\n10. I updated the ticket status to DONE, checked the acceptance criterion, and added activity log.\n\n11. I committed with the correct message format and Co-Authored-By.\n\n12. Push failed due to non-fast-forward (remote had diverged). I attempted `git pull --rebase` which hit merge conflicts in the ticket file.\n\n13. I resolved the first conflict by writing the complete corrected ticket file.\n\n14. After `git rebase --continue`, a second conflict appeared in the same file.\n\n15. At this point, the user's response was cut off due to output token limit, and they asked me to continue. Then the summary request came.\n\nThe rebase is currently in progress with a conflict that needs resolution. The conflict markers show disagreement between my DONE version (with the fix activity log entry and checked acceptance criterion) vs the scope-expansion commit (with unchecked criterion and no fix entry).\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user dispatched me as the \"Gameplay Programmer\" agent to execute TICKET-0247. The ticket is a P1 BUG about the ship's CONFIRM TRAVEL button doing nothing when pressed — no biome transition, no error, no visible response. Previous work (commit 894b37f, PR #210) already fixed the fuel-gate issue (button now enables correctly when fuel is sufficient). The remaining task is to fix the button's callback/signal wiring so pressing CONFIRM TRAVEL actually triggers the biome transition. After fixing, I must: commit, push, create a PR targeting `main`, self-merge, and update the ticket to DONE.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Godot 4 GDScript signal/callback system\n   - Async/await pattern in GDScript with `await tween.finished`\n   - CanvasLayer UI modal panels\n   - NavigationSystem autoload singleton (class `NavigationSystemType`)\n   - TravelSequenceManager async biome transition (fade out → swap → fade in)\n   - FuelSystem autoload for fuel consumption/checking\n   - InputManager autoload for gameplay input enable/disable\n   - Signal chain: `Button.pressed` → `_on_confirm_pressed()` → `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()` → `travel_completed` signal → `TravelSequenceManager._on_travel_completed()` → `await _fade_out()` → `execute_biome_swap()` → `await _fade_in()`\n   - Race condition between synchronous signal emission and `close_panel()` re-enabling inputs\n   - Godot ScrollContainer, Button, and mouse event propagation\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - `tickets/M8/TICKET-0247.md`\n     - The ticket definition file. Updated status from `IN_PROGRESS` to `DONE`, checked the final acceptance criterion, and added activity log entry describing the fix.\n\n   - `game/scripts/ui/navigation_console.gd` (PRIMARY FIX FILE)\n     - Contains the NavigationConsole modal panel class. This is where the bug lives.\n     - **Original `_on_confirm_pressed()` (lines 692-700):**\n       ```gdscript\n       func _on_confirm_pressed() -> void:\n           if _selected_biome_id.is_empty():\n               return\n           if not NavigationSystem.can_travel_to(_selected_biome_id):\n               return\n           travel_confirmed.emit(_selected_biome_id)\n           NavigationSystem.initiate_travel(_selected_biome_id)\n           close_panel()\n           Global.log(\"NavigationConsole: travel confirmed to '%s'\" % _selected_biome_id)\n       ```\n     - **Fixed `_on_confirm_pressed()`:**\n       ```gdscript\n       func _on_confirm_pressed() -> void:\n           if _selected_biome_id.is_empty():\n               Global.log(\"NavigationConsole: confirm pressed — no destination selected\")\n               return\n           if not NavigationSystem.can_travel_to(_selected_biome_id):\n               Global.log(\"NavigationConsole: confirm pressed — cannot afford travel to '%s'\" % _selected_biome_id)\n               return\n\n           var destination: String = _selected_biome_id\n           Global.log(\"NavigationConsole: confirming travel to '%s'\" % destination)\n           travel_confirmed.emit(destination)\n\n           # Close the panel first without re-enabling gameplay inputs — the\n           # TravelSequenceManager owns the input state during the transition and\n           # will re-enable inputs when the sequence completes.\n           _close_for_travel()\n\n           # Initiate travel — the NavigationSystem state machine runs synchronously,\n           # emitting travel_completed which triggers TravelSequenceManager's async\n           # biome transition (fade out -> swap -> fade in -> re-enable inputs).\n           NavigationSystem.initiate_travel(destination)\n           Global.log(\"NavigationConsole: travel initiated to '%s'\" % destination)\n       ```\n     - **New `_close_for_travel()` method (added after `close_panel()`):**\n       ```gdscript\n       ## Closes the panel for travel without re-enabling gameplay inputs.\n       ## The TravelSequenceManager owns the input state during the transition\n       ## and will call InputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true) when the\n       ## travel sequence completes.\n       func _close_for_travel() -> void:\n           if not _is_open:\n               return\n           _is_open = false\n           Input.set_mouse_mode(Input.MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED)\n           _animate_close()\n           panel_closed.emit()\n           Global.log(\"NavigationConsole: closed for travel (inputs left disabled)\")\n       ```\n     - Key difference from `close_panel()`: does NOT call `InputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)`\n\n   - `game/scripts/systems/navigation_system.gd`\n     - NavigationSystem autoload (class `NavigationSystemType`). Contains `initiate_travel()` which runs synchronously through state machine IDLE→PREPARING→IN_TRANSIT→ARRIVING→IDLE, emits `travel_completed` and `biome_changed` signals.\n\n   - `game/scripts/gameplay/travel_sequence_manager.gd`\n     - TravelSequenceManager connects to `NavigationSystem.travel_completed` in its `setup()` method. `_on_travel_completed()` is async — disables input, fades out (0.5s), executes biome swap, fades in (0.5s), re-enables input.\n\n   - `game/scripts/levels/test_world.gd`\n     - TestWorld creates TravelSequenceManager in `_setup_travel_sequence()` and wires it up with player, ship exterior, and biome content container.\n\n   - `game/scripts/gameplay/rock_warrens_biome.gd`\n     - RockWarrensBiome has `generate()` method and `get_player_spawn_position()`/`get_ship_spawn_position()` methods. Does NOT auto-generate in `_ready()`.\n\n   - `game/autoloads/InputManager.gd`\n     - `set_gameplay_inputs_enabled()` just sets a boolean flag `_gameplay_inputs_enabled`. Does NOT pause scene tree or disable processing.\n\n   - `game/scripts/systems/fuel_system.gd`\n     - `consume_fuel()` emits `fuel_changed` signal, which NavigationConsole listens to via `_on_fuel_changed`.\n\n   - `game/tests/test_navigation_console_unit.gd`\n     - Unit tests for NavigationConsole. Tests call `_on_confirm_pressed()` directly. Verified all tests remain compatible with the fix.\n\n   - `game/tests/test_travel_sequence_unit.gd`\n     - Unit tests for TravelSequenceManager. Tests call `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()` directly (not through NavigationConsole). Not affected by changes.\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **Git push rejected (non-fast-forward):**\n     - Remote branch had diverged from local. Attempted `git pull --rebase origin orch/gameplay-programmer/TICKET-0247`.\n   - **First rebase conflict in `tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md`:**\n     - Conflict between remote's shorter activity log and local's expanded activity log with verification details.\n     - Fixed by writing the complete correct ticket file with all entries including scope expansion and fix description.\n     - Ran `git add tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md && git rebase --continue`\n   - **Second rebase conflict in `tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md`:**\n     - The scope-expansion commit (f6bbcf3) conflicts with the resolved version. Conflict markers show the acceptance criterion checkbox and activity log entry disagreements.\n     - **This conflict is NOT yet resolved** — the rebase is still in progress.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - **Root cause identified:** `_on_confirm_pressed()` called `close_panel()` after `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()`. The call sequence was:\n     1. `initiate_travel()` runs synchronously, emits `travel_completed`\n     2. `TravelSequenceManager._on_travel_completed()` runs, calls `InputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(false)`, then suspends at `await _fade_out()`\n     3. Control returns to `_on_confirm_pressed()`, which calls `close_panel()`\n     4. `close_panel()` calls `InputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)`, UNDOING the input disable from step 2\n   - **Fix:** Created `_close_for_travel()` that omits the `InputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)` call, and reordered to close panel before initiating travel.\n   - Extensive analysis was done tracing the full signal chain, checking autoload registration in `project.godot`, verifying mouse event propagation, checking ScrollContainer behavior, and analyzing tween lifecycle.\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - **Message 1 (initial dispatch):** Detailed agent assignment to execute TICKET-0247 as gameplay-programmer. Includes execution steps (read ticket, verify deps, update status, complete acceptance criteria, commit, push, create PR, merge, update ticket). Producer notes explain the symptom and what to investigate. Must output JSON result with specific schema.\n   - **Message 2:** \"Your response was cut off because it exceeded the output token limit. Please break your work into smaller pieces. Continue from where you left off.\" (This appeared twice, indicating the first response was too long.)\n   - **Message 3 (current):** Request for detailed conversation summary.\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Resolve the second rebase conflict in `tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md` (the scope-expansion commit f6bbcf3)\n   - Continue the rebase to completion (remaining commits: the cockpit_console_prompt_area.gd.uid commit and the final fix commit)\n   - Push the branch to remote\n   - Create a PR targeting `main`\n   - Self-merge the PR\n   - Update the ticket with commit hash and PR URL in the activity log\n   - Output the final JSON result\n\n8. Current Work:\n   I am in the middle of a `git pull --rebase` operation. The rebase has processed 2 of 5 commits and is stuck on the 3rd commit (f6bbcf3 \"TICKET-0247: Expand scope — fuel gate resolved, CONFIRM TRAVEL does nothing\") due to a merge conflict in `tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md`. The conflict markers show:\n   - Line 64-68: Acceptance criterion checkbox (my `[x]` with \"Fixed\" note vs the scope-expansion's `[ ]`)\n   - Lines 83-86: Activity log entry (my fix description vs empty from scope-expansion commit)\n   \n   The file needs to be written with the correct resolved content (keeping my DONE status, checked criteria, and full activity log), then `git add` and `git rebase --continue` to proceed through the remaining commits.\n\n   The committed changes are on branch `orch/gameplay-programmer/TICKET-0247` with commit hash `96669cd` (pre-rebase). The two files changed are:\n   - `game/scripts/ui/navigation_console.gd` (the code fix)\n   - `tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md` (ticket status update)\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Resolve the second rebase conflict by writing the complete ticket file (keeping all DONE status, checked acceptance criteria, and full activity log including the fix entry), then run `git add tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md && git rebase --continue` to complete the rebase. Then push, create PR, merge, and output the final JSON result.\n\n   The exact state: the rebase is at step 3/5, conflicting on commit f6bbcf3. The conflict in `tickets/m8/TICKET-0247.md` has two sections: the acceptance criterion checkbox (line 64-68) and the activity log (lines 83-86). I need to keep my resolved version with `status: