ge":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GX7E9WyHCBQ9TqXkdvCHaU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FXcpdzDJtUK2Xdpd1cBNVX","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/.claude/worktrees/orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247 && gh pr create --title \"TICKET-0247: Fix CONFIRM TRAVEL — close panel without re-enabling inputs\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n- **Root cause**: `_on_confirm_pressed()` called `close_panel()` after `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()`. The `travel_completed` signal fires synchronously during `initiate_travel`, triggering `TravelSequenceManager._on_travel_completed` which disables inputs and suspends on `await _fade_out()`. Then `close_panel()` re-enables inputs, undoing the disable and breaking the transition sequence.\n- **Fix**: Created `_close_for_travel()` that closes the panel without re-enabling gameplay inputs (the TravelSequenceManager handles that when the transition completes). Reordered to close panel before initiating travel.\n- Added logging for all silent early-return paths in `_on_confirm_pressed()`.\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] Existing unit tests pass (test_navigation_console_unit.gd, test_travel_sequence_unit.gd)\n- [ ] Manual: open Navigation Console, select Rock Warrens, press CONFIRM TRAVEL — biome transition should execute\n- [ ] Manual: verify inputs are disabled during fade transition and re-enabled after arrival\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" --base main","description":"Create PR targeting main"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":426,"cache_read_input_tokens":54931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":426},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e48025c-31f9-47d5-a435-54bf8bb