nst a cell count instead of the raw unit value, or reading the wrong property from `ShipState`.\r","-\r","-Likely locations to investigate:\r","-\r","-- `game/scripts/ui/navigation_console.gd` — fuel display and travel validation logic\r","-- `game/scripts/systems/ship_state.gd` — fuel unit storage and any fuel-cell conversion helpers\r","-- `game/scripts/systems/navigation_system.gd` (if it exists) — travel cost calculation\r","-\r","-Specific things to check:\r","-1. What is the Fuel Cell → unit conversion ratio? (e.g., 1 cell = 100 units → full tank = 10 cells; that matches the observed \"10 Fuel Cell(s)\" display)\r","-2. Is the travel-cost comparison done in cells or units? If cost is in cells and the check compares against raw units (1000) without converting, the display bug and the gate bug are separate issues.\r","-3. Is there a hardcoded or stale constant standing in for the live fuel value?\r","-\r","-## Acceptance Criteria\r","-\r","-- [x] With a full ship tank (1000 / 1000 units) the navigation console correctly represents available fuel in terms of fuel cells. *(Fixed — commit 894b37f)*\r","-- [x] CONFIRM TRAVEL is enabled when the ship has enough fuel to reach the selected destination. *(Fixed — commit 894b37f)*\r","-- [x] \"Not enough fuel\" warning and disabled button only appear when the tank genuinely cannot cover the journey cost. *(Fixed — commit 894b37f)*\r","-- [x] The fuel unit ↔ fuel cell conversion is consistent between the SHIP FUEL display and the Ship Tank row in the detail panel. *(Fixed — commit 894b37f)*\r","-- [x] Existing unit tests pass; new unit tests added for the fuel conversion and travel eligibility logic. *(Fixed — commit 894b37f)*\r","-<<<<<<< HEAD\r","-- [x] Pressing CONFIRM TRAVEL triggers the biome transition — the game loads the selected biome. *(Fixed — see activity log)*\r","-=======\r","-- [ ] Pressing CONFIRM TRAVEL triggers the biome transition — the game loads the selected biome.\r","->>>>>>> origin/main\r","-\r","-